52// A pattern matcher for abitrary value constants.
53template <typename T, IrOpcode::Value kOpcode>
54struct ValueMatcher : public NodeMatcher {
55 using ValueType = T;
56
57 explicit ValueMatcher(Node* node) : NodeMatcher(node) {
58 static_assert(kOpcode != IrOpcode::kFoldConstant, "unsupported opcode");
59 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFoldConstant) {
60 node = node->InputAt(1);
61 }
62 DCHECK_NE(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kFoldConstant)((void) 0);
63 has_value_ = opcode() == kOpcode;
64 if (has_value_) {
65 value_ = OpParameter<T>(node->op());
66 }
67 }
68
69 bool HasValue() const { return has_value_; }
70 const T& Value() const {
71 DCHECK(HasValue())((void) 0);
72 return value_;
73 }
74
75 private:
76 T value_;
uninitialized field 'this->ValueMatcher::value_'
77 bool has_value_;
78};
79
80
81template <>
82inline ValueMatcher<uint32_t, IrOpcode::kInt32Constant>::ValueMatcher(
83 Node* node)
84 : NodeMatcher(node),
85 value_(),
86 has_value_(opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt32Constant) {
87 if (has_value_) {
88 value_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(OpParameter<int32_t>(node->op()));
89 }
90}
91
92
93template <>
94inline ValueMatcher<int64_t, IrOpcode::kInt64Constant>::ValueMatcher(Node* node)
95 : NodeMatcher(node), value_(), has_value_(false) {
96 if (opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt32Constant) {
97 value_ = OpParameter<int32_t>(node->op());
98 has_value_ = true;
99 } else if (opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt64Constant) {
100 value_ = OpParameter<int64_t>(node->op());
101 has_value_ = true;
102 }
103}
104
105
106template <>
107inline ValueMatcher<uint64_t, IrOpcode::kInt64Constant>::ValueMatcher(
108 Node* node)
109 : NodeMatcher(node), value_(), has_value_(false) {
110 if (opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt32Constant) {
111 value_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(OpParameter<int32_t>(node->op()));
112 has_value_ = true;
113 } else if (opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt64Constant) {
114 value_ = static_cast<uint64_t>(OpParameter<int64_t>(node->op()));
115 has_value_ = true;
116 }
117}
118
119template <>
120inline ValueMatcher<double, IrOpcode::kNumberConstant>::ValueMatcher(Node* node)
121 : NodeMatcher(node), value_(), has_value_(false) {
122 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kNumberConstant) {
123 value_ = OpParameter<double>(node->op());
124 has_value_ = true;
125 } else if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFoldConstant) {
126 node = node->InputAt(1);
127 DCHECK_NE(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kFoldConstant)((void) 0);
128 }
129}
130
131template <>
132inline ValueMatcher<Handle<HeapObject>, IrOpcode::kHeapConstant>::ValueMatcher(
133 Node* node)
134 : NodeMatcher(node), value_(), has_value_(false) {
135 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kHeapConstant) {
136 value_ = OpParameter<Handle<HeapObject>>(node->op());
137 has_value_ = true;
138 } else if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFoldConstant) {
139 node = node->InputAt(1);
140 DCHECK_NE(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kFoldConstant)((void) 0);
141 }
142}
143
144// A pattern matcher for integer constants.
145template <typename T, IrOpcode::Value kOpcode>
146struct IntMatcher final : public ValueMatcher<T, kOpcode> {
147 explicit IntMatcher(Node* node) : ValueMatcher<T, kOpcode>(node) {}
4
←
1 uninitialized field at the end of the constructor call
148
149 bool Is(const T& value) const {
150 return this->HasValue() && this->Value() == value;
151 }
152 bool IsInRange(const T& low, const T& high) const {
153 return this->HasValue() && low <= this->Value() && this->Value() <= high;
154 }
155 bool IsMultipleOf(T n) const {
156 return this->HasValue() && (this->Value() % n) == 0;
157 }
158 bool IsPowerOf2() const {
159 return this->HasValue() && this->Value() > 0 &&
160 (this->Value() & (this->Value() - 1)) == 0;
161 }
162 bool IsNegativePowerOf2() const {
163 return this->HasValue() && this->Value() < 0 &&
164 ((this->Value() == std::numeric_limits<T>::min()) ||
165 (-this->Value() & (-this->Value() - 1)) == 0);
166 }
167 bool IsNegative() const { return this->HasValue() && this->Value() < 0; }
168};
169
170using Int32Matcher = IntMatcher<int32_t, IrOpcode::kInt32Constant>;
171using Uint32Matcher = IntMatcher<uint32_t, IrOpcode::kInt32Constant>;
172using Int64Matcher = IntMatcher<int64_t, IrOpcode::kInt64Constant>;
173using Uint64Matcher = IntMatcher<uint64_t, IrOpcode::kInt64Constant>;
174#if V8_HOST_ARCH_32_BIT
175using IntPtrMatcher = Int32Matcher;
176using UintPtrMatcher = Uint32Matcher;
177#else
178using IntPtrMatcher = Int64Matcher;
179using UintPtrMatcher = Uint64Matcher;
180#endif
181
182
183// A pattern matcher for floating point constants.
184template <typename T, IrOpcode::Value kOpcode>
185struct FloatMatcher final : public ValueMatcher<T, kOpcode> {
186 explicit FloatMatcher(Node* node) : ValueMatcher<T, kOpcode>(node) {}
187
188 bool Is(const T& value) const {
189 return this->HasValue() && this->Value() == value;
190 }
191 bool IsInRange(const T& low, const T& high) const {
192 return this->HasValue() && low <= this->Value() && this->Value() <= high;
193 }
194 bool IsMinusZero() const {
195 return this->Is(0.0) && std::signbit(this->Value());
196 }
197 bool IsNegative() const { return this->HasValue() && this->Value() < 0.0; }
198 bool IsNaN() const { return this->HasValue() && std::isnan(this->Value()); }
199 bool IsZero() const { return this->Is(0.0) && !std::signbit(this->Value()); }
200 bool IsNormal() const {
201 return this->HasValue() && std::isnormal(this->Value());
202 }
203 bool IsInteger() const {
204 return this->HasValue() && std::nearbyint(this->Value()) == this->Value();
205 }
206 bool IsPositiveOrNegativePowerOf2() const {
207 if (!this->HasValue() || (this->Value() == 0.0)) {
208 return false;
209 }
210 Double value = Double(this->Value());
211 return !value.IsInfinite() && base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(value.Significand());
212 }
213};
214
215using Float32Matcher = FloatMatcher<float, IrOpcode::kFloat32Constant>;
216using Float64Matcher = FloatMatcher<double, IrOpcode::kFloat64Constant>;
217using NumberMatcher = FloatMatcher<double, IrOpcode::kNumberConstant>;
218
219// A pattern matcher for heap object constants.
220template <IrOpcode::Value kHeapConstantOpcode>
221struct HeapObjectMatcherImpl final
222 : public ValueMatcher<Handle<HeapObject>, kHeapConstantOpcode> {
223 explicit HeapObjectMatcherImpl(Node* node)
224 : ValueMatcher<Handle<HeapObject>, kHeapConstantOpcode>(node) {}
225
226 bool Is(Handle<HeapObject> const& value) const {
227 return this->HasValue() && this->Value().address() == value.address();
228 }
229
230 HeapObjectRef Ref(JSHeapBroker* broker) const {
231 return HeapObjectRef(broker, this->Value());
232 }
233};
234
235using HeapObjectMatcher = HeapObjectMatcherImpl<IrOpcode::kHeapConstant>;
236using CompressedHeapObjectMatcher =
237 HeapObjectMatcherImpl<IrOpcode::kCompressedHeapConstant>;
238
239// A pattern matcher for external reference constants.
240struct ExternalReferenceMatcher final
241 : public ValueMatcher<ExternalReference, IrOpcode::kExternalConstant> {
242 explicit ExternalReferenceMatcher(Node* node)
243 : ValueMatcher<ExternalReference, IrOpcode::kExternalConstant>(node) {}
244 bool Is(const ExternalReference& value) const {
245 return this->HasValue() && this->Value() == value;
246 }
247};
248
249
250// For shorter pattern matching code, this struct matches the inputs to
251// machine-level load operations.
252template <typename Object>
253struct LoadMatcher : public NodeMatcher {
254 explicit LoadMatcher(Node* node)
255 : NodeMatcher(node), object_(InputAt(0)), index_(InputAt(1)) {}
256
257 using ObjectMatcher = Object;
258
259 Object const& object() const { return object_; }
260 IntPtrMatcher const& index() const { return index_; }
261
262 private:
263 Object const object_;
264 IntPtrMatcher const index_;
265};
266
267
268// For shorter pattern matching code, this struct matches both the left and
269// right hand sides of a binary operation and can put constants on the right
270// if they appear on the left hand side of a commutative operation.
271template <typename Left, typename Right>
272struct BinopMatcher : public NodeMatcher {
273 explicit BinopMatcher(Node* node)
274 : NodeMatcher(node), left_(InputAt(0)), right_(InputAt(1)) {
275 if (HasProperty(Operator::kCommutative)) PutConstantOnRight();
276 }
277 BinopMatcher(Node* node, bool allow_input_swap)
278 : NodeMatcher(node), left_(InputAt(0)), right_(InputAt(1)) {
279 if (allow_input_swap) PutConstantOnRight();
280 }
281
282 using LeftMatcher = Left;
283 using RightMatcher = Right;
284
285 const Left& left() const { return left_; }
286 const Right& right() const { return right_; }
287
288 bool IsFoldable() const { return left().HasValue() && right().HasValue(); }
289 bool LeftEqualsRight() const { return left().node() == right().node(); }
290
291 bool OwnsInput(Node* input) {
292 for (Node* use : input->uses()) {
293 if (use != node()) {
294 return false;
295 }
296 }
297 return true;
298 }
299
300 protected:
301 void SwapInputs() {
302 std::swap(left_, right_);
303 // TODO(tebbi): This modification should notify the reducers using
304 // BinopMatcher. Alternatively, all reducers (especially value numbering)
305 // could ignore the ordering for commutative binops.
306 node()->ReplaceInput(0, left().node());
307 node()->ReplaceInput(1, right().node());
308 }
309
310 private:
311 void PutConstantOnRight() {
312 if (left().HasValue() && !right().HasValue()) {
313 SwapInputs();
314 }
315 }
316
317 Left left_;
318 Right right_;
319};
320
321using Int32BinopMatcher = BinopMatcher<Int32Matcher, Int32Matcher>;
322using Uint32BinopMatcher = BinopMatcher<Uint32Matcher, Uint32Matcher>;
323using Int64BinopMatcher = BinopMatcher<Int64Matcher, Int64Matcher>;
324using Uint64BinopMatcher = BinopMatcher<Uint64Matcher, Uint64Matcher>;
325using IntPtrBinopMatcher = BinopMatcher<IntPtrMatcher, IntPtrMatcher>;
326using UintPtrBinopMatcher = BinopMatcher<UintPtrMatcher, UintPtrMatcher>;
327using Float32BinopMatcher = BinopMatcher<Float32Matcher, Float32Matcher>;
328using Float64BinopMatcher = BinopMatcher<Float64Matcher, Float64Matcher>;
329using NumberBinopMatcher = BinopMatcher<NumberMatcher, NumberMatcher>;
330using HeapObjectBinopMatcher =
331 BinopMatcher<HeapObjectMatcher, HeapObjectMatcher>;
332using CompressedHeapObjectBinopMatcher =
333 BinopMatcher<CompressedHeapObjectMatcher, CompressedHeapObjectMatcher>;
334
335template <class BinopMatcher, IrOpcode::Value kMulOpcode,
336 IrOpcode::Value kShiftOpcode>
337struct ScaleMatcher {
338 explicit ScaleMatcher(Node* node, bool allow_power_of_two_plus_one = false)
339 : scale_(-1), power_of_two_plus_one_(false) {
340 if (node->InputCount() < 2) return;
341 BinopMatcher m(node);
342 if (node->opcode() == kShiftOpcode) {
343 if (m.right().HasValue()) {
344 typename BinopMatcher::RightMatcher::ValueType value =
345 m.right().Value();
346 if (value >= 0 && value <= 3) {
347 scale_ = static_cast<int>(value);
348 }
349 }
350 } else if (node->opcode() == kMulOpcode) {
351 if (m.right().HasValue()) {
352 typename BinopMatcher::RightMatcher::ValueType value =
353 m.right().Value();
354 if (value == 1) {
355 scale_ = 0;
356 } else if (value == 2) {
357 scale_ = 1;
358 } else if (value == 4) {
359 scale_ = 2;
360 } else if (value == 8) {
361 scale_ = 3;
362 } else if (allow_power_of_two_plus_one) {
363 if (value == 3) {
364 scale_ = 1;
365 power_of_two_plus_one_ = true;
366 } else if (value == 5) {
367 scale_ = 2;
368 power_of_two_plus_one_ = true;
369 } else if (value == 9) {
370 scale_ = 3;
371 power_of_two_plus_one_ = true;
372 }
373 }
374 }
375 }
376 }
377
378 bool matches() const { return scale_ != -1; }
379 int scale() const { return scale_; }
380 bool power_of_two_plus_one() const { return power_of_two_plus_one_; }
381
382 private:
383 int scale_;
384 bool power_of_two_plus_one_;
385};
386
387using Int32ScaleMatcher =
388 ScaleMatcher<Int32BinopMatcher, IrOpcode::kInt32Mul, IrOpcode::kWord32Shl>;
389using Int64ScaleMatcher =
390 ScaleMatcher<Int64BinopMatcher, IrOpcode::kInt64Mul, IrOpcode::kWord64Shl>;
391
392template <class BinopMatcher, IrOpcode::Value AddOpcode,
393 IrOpcode::Value SubOpcode, IrOpcode::Value kMulOpcode,
394 IrOpcode::Value kShiftOpcode>
395struct AddMatcher : public BinopMatcher {
396 static const IrOpcode::Value kAddOpcode = AddOpcode;
397 static const IrOpcode::Value kSubOpcode = SubOpcode;
398 using Matcher = ScaleMatcher<BinopMatcher, kMulOpcode, kShiftOpcode>;
399
400 AddMatcher(Node* node, bool allow_input_swap)
401 : BinopMatcher(node, allow_input_swap),
402 scale_(-1),
403 power_of_two_plus_one_(false) {
404 Initialize(node, allow_input_swap);
405 }
406 explicit AddMatcher(Node* node)
407 : BinopMatcher(node, node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kCommutative)),
408 scale_(-1),
409 power_of_two_plus_one_(false) {
410 Initialize(node, node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kCommutative));
411 }
412
413 bool HasIndexInput() const { return scale_ != -1; }
414 Node* IndexInput() const {
415 DCHECK(HasIndexInput())((void) 0);
416 return this->left().node()->InputAt(0);
417 }
418 int scale() const {
419 DCHECK(HasIndexInput())((void) 0);
420 return scale_;
421 }
422 bool power_of_two_plus_one() const { return power_of_two_plus_one_; }
423
424 private:
425 void Initialize(Node* node, bool allow_input_swap) {
426 Matcher left_matcher(this->left().node(), true);
427 if (left_matcher.matches()) {
428 scale_ = left_matcher.scale();
429 power_of_two_plus_one_ = left_matcher.power_of_two_plus_one();
430 return;
431 }
432
433 if (!allow_input_swap) {
434 return;
435 }
436
437 Matcher right_matcher(this->right().node(), true);
438 if (right_matcher.matches()) {
439 scale_ = right_matcher.scale();
440 power_of_two_plus_one_ = right_matcher.power_of_two_plus_one();
441 this->SwapInputs();
442 return;
443 }
444
445 if ((this->left().opcode() != kSubOpcode &&
446 this->left().opcode() != kAddOpcode) &&
447 (this->right().opcode() == kAddOpcode ||
448 this->right().opcode() == kSubOpcode)) {
449 this->SwapInputs();
450 }
451 }
452
453 int scale_;
454 bool power_of_two_plus_one_;
455};
456
457using Int32AddMatcher =
458 AddMatcher<Int32BinopMatcher, IrOpcode::kInt32Add, IrOpcode::kInt32Sub,
459 IrOpcode::kInt32Mul, IrOpcode::kWord32Shl>;
460using Int64AddMatcher =
461 AddMatcher<Int64BinopMatcher, IrOpcode::kInt64Add, IrOpcode::kInt64Sub,
462 IrOpcode::kInt64Mul, IrOpcode::kWord64Shl>;
463
464enum DisplacementMode { kPositiveDisplacement, kNegativeDisplacement };
465
466enum class AddressOption : uint8_t {
467 kAllowNone = 0u,
468 kAllowInputSwap = 1u << 0,
469 kAllowScale = 1u << 1,
470 kAllowAll = kAllowInputSwap | kAllowScale
471};
472
473using AddressOptions = base::Flags<AddressOption, uint8_t>;
474DEFINE_OPERATORS_FOR_FLAGS(AddressOptions)__attribute__((unused)) __attribute__((warn_unused_result)) inline
constexpr AddressOptions operator&( AddressOptions::flag_type
lhs, AddressOptions::flag_type rhs) { return AddressOptions(
lhs) & rhs; } __attribute__((unused)) __attribute__((warn_unused_result
)) inline constexpr AddressOptions operator&( AddressOptions
::flag_type lhs, const AddressOptions& rhs) { return rhs &
lhs; } __attribute__((unused)) inline void operator&(AddressOptions
::flag_type lhs, AddressOptions::mask_type rhs) {} __attribute__
((unused)) __attribute__((warn_unused_result)) inline constexpr
AddressOptions operator|( AddressOptions::flag_type lhs, AddressOptions
::flag_type rhs) { return AddressOptions(lhs) | rhs; } __attribute__
((unused)) __attribute__((warn_unused_result)) inline constexpr
AddressOptions operator|( AddressOptions::flag_type lhs, const
AddressOptions& rhs) { return rhs | lhs; } __attribute__
((unused)) inline void operator|(AddressOptions::flag_type lhs
, AddressOptions::mask_type rhs) {} __attribute__((unused)) __attribute__
((warn_unused_result)) inline constexpr AddressOptions operator
^( AddressOptions::flag_type lhs, AddressOptions::flag_type rhs
) { return AddressOptions(lhs) ^ rhs; } __attribute__((unused
)) __attribute__((warn_unused_result)) inline constexpr AddressOptions
operator^( AddressOptions::flag_type lhs, const AddressOptions
& rhs) { return rhs ^ lhs; } __attribute__((unused)) inline
void operator^(AddressOptions::flag_type lhs, AddressOptions
::mask_type rhs) {} __attribute__((unused)) inline constexpr AddressOptions
operator~(AddressOptions::flag_type val) { return ~AddressOptions
(val); }
475
476template <class AddMatcher>
477struct BaseWithIndexAndDisplacementMatcher {
478 BaseWithIndexAndDisplacementMatcher(Node* node, AddressOptions options)
479 : matches_(false),
480 index_(nullptr),
481 scale_(0),
482 base_(nullptr),
483 displacement_(nullptr),
484 displacement_mode_(kPositiveDisplacement) {
485 Initialize(node, options);
486 }
487
488 explicit BaseWithIndexAndDisplacementMatcher(Node* node)
489 : matches_(false),
490 index_(nullptr),
491 scale_(0),
492 base_(nullptr),
493 displacement_(nullptr),
494 displacement_mode_(kPositiveDisplacement) {
495 Initialize(node, AddressOption::kAllowScale |
496 (node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kCommutative)
497 ? AddressOption::kAllowInputSwap
498 : AddressOption::kAllowNone));
499 }
500
501 bool matches() const { return matches_; }
502 Node* index() const { return index_; }
503 int scale() const { return scale_; }
504 Node* base() const { return base_; }
505 Node* displacement() const { return displacement_; }
506 DisplacementMode displacement_mode() const { return displacement_mode_; }
507
508 private:
509 bool matches_;
510 Node* index_;
511 int scale_;
512 Node* base_;
513 Node* displacement_;
514 DisplacementMode displacement_mode_;
515
516 void Initialize(Node* node, AddressOptions options) {
517 // The BaseWithIndexAndDisplacementMatcher canonicalizes the order of
518 // displacements and scale factors that are used as inputs, so instead of
519 // enumerating all possible patterns by brute force, checking for node
520 // clusters using the following templates in the following order suffices to
521 // find all of the interesting cases (S = index * scale, B = base input, D =
522 // displacement input):
523 // (S + (B + D))
524 // (S + (B + B))
525 // (S + D)
526 // (S + B)
527 // ((S + D) + B)
528 // ((S + B) + D)
529 // ((B + D) + B)
530 // ((B + B) + D)
531 // (B + D)
532 // (B + B)
533 if (node->InputCount() < 2) return;
534 AddMatcher m(node, options & AddressOption::kAllowInputSwap);
535 Node* left = m.left().node();
536 Node* right = m.right().node();
537 Node* displacement = nullptr;
538 Node* base = nullptr;
539 Node* index = nullptr;
540 Node* scale_expression = nullptr;
541 bool power_of_two_plus_one = false;
542 DisplacementMode displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
543 int scale = 0;
544 if (m.HasIndexInput() && OwnedByAddressingOperand(left)) {
545 index = m.IndexInput();
546 scale = m.scale();
547 scale_expression = left;
548 power_of_two_plus_one = m.power_of_two_plus_one();
549 bool match_found = false;
550 if (right->opcode() == AddMatcher::kSubOpcode &&
551 OwnedByAddressingOperand(right)) {
552 AddMatcher right_matcher(right);
553 if (right_matcher.right().HasValue()) {
554 // (S + (B - D))
555 base = right_matcher.left().node();
556 displacement = right_matcher.right().node();
557 displacement_mode = kNegativeDisplacement;
558 match_found = true;
559 }
560 }
561 if (!match_found) {
562 if (right->opcode() == AddMatcher::kAddOpcode &&
563 OwnedByAddressingOperand(right)) {
564 AddMatcher right_matcher(right);
565 if (right_matcher.right().HasValue()) {
566 // (S + (B + D))
567 base = right_matcher.left().node();
568 displacement = right_matcher.right().node();
569 } else {
570 // (S + (B + B))
571 base = right;
572 }
573 } else if (m.right().HasValue()) {
574 // (S + D)
575 displacement = right;
576 } else {
577 // (S + B)
578 base = right;
579 }
580 }
581 } else {
582 bool match_found = false;
583 if (left->opcode() == AddMatcher::kSubOpcode &&
584 OwnedByAddressingOperand(left)) {
585 AddMatcher left_matcher(left);
586 Node* left_left = left_matcher.left().node();
587 Node* left_right = left_matcher.right().node();
588 if (left_matcher.right().HasValue()) {
589 if (left_matcher.HasIndexInput() && left_left->OwnedBy(left)) {
590 // ((S - D) + B)
591 index = left_matcher.IndexInput();
592 scale = left_matcher.scale();
593 scale_expression = left_left;
594 power_of_two_plus_one = left_matcher.power_of_two_plus_one();
595 displacement = left_right;
596 displacement_mode = kNegativeDisplacement;
597 base = right;
598 } else {
599 // ((B - D) + B)
600 index = left_left;
601 displacement = left_right;
602 displacement_mode = kNegativeDisplacement;
603 base = right;
604 }
605 match_found = true;
606 }
607 }
608 if (!match_found) {
609 if (left->opcode() == AddMatcher::kAddOpcode &&
610 OwnedByAddressingOperand(left)) {
611 AddMatcher left_matcher(left);
612 Node* left_left = left_matcher.left().node();
613 Node* left_right = left_matcher.right().node();
614 if (left_matcher.HasIndexInput() && left_left->OwnedBy(left)) {
615 if (left_matcher.right().HasValue()) {
616 // ((S + D) + B)
617 index = left_matcher.IndexInput();
618 scale = left_matcher.scale();
619 scale_expression = left_left;
620 power_of_two_plus_one = left_matcher.power_of_two_plus_one();
621 displacement = left_right;
622 base = right;
623 } else if (m.right().HasValue()) {
624 if (left->OwnedBy(node)) {
625 // ((S + B) + D)
626 index = left_matcher.IndexInput();
627 scale = left_matcher.scale();
628 scale_expression = left_left;
629 power_of_two_plus_one = left_matcher.power_of_two_plus_one();
630 base = left_right;
631 displacement = right;
632 } else {
633 // (B + D)
634 base = left;
635 displacement = right;
636 }
637 } else {
638 // (B + B)
639 index = left;
640 base = right;
641 }
642 } else {
643 if (left_matcher.right().HasValue()) {
644 // ((B + D) + B)
645 index = left_left;
646 displacement = left_right;
647 base = right;
648 } else if (m.right().HasValue()) {
649 if (left->OwnedBy(node)) {
650 // ((B + B) + D)
651 index = left_left;
652 base = left_right;
653 displacement = right;
654 } else {
655 // (B + D)
656 base = left;
657 displacement = right;
658 }
659 } else {
660 // (B + B)
661 index = left;
662 base = right;
663 }
664 }
665 } else {
666 if (m.right().HasValue()) {
667 // (B + D)
668 base = left;
669 displacement = right;
670 } else {
671 // (B + B)
672 base = left;
673 index = right;
674 }
675 }
676 }
677 }
678 int64_t value = 0;
679 if (displacement != nullptr) {
680 switch (displacement->opcode()) {
681 case IrOpcode::kInt32Constant: {
682 value = OpParameter<int32_t>(displacement->op());
683 break;
684 }
685 case IrOpcode::kInt64Constant: {
686 value = OpParameter<int64_t>(displacement->op());
687 break;
688 }
689 default:
690 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
691 break;
692 }
693 if (value == 0) {
694 displacement = nullptr;
695 }
696 }
697 if (power_of_two_plus_one) {
698 if (base != nullptr) {
699 // If the scale requires explicitly using the index as the base, but a
700 // base is already part of the match, then the (1 << N + 1) scale factor
701 // can't be folded into the match and the entire index * scale
702 // calculation must be computed separately.
703 index = scale_expression;
704 scale = 0;
705 } else {
706 base = index;
707 }
708 }
709 if (!(options & AddressOption::kAllowScale) && scale != 0) {
710 index = scale_expression;
711 scale = 0;
712 }
713 base_ = base;
714 displacement_ = displacement;
715 displacement_mode_ = displacement_mode;
716 index_ = index;
717 scale_ = scale;
718 matches_ = true;
719 }
720
721 static bool OwnedByAddressingOperand(Node* node) {
722 for (auto use : node->use_edges()) {
723 Node* from = use.from();
724 switch (from->opcode()) {
725 case IrOpcode::kLoad:
726 case IrOpcode::kPoisonedLoad:
727 case IrOpcode::kProtectedLoad:
728 case IrOpcode::kInt32Add:
729 case IrOpcode::kInt64Add:
730 // Skip addressing uses.
731 break;
732 case IrOpcode::kStore:
733 case IrOpcode::kProtectedStore:
734 // If the stored value is this node, it is not an addressing use.
735 if (from->InputAt(2) == node) return false;
736 // Otherwise it is used as an address and skipped.
737 break;
738 default:
739 // Non-addressing use found.
740 return false;
741 }
742 }
743 return true;
744 }
745};
746
747using BaseWithIndexAndDisplacement32Matcher =
748 BaseWithIndexAndDisplacementMatcher<Int32AddMatcher>;
749using BaseWithIndexAndDisplacement64Matcher =
750 BaseWithIndexAndDisplacementMatcher<Int64AddMatcher>;
751
752struct V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE BranchMatcher : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(NodeMatcher)NodeMatcher {
753 explicit BranchMatcher(Node* branch);
754
755 bool Matched() const { return if_true_ && if_false_; }
756
757 Node* Branch() const { return node(); }
758 Node* IfTrue() const { return if_true_; }
759 Node* IfFalse() const { return if_false_; }
760
761 private:
762 Node* if_true_;
763 Node* if_false_;
764};
765
766struct V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE DiamondMatcher
767 : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(NodeMatcher)NodeMatcher {
768 explicit DiamondMatcher(Node* merge);
769
770 bool Matched() const { return branch_; }
771 bool IfProjectionsAreOwned() const {
772 return if_true_->OwnedBy(node()) && if_false_->OwnedBy(node());
773 }
774
775 Node* Branch() const { return branch_; }
776 Node* IfTrue() const { return if_true_; }
777 Node* IfFalse() const { return if_false_; }
778 Node* Merge() const { return node(); }
779
780 Node* TrueInputOf(Node* phi) const {
781 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsPhiOpcode(phi->opcode()))((void) 0);
782 DCHECK_EQ(3, phi->InputCount())((void) 0);
783 DCHECK_EQ(Merge(), phi->InputAt(2))((void) 0);
784 return phi->InputAt(if_true_ == Merge()->InputAt(0) ? 0 : 1);
785 }
786
787 Node* FalseInputOf(Node* phi) const {
788 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsPhiOpcode(phi->opcode()))((void) 0);
789 DCHECK_EQ(3, phi->InputCount())((void) 0);
790 DCHECK_EQ(Merge(), phi->InputAt(2))((void) 0);
791 return phi->InputAt(if_true_ == Merge()->InputAt(0) ? 1 : 0);
792 }
793
794 private:
795 Node* branch_;
796 Node* if_true_;
797 Node* if_false_;
798};

66#define FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode) \
67 FATAL("Unsupported opcode 0x%x:%s", (opcode), \V8_Fatal("Unsupported opcode 0x%x:%s", (opcode), wasm::WasmOpcodes
::OpcodeName(opcode))

70MachineType assert_size(int expected_size, MachineType type) {
71 DCHECK_EQ(expected_size, ElementSizeInBytes(type.representation()))((void) 0);
72 return type;
73}
74
75#define WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_SIZE(name) \
76 (WasmInstanceObject::k##name##OffsetEnd - \
77 WasmInstanceObject::k##name##Offset + 1) // NOLINT(whitespace/indent)
78
79#define WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_OFFSET(name) \
80 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmInstanceObject::k##name##Offset)
81
82// We would like to use gasm_->Call() to implement this macro,
83// but this doesn't work currently when we try to call it from functions
84// which set IfSuccess/IfFailure control paths (e.g. within Throw()).
85// TODO(manoskouk): Maybe clean this up at some point?
86#define CALL_BUILTIN(name, ...) \
87 SetEffect(graph()->NewNode( \
88 mcgraph()->common()->Call(GetBuiltinCallDescriptor<name##Descriptor>( \
89 this, StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer)), \
90 GetBuiltinPointerTarget(Builtins::k##name), ##__VA_ARGS__, effect(), \
91 control()))
92
93#define LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(name, type) \
94 gasm_->Load(assert_size(WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_SIZE(name), type), \
95 instance_node_.get(), WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_OFFSET(name))
96
97#define LOAD_FULL_POINTER(base_pointer, byte_offset)gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), base_pointer, byte_offset
) \
98 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), base_pointer, byte_offset)
99
100#define LOAD_TAGGED_POINTER(base_pointer, byte_offset) \
101 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), base_pointer, byte_offset)
102
103#define LOAD_TAGGED_ANY(base_pointer, byte_offset) \
104 gasm_->Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), base_pointer, byte_offset)
105
106#define LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT(array_node, index, type) \
107 gasm_->Load(type, array_node, \
108 wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(index))
109
110#define LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_SMI(array_node, index) \
111 LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT(array_node, index, MachineType::TaggedSigned())
112
113#define LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_PTR(array_node, index) \
114 LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT(array_node, index, MachineType::TaggedPointer())
115
116#define LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(array_node, index) \
117 LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT(array_node, index, MachineType::AnyTagged())
118
119#define STORE_RAW(base, offset, val, rep, barrier) \
120 STORE_RAW_NODE_OFFSET(base, gasm_->Int32Constant(offset), val, rep, barrier)
121
122#define STORE_RAW_NODE_OFFSET(base, node_offset, val, rep, barrier) \
123 gasm_->Store(StoreRepresentation(rep, barrier), base, node_offset, val)
124
125// This can be used to store tagged Smi values only.
126#define STORE_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_SMI(array_node, index, value) \
127 STORE_RAW(array_node, \
128 wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(index), value, \
129 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned, kNoWriteBarrier)
130
131// This can be used to store any tagged (Smi and HeapObject) value.
132#define STORE_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(array_node, index, value) \
133 STORE_RAW(array_node, \
134 wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(index), value, \
135 MachineRepresentation::kTagged, kFullWriteBarrier)
136
137void MergeControlToEnd(MachineGraph* mcgraph, Node* node) {
138 Graph* g = mcgraph->graph();
139 if (g->end()) {
140 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(g, mcgraph->common(), node);
141 } else {
142 g->SetEnd(g->NewNode(mcgraph->common()->End(1), node));
143 }
144}
145
146bool ContainsSimd(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig) {
147 for (auto type : sig->all()) {
148 if (type == wasm::kWasmS128) return true;
149 }
150 return false;
151}
152
153bool ContainsInt64(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig) {
154 for (auto type : sig->all()) {
155 if (type == wasm::kWasmI64) return true;
156 }
157 return false;
158}
159
160template <typename BuiltinDescriptor>
161CallDescriptor* GetBuiltinCallDescriptor(WasmGraphBuilder* builder,
162 StubCallMode stub_mode) {
163 BuiltinDescriptor interface_descriptor;
164 return Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
165 builder->mcgraph()->zone(), // zone
166 interface_descriptor, // descriptor
167 interface_descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(), // stack parameter count
168 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, // flags
169 Operator::kNoProperties, // properties
170 stub_mode); // stub call mode
171}
172} // namespace

174class WasmGraphAssembler : public GraphAssembler {
175 public:
176 WasmGraphAssembler(MachineGraph* mcgraph, Zone* zone)
177 : GraphAssembler(mcgraph, zone) {}
178};
179
180WasmGraphBuilder::WasmGraphBuilder(
181 wasm::CompilationEnv* env, Zone* zone, MachineGraph* mcgraph,
182 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
183 compiler::SourcePositionTable* source_position_table)
184 : gasm_(std::make_unique<WasmGraphAssembler>(mcgraph, zone)),
185 zone_(zone),
186 mcgraph_(mcgraph),
187 env_(env),
188 has_simd_(ContainsSimd(sig)),
189 untrusted_code_mitigations_(FLAG_untrusted_code_mitigations),
190 sig_(sig),
191 source_position_table_(source_position_table) {
192 DCHECK_IMPLIES(use_trap_handler(), trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled())((void) 0);
193 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mcgraph_)((void) 0);
194}
195
196// Destructor define here where the definition of {WasmGraphAssembler} is
197// available.
198WasmGraphBuilder::~WasmGraphBuilder() = default;
199
200Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Error() { return mcgraph()->Dead(); }
201
202Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Start(unsigned params) {
203 Node* start = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Start(params));
204 graph()->SetStart(start);
205 return start;
206}
207
208Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Param(unsigned index) {
209 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Parameter(index),
210 graph()->start());
211}
212
213Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Loop(Node* entry) {
214 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Loop(1), entry);
215}
216
217Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TerminateLoop(Node* effect, Node* control) {
218 Node* terminate =
219 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Terminate(), effect, control);
220 MergeControlToEnd(mcgraph(), terminate);
221 return terminate;
222}
223
224Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TerminateThrow(Node* effect, Node* control) {
225 Node* terminate =
226 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Throw(), effect, control);
227 MergeControlToEnd(mcgraph(), terminate);
228 return terminate;
229}
230
231bool WasmGraphBuilder::IsPhiWithMerge(Node* phi, Node* merge) {
232 return phi && IrOpcode::IsPhiOpcode(phi->opcode()) &&
233 NodeProperties::GetControlInput(phi) == merge;
234}
235
236bool WasmGraphBuilder::ThrowsException(Node* node, Node** if_success,
237 Node** if_exception) {
238 if (node->op()->HasProperty(compiler::Operator::kNoThrow)) {
239 return false;
240 }
241
242 *if_success = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfSuccess(), node);
243 *if_exception =
244 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfException(), node, node);
245
246 return true;
247}
248
249void WasmGraphBuilder::AppendToMerge(Node* merge, Node* from) {
250 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsMergeOpcode(merge->opcode()))((void) 0);
251 merge->AppendInput(mcgraph()->zone(), from);
252 int new_size = merge->InputCount();
253 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
254 merge, mcgraph()->common()->ResizeMergeOrPhi(merge->op(), new_size));
255}
256
257void WasmGraphBuilder::AppendToPhi(Node* phi, Node* from) {
258 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsPhiOpcode(phi->opcode()))((void) 0);
259 int new_size = phi->InputCount();
260 phi->InsertInput(mcgraph()->zone(), phi->InputCount() - 1, from);
261 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
262 phi, mcgraph()->common()->ResizeMergeOrPhi(phi->op(), new_size));
263}
264
265Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Merge(unsigned count, Node** controls) {
266 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Merge(count), count, controls);
267}
268
269Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Phi(wasm::ValueType type, unsigned count,
270 Node** vals_and_control) {
271 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsMergeOpcode(vals_and_control[count]->opcode()))((void) 0);
272 return graph()->NewNode(
273 mcgraph()->common()->Phi(type.machine_representation(), count), count + 1,
274 vals_and_control);
275}
276
277Node* WasmGraphBuilder::EffectPhi(unsigned count, Node** effects_and_control) {
278 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsMergeOpcode(effects_and_control[count]->opcode()))((void) 0);
279 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
280 effects_and_control);
281}

283Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RefNull() {
284 return LOAD_FULL_POINTER(gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kNullValue))
285 BuildLoadIsolateRoot(),gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kNullValue))
286 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kNullValue))gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kNullValue));
287}
288
289Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RefFunc(uint32_t function_index) {
290 auto call_descriptor = GetBuiltinCallDescriptor<WasmRefFuncDescriptor>(
291 this, StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
292 // A direct call to a wasm runtime stub defined in this module.
293 // Just encode the stub index. This will be patched at relocation.
294 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
295 wasm::WasmCode::kWasmRefFunc, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
296
297 return SetEffectControl(
298 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), call_target,
299 Uint32Constant(function_index), effect(), control()));
300}
301
302Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RefAsNonNull(Node* arg,
303 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
304 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapIllegalCast, gasm_->WordEqual(arg, RefNull()),
305 position);
306 return arg;
307}
308
309Node* WasmGraphBuilder::NoContextConstant() {
310 return mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(0);
311}
312
313Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildLoadIsolateRoot() {
314 // The IsolateRoot is loaded from the instance node so that the generated
315 // code is Isolate independent. This can be overridden by setting a specific
316 // node in {isolate_root_node_} beforehand.
317 if (isolate_root_node_.is_set()) return isolate_root_node_.get();
318 return LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(IsolateRoot, MachineType::Pointer());
319}

321Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Uint32Constant(uint32_t value) {
322 return mcgraph()->Uint32Constant(value);
323}

325Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Int32Constant(int32_t value) {
326 return mcgraph()->Int32Constant(value);
327}

329Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Int64Constant(int64_t value) {
330 return mcgraph()->Int64Constant(value);
331}

333Node* WasmGraphBuilder::IntPtrConstant(intptr_t value) {
334 return mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(value);
335}
336
337void WasmGraphBuilder::StackCheck(wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
338 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(env_)((void) 0); // Wrappers don't get stack checks.
339 if (!FLAG_wasm_stack_checks || !env_->runtime_exception_support) {
340 return;
341 }
342
343 Node* limit_address = graph()->NewNode(
344 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::Pointer()), instance_node_.get(),
345 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_OFFSET(StackLimitAddress)),
346 effect(), control());
347 Node* limit = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
348 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::Pointer()), limit_address,
349 mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(0), limit_address, control()));
350
351 Node* check = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
352 mcgraph()->machine()->StackPointerGreaterThan(StackCheckKind::kWasm),
353 limit, effect()));
354
355 Diamond stack_check(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), check, BranchHint::kTrue);
356 stack_check.Chain(control());
357
358 if (stack_check_call_operator_ == nullptr) {
359 // Build and cache the stack check call operator and the constant
360 // representing the stack check code.
361 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
362 mcgraph()->zone(), // zone
363 NoContextDescriptor{}, // descriptor
364 0, // stack parameter count
365 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, // flags
366 Operator::kNoProperties, // properties
367 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub); // stub call mode
368 // A direct call to a wasm runtime stub defined in this module.
369 // Just encode the stub index. This will be patched at relocation.
370 stack_check_code_node_.set(mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
371 wasm::WasmCode::kWasmStackGuard, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL));
372 stack_check_call_operator_ = mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor);
373 }
374
375 Node* call = graph()->NewNode(stack_check_call_operator_.get(),
376 stack_check_code_node_.get(), effect(),
377 stack_check.if_false);
378
379 SetSourcePosition(call, position);
380
381 Node* ephi = stack_check.EffectPhi(effect(), call);
382
383 SetEffectControl(ephi, stack_check.merge);
384}
385
386void WasmGraphBuilder::PatchInStackCheckIfNeeded() {
387 if (!needs_stack_check_) return;
388
389 Node* start = graph()->start();
390 // Place a stack check which uses a dummy node as control and effect.
391 Node* dummy = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Dead());
392 SetEffectControl(dummy);
393 // The function-prologue stack check is associated with position 0, which
394 // is never a position of any instruction in the function.
395 StackCheck(0);
396
397 // In testing, no steck checks were emitted. Nothing to rewire then.
398 if (effect() == dummy) return;
399
400 // Now patch all control uses of {start} to use {control} and all effect uses
401 // to use {effect} instead. Then rewire the dummy node to use start instead.
402 NodeProperties::ReplaceUses(start, start, effect(), control());
403 NodeProperties::ReplaceUses(dummy, nullptr, start, start);
404}
405
406Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Binop(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode, Node* left, Node* right,
407 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
408 const Operator* op;
409 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
410 switch (opcode) {
411 case wasm::kExprI32Add:
412 op = m->Int32Add();
413 break;
414 case wasm::kExprI32Sub:
415 op = m->Int32Sub();
416 break;
417 case wasm::kExprI32Mul:
418 op = m->Int32Mul();
419 break;
420 case wasm::kExprI32DivS:
421 return BuildI32DivS(left, right, position);
422 case wasm::kExprI32DivU:
423 return BuildI32DivU(left, right, position);
424 case wasm::kExprI32RemS:
425 return BuildI32RemS(left, right, position);
426 case wasm::kExprI32RemU:
427 return BuildI32RemU(left, right, position);
428 case wasm::kExprI32And:
429 op = m->Word32And();
430 break;
431 case wasm::kExprI32Ior:
432 op = m->Word32Or();
433 break;
434 case wasm::kExprI32Xor:
435 op = m->Word32Xor();
436 break;
437 case wasm::kExprI32Shl:
438 op = m->Word32Shl();
439 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
440 break;
441 case wasm::kExprI32ShrU:
442 op = m->Word32Shr();
443 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
444 break;
445 case wasm::kExprI32ShrS:
446 op = m->Word32Sar();
447 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
448 break;
449 case wasm::kExprI32Ror:
450 op = m->Word32Ror();
451 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
452 break;
453 case wasm::kExprI32Rol:
454 if (m->Word32Rol().IsSupported()) {
455 op = m->Word32Rol().op();
456 right = MaskShiftCount32(right);
457 break;
458 }
459 return BuildI32Rol(left, right);
460 case wasm::kExprI32Eq:
461 op = m->Word32Equal();
462 break;
463 case wasm::kExprI32Ne:
464 return Invert(Binop(wasm::kExprI32Eq, left, right));
465 case wasm::kExprI32LtS:
466 op = m->Int32LessThan();
467 break;
468 case wasm::kExprI32LeS:
469 op = m->Int32LessThanOrEqual();
470 break;
471 case wasm::kExprI32LtU:
472 op = m->Uint32LessThan();
473 break;
474 case wasm::kExprI32LeU:
475 op = m->Uint32LessThanOrEqual();
476 break;
477 case wasm::kExprI32GtS:
478 op = m->Int32LessThan();
479 std::swap(left, right);
480 break;
481 case wasm::kExprI32GeS:
482 op = m->Int32LessThanOrEqual();
483 std::swap(left, right);
484 break;
485 case wasm::kExprI32GtU:
486 op = m->Uint32LessThan();
487 std::swap(left, right);
488 break;
489 case wasm::kExprI32GeU:
490 op = m->Uint32LessThanOrEqual();
491 std::swap(left, right);
492 break;
493 case wasm::kExprI64And:
494 op = m->Word64And();
495 break;
496 case wasm::kExprI64Add:
497 op = m->Int64Add();
498 break;
499 case wasm::kExprI64Sub:
500 op = m->Int64Sub();
501 break;
502 case wasm::kExprI64Mul:
503 op = m->Int64Mul();
504 break;
505 case wasm::kExprI64DivS:
506 return BuildI64DivS(left, right, position);
507 case wasm::kExprI64DivU:
508 return BuildI64DivU(left, right, position);
509 case wasm::kExprI64RemS:
510 return BuildI64RemS(left, right, position);
511 case wasm::kExprI64RemU:
512 return BuildI64RemU(left, right, position);
513 case wasm::kExprI64Ior:
514 op = m->Word64Or();
515 break;
516 case wasm::kExprI64Xor:
517 op = m->Word64Xor();
518 break;
519 case wasm::kExprI64Shl:
520 op = m->Word64Shl();
521 right = MaskShiftCount64(right);
522 break;
523 case wasm::kExprI64ShrU:
524 op = m->Word64Shr();
525 right = MaskShiftCount64(right);
526 break;
527 case wasm::kExprI64ShrS:
528 op = m->Word64Sar();
529 right = MaskShiftCount64(right);
530 break;
531 case wasm::kExprI64Eq:
532 op = m->Word64Equal();
533 break;
534 case wasm::kExprI64Ne:
535 return Invert(Binop(wasm::kExprI64Eq, left, right));
536 case wasm::kExprI64LtS:
537 op = m->Int64LessThan();
538 break;
539 case wasm::kExprI64LeS:
540 op = m->Int64LessThanOrEqual();
541 break;
542 case wasm::kExprI64LtU:
543 op = m->Uint64LessThan();
544 break;
545 case wasm::kExprI64LeU:
546 op = m->Uint64LessThanOrEqual();
547 break;
548 case wasm::kExprI64GtS:
549 op = m->Int64LessThan();
550 std::swap(left, right);
551 break;
552 case wasm::kExprI64GeS:
553 op = m->Int64LessThanOrEqual();
554 std::swap(left, right);
555 break;
556 case wasm::kExprI64GtU:
557 op = m->Uint64LessThan();
558 std::swap(left, right);
559 break;
560 case wasm::kExprI64GeU:
561 op = m->Uint64LessThanOrEqual();
562 std::swap(left, right);
563 break;
564 case wasm::kExprI64Ror:
565 op = m->Word64Ror();
566 right = MaskShiftCount64(right);
567 break;
568 case wasm::kExprI64Rol:
569 if (m->Word64Rol().IsSupported()) {
570 op = m->Word64Rol().op();
571 right = MaskShiftCount64(right);
572 break;
573 } else if (m->Word32Rol().IsSupported()) {
574 op = m->Word64Rol().placeholder();
575 break;
576 }
577 return BuildI64Rol(left, right);
578 case wasm::kExprF32CopySign:
579 return BuildF32CopySign(left, right);
580 case wasm::kExprF64CopySign:
581 return BuildF64CopySign(left, right);
582 case wasm::kExprF32Add:
583 op = m->Float32Add();
584 break;
585 case wasm::kExprF32Sub:
586 op = m->Float32Sub();
587 break;
588 case wasm::kExprF32Mul:
589 op = m->Float32Mul();
590 break;
591 case wasm::kExprF32Div:
592 op = m->Float32Div();
593 break;
594 case wasm::kExprF32Eq:
595 op = m->Float32Equal();
596 break;
597 case wasm::kExprF32Ne:
598 return Invert(Binop(wasm::kExprF32Eq, left, right));
599 case wasm::kExprF32Lt:
600 op = m->Float32LessThan();
601 break;
602 case wasm::kExprF32Ge:
603 op = m->Float32LessThanOrEqual();
604 std::swap(left, right);
605 break;
606 case wasm::kExprF32Gt:
607 op = m->Float32LessThan();
608 std::swap(left, right);
609 break;
610 case wasm::kExprF32Le:
611 op = m->Float32LessThanOrEqual();
612 break;
613 case wasm::kExprF64Add:
614 op = m->Float64Add();
615 break;
616 case wasm::kExprF64Sub:
617 op = m->Float64Sub();
618 break;
619 case wasm::kExprF64Mul:
620 op = m->Float64Mul();
621 break;
622 case wasm::kExprF64Div:
623 op = m->Float64Div();
624 break;
625 case wasm::kExprF64Eq:
626 op = m->Float64Equal();
627 break;
628 case wasm::kExprF64Ne:
629 return Invert(Binop(wasm::kExprF64Eq, left, right));
630 case wasm::kExprF64Lt:
631 op = m->Float64LessThan();
632 break;
633 case wasm::kExprF64Le:
634 op = m->Float64LessThanOrEqual();
635 break;
636 case wasm::kExprF64Gt:
637 op = m->Float64LessThan();
638 std::swap(left, right);
639 break;
640 case wasm::kExprF64Ge:
641 op = m->Float64LessThanOrEqual();
642 std::swap(left, right);
643 break;
644 case wasm::kExprF32Min:
645 op = m->Float32Min();
646 break;
647 case wasm::kExprF64Min:
648 op = m->Float64Min();
649 break;
650 case wasm::kExprF32Max:
651 op = m->Float32Max();
652 break;
653 case wasm::kExprF64Max:
654 op = m->Float64Max();
655 break;
656 case wasm::kExprF64Pow:
657 return BuildF64Pow(left, right);
658 case wasm::kExprF64Atan2:
659 op = m->Float64Atan2();
660 break;
661 case wasm::kExprF64Mod:
662 return BuildF64Mod(left, right);
663 case wasm::kExprRefEq:
664 return gasm_->TaggedEqual(left, right);
665 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsDivS:
666 return BuildI32AsmjsDivS(left, right);
667 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsDivU:
668 return BuildI32AsmjsDivU(left, right);
669 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsRemS:
670 return BuildI32AsmjsRemS(left, right);
671 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsRemU:
672 return BuildI32AsmjsRemU(left, right);
673 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsStoreMem8:
674 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Int8(), left, right);
675 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsStoreMem16:
676 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Int16(), left, right);
677 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsStoreMem:
678 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Int32(), left, right);
679 case wasm::kExprF32AsmjsStoreMem:
680 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Float32(), left, right);
681 case wasm::kExprF64AsmjsStoreMem:
682 return BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType::Float64(), left, right);
683 default:
684 FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode);
685 }
686 return graph()->NewNode(op, left, right);
687}
688
689Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Unop(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode, Node* input,
690 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
691 const Operator* op;
692 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
693 switch (opcode) {
694 case wasm::kExprI32Eqz:
695 op = m->Word32Equal();
696 return graph()->NewNode(op, input, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0));
697 case wasm::kExprF32Abs:
698 op = m->Float32Abs();
699 break;
700 case wasm::kExprF32Neg: {
701 op = m->Float32Neg();
702 break;
703 }
704 case wasm::kExprF32Sqrt:
705 op = m->Float32Sqrt();
706 break;
707 case wasm::kExprF64Abs:
708 op = m->Float64Abs();
709 break;
710 case wasm::kExprF64Neg: {
711 op = m->Float64Neg();
712 break;
713 }
714 case wasm::kExprF64Sqrt:
715 op = m->Float64Sqrt();
716 break;
717 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF32:
718 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:
719 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF64:
720 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF64:
721 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
722 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
723 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
724 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
725 return BuildIntConvertFloat(input, position, opcode);
726 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsSConvertF64:
727 return BuildI32AsmjsSConvertF64(input);
728 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsUConvertF64:
729 return BuildI32AsmjsUConvertF64(input);
730 case wasm::kExprF32ConvertF64:
731 op = m->TruncateFloat64ToFloat32();
732 break;
733 case wasm::kExprF64SConvertI32:
734 op = m->ChangeInt32ToFloat64();
735 break;
736 case wasm::kExprF64UConvertI32:
737 op = m->ChangeUint32ToFloat64();
738 break;
739 case wasm::kExprF32SConvertI32:
740 op = m->RoundInt32ToFloat32();
741 break;
742 case wasm::kExprF32UConvertI32:
743 op = m->RoundUint32ToFloat32();
744 break;
745 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsSConvertF32:
746 return BuildI32AsmjsSConvertF32(input);
747 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsUConvertF32:
748 return BuildI32AsmjsUConvertF32(input);
749 case wasm::kExprF64ConvertF32:
750 op = m->ChangeFloat32ToFloat64();
751 break;
752 case wasm::kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
753 op = m->BitcastInt32ToFloat32();
754 break;
755 case wasm::kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
756 op = m->BitcastFloat32ToInt32();
757 break;
758 case wasm::kExprI32Clz:
759 op = m->Word32Clz();
760 break;
761 case wasm::kExprI32Ctz: {
762 if (m->Word32Ctz().IsSupported()) {
763 op = m->Word32Ctz().op();
764 break;
765 } else if (m->Word32ReverseBits().IsSupported()) {
766 Node* reversed = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32ReverseBits().op(), input);
767 Node* result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Clz(), reversed);
768 return result;
769 } else {
770 return BuildI32Ctz(input);
771 }
772 }
773 case wasm::kExprI32Popcnt: {
774 if (m->Word32Popcnt().IsSupported()) {
775 op = m->Word32Popcnt().op();
776 break;
777 } else {
778 return BuildI32Popcnt(input);
779 }
780 }
781 case wasm::kExprF32Floor: {
782 if (!m->Float32RoundDown().IsSupported()) return BuildF32Floor(input);
783 op = m->Float32RoundDown().op();
784 break;
785 }
786 case wasm::kExprF32Ceil: {
787 if (!m->Float32RoundUp().IsSupported()) return BuildF32Ceil(input);
788 op = m->Float32RoundUp().op();
789 break;
790 }
791 case wasm::kExprF32Trunc: {
792 if (!m->Float32RoundTruncate().IsSupported()) return BuildF32Trunc(input);
793 op = m->Float32RoundTruncate().op();
794 break;
795 }
796 case wasm::kExprF32NearestInt: {
797 if (!m->Float32RoundTiesEven().IsSupported())
798 return BuildF32NearestInt(input);
799 op = m->Float32RoundTiesEven().op();
800 break;
801 }
802 case wasm::kExprF64Floor: {
803 if (!m->Float64RoundDown().IsSupported()) return BuildF64Floor(input);
804 op = m->Float64RoundDown().op();
805 break;
806 }
807 case wasm::kExprF64Ceil: {
808 if (!m->Float64RoundUp().IsSupported()) return BuildF64Ceil(input);
809 op = m->Float64RoundUp().op();
810 break;
811 }
812 case wasm::kExprF64Trunc: {
813 if (!m->Float64RoundTruncate().IsSupported()) return BuildF64Trunc(input);
814 op = m->Float64RoundTruncate().op();
815 break;
816 }
817 case wasm::kExprF64NearestInt: {
818 if (!m->Float64RoundTiesEven().IsSupported())
819 return BuildF64NearestInt(input);
820 op = m->Float64RoundTiesEven().op();
821 break;
822 }
823 case wasm::kExprF64Acos: {
824 return BuildF64Acos(input);
825 }
826 case wasm::kExprF64Asin: {
827 return BuildF64Asin(input);
828 }
829 case wasm::kExprF64Atan:
830 op = m->Float64Atan();
831 break;
832 case wasm::kExprF64Cos: {
833 op = m->Float64Cos();
834 break;
835 }
836 case wasm::kExprF64Sin: {
837 op = m->Float64Sin();
838 break;
839 }
840 case wasm::kExprF64Tan: {
841 op = m->Float64Tan();
842 break;
843 }
844 case wasm::kExprF64Exp: {
845 op = m->Float64Exp();
846 break;
847 }
848 case wasm::kExprF64Log:
849 op = m->Float64Log();
850 break;
851 case wasm::kExprI32ConvertI64:
852 op = m->TruncateInt64ToInt32();
853 break;
854 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertI32:
855 op = m->ChangeInt32ToInt64();
856 break;
857 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertI32:
858 op = m->ChangeUint32ToUint64();
859 break;
860 case wasm::kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
861 op = m->BitcastInt64ToFloat64();
862 break;
863 case wasm::kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
864 op = m->BitcastFloat64ToInt64();
865 break;
866 case wasm::kExprI64Clz:
867 op = m->Word64Clz();
868 break;
869 case wasm::kExprI64Ctz: {
870 OptionalOperator ctz64 = m->Word64Ctz();
871 if (ctz64.IsSupported()) {
872 op = ctz64.op();
873 break;
874 } else if (m->Is32() && m->Word32Ctz().IsSupported()) {
875 op = ctz64.placeholder();
876 break;
877 } else if (m->Word64ReverseBits().IsSupported()) {
878 Node* reversed = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64ReverseBits().op(), input);
879 Node* result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Clz(), reversed);
880 return result;
881 } else {
882 return BuildI64Ctz(input);
883 }
884 }
885 case wasm::kExprI64Popcnt: {
886 OptionalOperator popcnt64 = m->Word64Popcnt();
887 if (popcnt64.IsSupported()) {
888 op = popcnt64.op();
889 } else if (m->Is32() && m->Word32Popcnt().IsSupported()) {
890 op = popcnt64.placeholder();
891 } else {
892 return BuildI64Popcnt(input);
893 }
894 break;
895 }
896 case wasm::kExprI64Eqz:
897 op = m->Word64Equal();
898 return graph()->NewNode(op, input, mcgraph()->Int64Constant(0));
899 case wasm::kExprF32SConvertI64:
900 if (m->Is32()) {
901 return BuildF32SConvertI64(input);
902 }
903 op = m->RoundInt64ToFloat32();
904 break;
905 case wasm::kExprF32UConvertI64:
906 if (m->Is32()) {
907 return BuildF32UConvertI64(input);
908 }
909 op = m->RoundUint64ToFloat32();
910 break;
911 case wasm::kExprF64SConvertI64:
912 if (m->Is32()) {
913 return BuildF64SConvertI64(input);
914 }
915 op = m->RoundInt64ToFloat64();
916 break;
917 case wasm::kExprF64UConvertI64:
918 if (m->Is32()) {
919 return BuildF64UConvertI64(input);
920 }
921 op = m->RoundUint64ToFloat64();
922 break;
923 case wasm::kExprI32SExtendI8:
924 op = m->SignExtendWord8ToInt32();
925 break;
926 case wasm::kExprI32SExtendI16:
927 op = m->SignExtendWord16ToInt32();
928 break;
929 case wasm::kExprI64SExtendI8:
930 op = m->SignExtendWord8ToInt64();
931 break;
932 case wasm::kExprI64SExtendI16:
933 op = m->SignExtendWord16ToInt64();
934 break;
935 case wasm::kExprI64SExtendI32:
936 op = m->SignExtendWord32ToInt64();
937 break;
938 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
939 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
940 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
941 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
942 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
943 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
944 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
945 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
946 return mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()
947 ? BuildCcallConvertFloat(input, position, opcode)
948 : BuildIntConvertFloat(input, position, opcode);
949 case wasm::kExprRefIsNull:
950 return graph()->NewNode(m->WordEqual(), input, RefNull());
951 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem8S:
952 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Int8(), input);
953 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem8U:
954 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Uint8(), input);
955 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem16S:
956 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Int16(), input);
957 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem16U:
958 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Uint16(), input);
959 case wasm::kExprI32AsmjsLoadMem:
960 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Int32(), input);
961 case wasm::kExprF32AsmjsLoadMem:
962 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Float32(), input);
963 case wasm::kExprF64AsmjsLoadMem:
964 return BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType::Float64(), input);
965 default:
966 FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode);
967 }
968 return graph()->NewNode(op, input);
969}
970
971Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Float32Constant(float value) {
972 return mcgraph()->Float32Constant(value);
973}
974
975Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Float64Constant(double value) {
976 return mcgraph()->Float64Constant(value);
977}

979Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Simd128Constant(const uint8_t value[16]) {
980 has_simd_ = true;
981 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->S128Const(value));
982}

984namespace {
985Node* Branch(MachineGraph* mcgraph, Node* cond, Node** true_node,
986 Node** false_node, Node* control, BranchHint hint) {
987 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(cond)((void) 0);
988 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(control)((void) 0);
989 Node* branch =
990 mcgraph->graph()->NewNode(mcgraph->common()->Branch(hint), cond, control);
991 *true_node = mcgraph->graph()->NewNode(mcgraph->common()->IfTrue(), branch);
992 *false_node = mcgraph->graph()->NewNode(mcgraph->common()->IfFalse(), branch);
993 return branch;
994}
995} // namespace
996
997Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BranchNoHint(Node* cond, Node** true_node,
998 Node** false_node) {
999 return Branch(mcgraph(), cond, true_node, false_node, control(),
1000 BranchHint::kNone);
1001}
1002
1003Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BranchExpectTrue(Node* cond, Node** true_node,
1004 Node** false_node) {
1005 return Branch(mcgraph(), cond, true_node, false_node, control(),
1006 BranchHint::kTrue);
1007}
1008
1009Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BranchExpectFalse(Node* cond, Node** true_node,
1010 Node** false_node) {
1011 return Branch(mcgraph(), cond, true_node, false_node, control(),
1012 BranchHint::kFalse);
1013}
1014
1015TrapId WasmGraphBuilder::GetTrapIdForTrap(wasm::TrapReason reason) {
1016 // TODO(wasm): "!env_" should not happen when compiling an actual wasm
1017 // function.
1018 if (!env_ || !env_->runtime_exception_support) {
1019 // We use TrapId::kInvalid as a marker to tell the code generator
1020 // to generate a call to a testing c-function instead of a runtime
1021 // stub. This code should only be called from a cctest.
1022 return TrapId::kInvalid;
1023 }
1024
1025 switch (reason) {
1026#define TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(name) \
1027 case wasm::k##name: \
1028 static_assert( \
1029 static_cast<int>(TrapId::k##name) == wasm::WasmCode::kThrowWasm##name, \
1030 "trap id mismatch"); \
1031 return TrapId::k##name;
1032 FOREACH_WASM_TRAPREASON(TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID)TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapUnreachable) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapMemOutOfBounds
) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapUnalignedAccess) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID
(TrapDivByZero) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapDivUnrepresentable) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID
(TrapRemByZero) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapFloatUnrepresentable
) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapFuncInvalid) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(
TrapFuncSigMismatch) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapDataSegmentDropped
) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapElemSegmentDropped) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID
(TrapTableOutOfBounds) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapBrOnExnNull) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID
(TrapRethrowNull) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapNullDereference) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID
(TrapIllegalCast) TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID(TrapArrayOutOfBounds)
1033#undef TRAPREASON_TO_TRAPID
1034 default:
1035 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1036 }
1037}
1038
1039Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TrapIfTrue(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* cond,
1040 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1041 TrapId trap_id = GetTrapIdForTrap(reason);
1042 Node* node = SetControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->TrapIf(trap_id),
1043 cond, effect(), control()));
1044 SetSourcePosition(node, position);
1045 return node;
1046}
1047
1048Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TrapIfFalse(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* cond,
1049 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1050 TrapId trap_id = GetTrapIdForTrap(reason);
1051 Node* node = SetControl(graph()->NewNode(
1052 mcgraph()->common()->TrapUnless(trap_id), cond, effect(), control()));
1053 SetSourcePosition(node, position);
1054 return node;
1055}
1056
1057// Add a check that traps if {node} is equal to {val}.
1058Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TrapIfEq32(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* node,
1059 int32_t val,
1060 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1061 Int32Matcher m(node);
1062 if (m.HasValue() && !m.Is(val)) return graph()->start();
1063 if (val == 0) {
1064 return TrapIfFalse(reason, node, position);
1065 } else {
1066 return TrapIfTrue(reason,
1067 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word32Equal(),
1068 node, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(val)),
1069 position);
1070 }
1071}
1072
1073// Add a check that traps if {node} is zero.
1074Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ZeroCheck32(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* node,
1075 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1076 return TrapIfEq32(reason, node, 0, position);
1077}
1078
1079// Add a check that traps if {node} is equal to {val}.
1080Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TrapIfEq64(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* node,
1081 int64_t val,
1082 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1083 Int64Matcher m(node);
1084 if (m.HasValue() && !m.Is(val)) return graph()->start();
1085 return TrapIfTrue(reason,
1086 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word64Equal(), node,
1087 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(val)),
1088 position);
1089}
1090
1091// Add a check that traps if {node} is zero.
1092Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ZeroCheck64(wasm::TrapReason reason, Node* node,
1093 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1094 return TrapIfEq64(reason, node, 0, position);
1095}
1096
1097Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Switch(unsigned count, Node* key) {
1098 // The instruction selector will use {kArchTableSwitch} for large switches,
1099 // which has limited input count, see {InstructionSelector::EmitTableSwitch}.
1100 DCHECK_LE(count, Instruction::kMaxInputCount - 2)((void) 0); // value_range + 2
1101 DCHECK_LE(count, wasm::kV8MaxWasmFunctionBrTableSize + 1)((void) 0); // plus IfDefault
1102 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Switch(count), key, control());
1103}
1104
1105Node* WasmGraphBuilder::IfValue(int32_t value, Node* sw) {
1106 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kSwitch, sw->opcode())((void) 0);
1107 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfValue(value), sw);
1108}
1109
1110Node* WasmGraphBuilder::IfDefault(Node* sw) {
1111 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kSwitch, sw->opcode())((void) 0);
1112 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfDefault(), sw);
1113}
1114
1115Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Return(Vector<Node*> vals) {
1116 unsigned count = static_cast<unsigned>(vals.size());
1117 base::SmallVector<Node*, 8> buf(count + 3);
1118
1119 buf[0] = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
1120 if (count > 0) {
1121 memcpy(buf.data() + 1, vals.begin(), sizeof(void*) * count);
1122 }
1123 buf[count + 1] = effect();
1124 buf[count + 2] = control();
1125 Node* ret = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Return(count), count + 3,
1126 buf.data());
1127
1128 MergeControlToEnd(mcgraph(), ret);
1129 return ret;
1130}
1131
1132Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Trap(wasm::TrapReason reason,
1133 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
1134 TrapIfFalse(reason, Int32Constant(0), position);
1135 Return(Vector<Node*>{});
1136 return nullptr;
1137}
1138
1139Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MaskShiftCount32(Node* node) {
1140 static const int32_t kMask32 = 0x1F;
1141 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Word32ShiftIsSafe()) {
1
Assuming the condition is true
→
2
←
Taking true branch
→
1142 // Shifts by constants are so common we pattern-match them here.
1143 Int32Matcher match(node);
3
←
Calling constructor for 'IntMatcher<int, v8::internal::compiler::IrOpcode::kInt32Constant>'
→
1144 if (match.HasValue()) {
1145 int32_t masked = (match.Value() & kMask32);
1146 if (match.Value() != masked) node = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(masked);
1147 } else {
1148 node = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word32And(), node,
1149 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(kMask32));
1150 }
1151 }
1152 return node;
1153}
1154
1155Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MaskShiftCount64(Node* node) {
1156 static const int64_t kMask64 = 0x3F;
1157 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Word32ShiftIsSafe()) {
1158 // Shifts by constants are so common we pattern-match them here.
1159 Int64Matcher match(node);
1160 if (match.HasValue()) {
1161 int64_t masked = (match.Value() & kMask64);
1162 if (match.Value() != masked) node = mcgraph()->Int64Constant(masked);
1163 } else {
1164 node = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word64And(), node,
1165 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(kMask64));
1166 }
1167 }
1168 return node;
1169}
1170
1171namespace {
1172
1173bool ReverseBytesSupported(MachineOperatorBuilder* m, size_t size_in_bytes) {
1174 switch (size_in_bytes) {
1175 case 4:
1176 case 16:
1177 return true;
1178 case 8:
1179 return m->Is64();
1180 default:
1181 break;
1182 }
1183 return false;
1184}
1185
1186} // namespace
1187
1188Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildChangeEndiannessStore(
1189 Node* node, MachineRepresentation mem_rep, wasm::ValueType wasmtype) {
1190 Node* result;
1191 Node* value = node;
1192 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
1193 int valueSizeInBytes = wasmtype.element_size_bytes();
1194 int valueSizeInBits = 8 * valueSizeInBytes;
1195 bool isFloat = false;
1196
1197 switch (wasmtype.kind()) {
1198 case wasm::ValueType::kF64:
1199 value = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(), node);
1200 isFloat = true;
1201 V8_FALLTHROUGH[[clang::fallthrough]];
1202 case wasm::ValueType::kI64:
1203 result = mcgraph()->Int64Constant(0);
1204 break;
1205 case wasm::ValueType::kF32:
1206 value = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastFloat32ToInt32(), node);
1207 isFloat = true;
1208 V8_FALLTHROUGH[[clang::fallthrough]];
1209 case wasm::ValueType::kI32:
1210 result = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
1211 break;
1212 case wasm::ValueType::kS128:
1213 DCHECK(ReverseBytesSupported(m, valueSizeInBytes))((void) 0);
1214 break;
1215 default:
1216 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1217 }
1218
1219 if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8) {
1220 // No need to change endianness for byte size, return original node
1221 return node;
1222 }
1223 if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI64 && mem_rep < MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1224 // In case we store lower part of WasmI64 expression, we can truncate
1225 // upper 32bits
1226 value = graph()->NewNode(m->TruncateInt64ToInt32(), value);
1227 valueSizeInBytes = wasm::kWasmI32.element_size_bytes();
1228 valueSizeInBits = 8 * valueSizeInBytes;
1229 if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
1230 value =
1231 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Shl(), value, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(16));
1232 }
1233 } else if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI32 &&
1234 mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
1235 value =
1236 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Shl(), value, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(16));
1237 }
1238
1239 int i;
1240 uint32_t shiftCount;
1241
1242 if (ReverseBytesSupported(m, valueSizeInBytes)) {
1243 switch (valueSizeInBytes) {
1244 case 4:
1245 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32ReverseBytes(), value);
1246 break;
1247 case 8:
1248 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64ReverseBytes(), value);
1249 break;
1250 case 16:
1251 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Simd128ReverseBytes(), value);
1252 break;
1253 default:
1254 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1255 break;
1256 }
1257 } else {
1258 for (i = 0, shiftCount = valueSizeInBits - 8; i < valueSizeInBits / 2;
1259 i += 8, shiftCount -= 16) {
1260 Node* shiftLower;
1261 Node* shiftHigher;
1262 Node* lowerByte;
1263 Node* higherByte;
1264
1265 DCHECK_LT(0, shiftCount)((void) 0);
1266 DCHECK_EQ(0, (shiftCount + 8) % 16)((void) 0);
1267
1268 if (valueSizeInBits > 32) {
1269 shiftLower = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Shl(), value,
1270 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(shiftCount));
1271 shiftHigher = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Shr(), value,
1272 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(shiftCount));
1273 lowerByte = graph()->NewNode(
1274 m->Word64And(), shiftLower,
1275 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF)
1276 << (valueSizeInBits - 8 - i)));
1277 higherByte = graph()->NewNode(
1278 m->Word64And(), shiftHigher,
1279 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF) << i));
1280 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Or(), result, lowerByte);
1281 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Or(), result, higherByte);
1282 } else {
1283 shiftLower = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Shl(), value,
1284 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(shiftCount));
1285 shiftHigher = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Shr(), value,
1286 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(shiftCount));
1287 lowerByte = graph()->NewNode(
1288 m->Word32And(), shiftLower,
1289 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF)
1290 << (valueSizeInBits - 8 - i)));
1291 higherByte = graph()->NewNode(
1292 m->Word32And(), shiftHigher,
1293 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF) << i));
1294 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Or(), result, lowerByte);
1295 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Or(), result, higherByte);
1296 }
1297 }
1298 }
1299
1300 if (isFloat) {
1301 switch (wasmtype.kind()) {
1302 case wasm::ValueType::kF64:
1303 result = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastInt64ToFloat64(), result);
1304 break;
1305 case wasm::ValueType::kF32:
1306 result = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastInt32ToFloat32(), result);
1307 break;
1308 default:
1309 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1310 break;
1311 }
1312 }
1313
1314 return result;
1315}
1316
1317Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildChangeEndiannessLoad(Node* node,
1318 MachineType memtype,
1319 wasm::ValueType wasmtype) {
1320 Node* result;
1321 Node* value = node;
1322 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
1323 int valueSizeInBytes = ElementSizeInBytes(memtype.representation());
1324 int valueSizeInBits = 8 * valueSizeInBytes;
1325 bool isFloat = false;
1326
1327 switch (memtype.representation()) {
1328 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1329 value = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(), node);
1330 isFloat = true;
1331 V8_FALLTHROUGH[[clang::fallthrough]];
1332 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
1333 result = mcgraph()->Int64Constant(0);
1334 break;
1335 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1336 value = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastFloat32ToInt32(), node);
1337 isFloat = true;
1338 V8_FALLTHROUGH[[clang::fallthrough]];
1339 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
1340 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
1341 result = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
1342 break;
1343 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
1344 // No need to change endianness for byte size, return original node
1345 return node;
1346 break;
1347 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1348 DCHECK(ReverseBytesSupported(m, valueSizeInBytes))((void) 0);
1349 break;
1350 default:
1351 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1352 }
1353
1354 int i;
1355 uint32_t shiftCount;
1356
1357 if (ReverseBytesSupported(m, valueSizeInBytes < 4 ? 4 : valueSizeInBytes)) {
1358 switch (valueSizeInBytes) {
1359 case 2:
1360 result =
1361 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32ReverseBytes(),
1362 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Shl(), value,
1363 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(16)));
1364 break;
1365 case 4:
1366 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32ReverseBytes(), value);
1367 break;
1368 case 8:
1369 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64ReverseBytes(), value);
1370 break;
1371 case 16:
1372 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Simd128ReverseBytes(), value);
1373 break;
1374 default:
1375 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1376 }
1377 } else {
1378 for (i = 0, shiftCount = valueSizeInBits - 8; i < valueSizeInBits / 2;
1379 i += 8, shiftCount -= 16) {
1380 Node* shiftLower;
1381 Node* shiftHigher;
1382 Node* lowerByte;
1383 Node* higherByte;
1384
1385 DCHECK_LT(0, shiftCount)((void) 0);
1386 DCHECK_EQ(0, (shiftCount + 8) % 16)((void) 0);
1387
1388 if (valueSizeInBits > 32) {
1389 shiftLower = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Shl(), value,
1390 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(shiftCount));
1391 shiftHigher = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Shr(), value,
1392 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(shiftCount));
1393 lowerByte = graph()->NewNode(
1394 m->Word64And(), shiftLower,
1395 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF)
1396 << (valueSizeInBits - 8 - i)));
1397 higherByte = graph()->NewNode(
1398 m->Word64And(), shiftHigher,
1399 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(static_cast<uint64_t>(0xFF) << i));
1400 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Or(), result, lowerByte);
1401 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Or(), result, higherByte);
1402 } else {
1403 shiftLower = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Shl(), value,
1404 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(shiftCount));
1405 shiftHigher = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Shr(), value,
1406 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(shiftCount));
1407 lowerByte = graph()->NewNode(
1408 m->Word32And(), shiftLower,
1409 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF)
1410 << (valueSizeInBits - 8 - i)));
1411 higherByte = graph()->NewNode(
1412 m->Word32And(), shiftHigher,
1413 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(0xFF) << i));
1414 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Or(), result, lowerByte);
1415 result = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Or(), result, higherByte);
1416 }
1417 }
1418 }
1419
1420 if (isFloat) {
1421 switch (memtype.representation()) {
1422 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1423 result = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastInt64ToFloat64(), result);
1424 break;
1425 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1426 result = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastInt32ToFloat32(), result);
1427 break;
1428 default:
1429 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1430 break;
1431 }
1432 }
1433
1434 // We need to sign extend the value
1435 if (memtype.IsSigned()) {
1436 DCHECK(!isFloat)((void) 0);
1437 if (valueSizeInBits < 32) {
1438 Node* shiftBitCount;
1439 // Perform sign extension using following trick
1440 // result = (x << machine_width - type_width) >> (machine_width -
1441 // type_width)
1442 if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI64) {
1443 shiftBitCount = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(64 - valueSizeInBits);
1444 result = graph()->NewNode(
1445 m->Word64Sar(),
1446 graph()->NewNode(m->Word64Shl(),
1447 graph()->NewNode(m->ChangeInt32ToInt64(), result),
1448 shiftBitCount),
1449 shiftBitCount);
1450 } else if (wasmtype == wasm::kWasmI32) {
1451 shiftBitCount = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(32 - valueSizeInBits);
1452 result = graph()->NewNode(
1453 m->Word32Sar(),
1454 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Shl(), result, shiftBitCount),
1455 shiftBitCount);
1456 }
1457 }
1458 }
1459
1460 return result;
1461}
1462
1463Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF32CopySign(Node* left, Node* right) {
1464 Node* result = Unop(
1465 wasm::kExprF32ReinterpretI32,
1466 Binop(wasm::kExprI32Ior,
1467 Binop(wasm::kExprI32And, Unop(wasm::kExprI32ReinterpretF32, left),
1468 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0x7FFFFFFF)),
1469 Binop(wasm::kExprI32And, Unop(wasm::kExprI32ReinterpretF32, right),
1470 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0x80000000))));
1471
1472 return result;
1473}
1474
1475Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF64CopySign(Node* left, Node* right) {
1476 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()) {
1477 return gasm_->BitcastInt64ToFloat64(gasm_->Word64Or(
1478 gasm_->Word64And(gasm_->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(left),
1479 gasm_->Int64Constant(0x7FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF)),
1480 gasm_->Word64And(gasm_->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(right),
1481 gasm_->Int64Constant(0x8000000000000000))));
1482 }
1483
1484 DCHECK(mcgraph()->machine()->Is32())((void) 0);
1485
1486 Node* high_word_left = gasm_->Float64ExtractHighWord32(left);
1487 Node* high_word_right = gasm_->Float64ExtractHighWord32(right);
1488
1489 Node* new_high_word = gasm_->Word32Or(
1490 gasm_->Word32And(high_word_left, gasm_->Int32Constant(0x7FFFFFFF)),
1491 gasm_->Word32And(high_word_right, gasm_->Int32Constant(0x80000000)));
1492
1493 return gasm_->Float64InsertHighWord32(left, new_high_word);
1494}

1498MachineType IntConvertType(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1499 switch (opcode) {
1500 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF32:
1501 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF64:
1502 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
1503 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
1504 return MachineType::Int32();
1505 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:
1506 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF64:
1507 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
1508 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
1509 return MachineType::Uint32();
1510 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
1511 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
1512 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1513 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
1514 return MachineType::Int64();
1515 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
1516 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
1517 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
1518 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
1519 return MachineType::Uint64();
1520 default:
1521 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1522 }
1523}
1524
1525MachineType FloatConvertType(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1526 switch (opcode) {
1527 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF32:
1528 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:
1529 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
1530 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
1531 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
1532 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
1533 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1534 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
1535 return MachineType::Float32();
1536 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF64:
1537 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF64:
1538 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
1539 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
1540 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
1541 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
1542 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
1543 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
1544 return MachineType::Float64();
1545 default:
1546 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1547 }
1548}
1549
1550const Operator* ConvertOp(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1551 switch (opcode) {
1552 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF32:
1553 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat32ToInt32(
1554 TruncateKind::kSetOverflowToMin);
1555 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
1556 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat32ToInt32(
1557 TruncateKind::kArchitectureDefault);
1558 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:
1559 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat32ToUint32(
1560 TruncateKind::kSetOverflowToMin);
1561 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
1562 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat32ToUint32(
1563 TruncateKind::kArchitectureDefault);
1564 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF64:
1565 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
1566 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeFloat64ToInt32();
1567 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF64:
1568 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
1569 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat64ToUint32();
1570 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
1571 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1572 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TryTruncateFloat32ToInt64();
1573 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
1574 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
1575 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TryTruncateFloat32ToUint64();
1576 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
1577 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
1578 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TryTruncateFloat64ToInt64();
1579 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
1580 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
1581 return builder->mcgraph()->machine()->TryTruncateFloat64ToUint64();
1582 default:
1583 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1584 }
1585}
1586
1587wasm::WasmOpcode ConvertBackOp(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1588 switch (opcode) {
1589 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF32:
1590 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
1591 return wasm::kExprF32SConvertI32;
1592 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:
1593 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
1594 return wasm::kExprF32UConvertI32;
1595 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF64:
1596 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
1597 return wasm::kExprF64SConvertI32;
1598 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF64:
1599 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
1600 return wasm::kExprF64UConvertI32;
1601 default:
1602 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1603 }
1604}
1605
1606bool IsTrappingConvertOp(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1607 switch (opcode) {
1608 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF32:
1609 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF32:
1610 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertF64:
1611 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertF64:
1612 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
1613 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
1614 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
1615 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
1616 return true;
1617 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
1618 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
1619 case wasm::kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
1620 case wasm::kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
1621 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1622 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
1623 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
1624 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
1625 return false;
1626 default:
1627 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1628 }
1629}
