1631Node* Zero(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, const MachineType& ty) {
1632 switch (ty.representation()) {
1633 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
1634 return builder->Int32Constant(0);
1635 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
1636 return builder->Int64Constant(0);
1637 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1638 return builder->Float32Constant(0.0);
1639 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1640 return builder->Float64Constant(0.0);
1641 default:
1642 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1643 }
1644}
1645
1646Node* Min(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, const MachineType& ty) {
1647 switch (ty.semantic()) {
1648 case MachineSemantic::kInt32:
1649 return builder->Int32Constant(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min());
1650 case MachineSemantic::kUint32:
1651 return builder->Int32Constant(std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::min());
1652 case MachineSemantic::kInt64:
1653 return builder->Int64Constant(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min());
1654 case MachineSemantic::kUint64:
1655 return builder->Int64Constant(std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::min());
1656 default:
1657 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1658 }
1659}
1660
1661Node* Max(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, const MachineType& ty) {
1662 switch (ty.semantic()) {
1663 case MachineSemantic::kInt32:
1664 return builder->Int32Constant(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max());
1665 case MachineSemantic::kUint32:
1666 return builder->Int32Constant(std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
1667 case MachineSemantic::kInt64:
1668 return builder->Int64Constant(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max());
1669 case MachineSemantic::kUint64:
1670 return builder->Int64Constant(std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max());
1671 default:
1672 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1673 }
1674}

1676wasm::WasmOpcode TruncOp(const MachineType& ty) {
1677 switch (ty.representation()) {
1678 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1679 return wasm::kExprF32Trunc;
1680 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1681 return wasm::kExprF64Trunc;
1682 default:
1683 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1684 }
1685}

1687wasm::WasmOpcode NeOp(const MachineType& ty) {
1688 switch (ty.representation()) {
1689 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1690 return wasm::kExprF32Ne;
1691 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1692 return wasm::kExprF64Ne;
1693 default:
1694 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1695 }

1698wasm::WasmOpcode LtOp(const MachineType& ty) {
1699 switch (ty.representation()) {
1700 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1701 return wasm::kExprF32Lt;
1702 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1703 return wasm::kExprF64Lt;
1704 default:
1705 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1706 }

1708
1709Node* ConvertTrapTest(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, wasm::WasmOpcode opcode,
1710 const MachineType& int_ty, const MachineType& float_ty,
1711 Node* trunc, Node* converted_value) {
1712 if (int_ty.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
1713 Node* check = builder->Unop(ConvertBackOp(opcode), converted_value);
1714 return builder->Binop(NeOp(float_ty), trunc, check);
1715 }
1716 return builder->graph()->NewNode(builder->mcgraph()->common()->Projection(1),
1717 trunc, builder->graph()->start());
1718}
1719
1720Node* ConvertSaturateTest(WasmGraphBuilder* builder, wasm::WasmOpcode opcode,
1721 const MachineType& int_ty,
1722 const MachineType& float_ty, Node* trunc,
1723 Node* converted_value) {
1724 Node* test = ConvertTrapTest(builder, opcode, int_ty, float_ty, trunc,
1725 converted_value);
1726 if (int_ty.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1727 test = builder->Binop(wasm::kExprI64Eq, test, builder->Int64Constant(0));
1728 }
1729 return test;
1730}
1731
1732} // namespace
1733
1734Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildIntConvertFloat(Node* input,
1735 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
1736 wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1737 const MachineType int_ty = IntConvertType(opcode);
1738 const MachineType float_ty = FloatConvertType(opcode);
1739 const Operator* conv_op = ConvertOp(this, opcode);
1740 Node* trunc = nullptr;
1741 Node* converted_value = nullptr;
1742 const bool is_int32 =
1743 int_ty.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
1744 if (is_int32) {
1745 trunc = Unop(TruncOp(float_ty), input);
1746 converted_value = graph()->NewNode(conv_op, trunc);
1747 } else {
1748 trunc = graph()->NewNode(conv_op, input);
1749 converted_value = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Projection(0),
1750 trunc, graph()->start());
1751 }
1752 if (IsTrappingConvertOp(opcode)) {
1753 Node* test =
1754 ConvertTrapTest(this, opcode, int_ty, float_ty, trunc, converted_value);
1755 if (is_int32) {
1756 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapFloatUnrepresentable, test, position);
1757 } else {
1758 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapFloatUnrepresentable, test, position);
1759 }
1760 return converted_value;
1761 }
1762 if (mcgraph()->machine()->SatConversionIsSafe()) {
1763 return converted_value;
1764 }
1765 Node* test = ConvertSaturateTest(this, opcode, int_ty, float_ty, trunc,
1766 converted_value);
1767 Diamond tl_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), test, BranchHint::kFalse);
1768 tl_d.Chain(control());
1769 Node* nan_test = Binop(NeOp(float_ty), input, input);
1770 Diamond nan_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), nan_test, BranchHint::kFalse);
1771 nan_d.Nest(tl_d, true);
1772 Node* neg_test = Binop(LtOp(float_ty), input, Zero(this, float_ty));
1773 Diamond sat_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), neg_test, BranchHint::kNone);
1774 sat_d.Nest(nan_d, false);
1775 Node* sat_val =
1776 sat_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), Min(this, int_ty), Max(this, int_ty));
1777 Node* nan_val =
1778 nan_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), Zero(this, int_ty), sat_val);
1779 return tl_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), nan_val, converted_value);
1780}

1808Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildBitCountingCall(Node* input, ExternalReference ref,
1809 MachineRepresentation input_type) {
1810 Node* stack_slot_param = StoreArgsInStackSlot({{input_type, input}});
1811
1812 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
1813 MachineSignature sig(1, 1, sig_types);
1814
1815 Node* function = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->ExternalConstant(ref));
1816
1817 return BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot_param);
1818}

1855
1856Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF32Ceil(Node* input) {
1857 MachineType type = MachineType::Float32();

1915
1916Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCFuncInstruction(ExternalReference ref,
1917 MachineType type, Node* input0,
1918 Node* input1) {
1919 // We do truncation by calling a C function which calculates the result.
1920 // The input is passed to the C function as a byte buffer holding the two
1921 // input doubles. We reserve this byte buffer as a stack slot, store the
1922 // parameters in this buffer slots, pass a pointer to the buffer to the C
1923 // function, and after calling the C function we collect the return value from
1924 // the buffer.
1925 Node* stack_slot;
1926 if (input1) {
1927 stack_slot = StoreArgsInStackSlot(
1928 {{type.representation(), input0}, {type.representation(), input1}});
1929 } else {
1930 stack_slot = StoreArgsInStackSlot({{type.representation(), input0}});
1931 }
1932
1933 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Pointer()};
1934 MachineSignature sig(0, 1, sig_types);
1935 Node* function = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->ExternalConstant(ref));
1936 BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot);
1937
1938 return SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(type),
1939 stack_slot, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0),
1940 effect(), control()));
1941}
1942
1943Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF32SConvertI64(Node* input) {
1944 // TODO(titzer/bradnelson): Check handlng of asm.js case.
1945 return BuildIntToFloatConversionInstruction(
1946 input, ExternalReference::wasm_int64_to_float32(),
1947 MachineRepresentation::kWord64, MachineType::Float32());
1948}
1949Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF32UConvertI64(Node* input) {
1950 // TODO(titzer/bradnelson): Check handlng of asm.js case.
1951 return BuildIntToFloatConversionInstruction(
1952 input, ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_to_float32(),
1953 MachineRepresentation::kWord64, MachineType::Float32());
1954}

1957 input, ExternalReference::wasm_int64_to_float64(),
1958 MachineRepresentation::kWord64, MachineType::Float64());
1959}
1960Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildF64UConvertI64(Node* input) {

1964}
1965
1966Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildIntToFloatConversionInstruction(
1967 Node* input, ExternalReference ref,
1968 MachineRepresentation parameter_representation,
1969 const MachineType result_type) {
1970 int stack_slot_size =
1971 std::max(ElementSizeInBytes(parameter_representation),
1972 ElementSizeInBytes(result_type.representation()));
1973 Node* stack_slot =
1974 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->StackSlot(stack_slot_size));
1975 const Operator* store_op = mcgraph()->machine()->Store(
1976 StoreRepresentation(parameter_representation, kNoWriteBarrier));
1977 SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(store_op, stack_slot, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0),
1978 input, effect(), control()));
1979 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Pointer()};
1980 MachineSignature sig(0, 1, sig_types);
1981 Node* function = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->ExternalConstant(ref));
1982 BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot);
1983 return SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(result_type),
1984 stack_slot, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0),
1985 effect(), control()));
1986}

1988namespace {
1989
1990ExternalReference convert_ccall_ref(WasmGraphBuilder* builder,
1991 wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
1992 switch (opcode) {
1993 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF32:
1994 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1995 return ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_int64();
1996 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF32:
1997 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
1998 return ExternalReference::wasm_float32_to_uint64();
1999 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertF64:
2000 case wasm::kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
2001 return ExternalReference::wasm_float64_to_int64();
2002 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertF64:
2003 case wasm::kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
2004 return ExternalReference::wasm_float64_to_uint64();
2005 default:
2006 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
2007 }
2008}

2010} // namespace
2011
2012Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCcallConvertFloat(Node* input,
2013 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2014 wasm::WasmOpcode opcode) {
2015 const MachineType int_ty = IntConvertType(opcode);
2016 const MachineType float_ty = FloatConvertType(opcode);
2017 ExternalReference call_ref = convert_ccall_ref(this, opcode);
2018 int stack_slot_size = std::max(ElementSizeInBytes(int_ty.representation()),
2019 ElementSizeInBytes(float_ty.representation()));
2020 Node* stack_slot =
2021 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->StackSlot(stack_slot_size));
2022 const Operator* store_op = mcgraph()->machine()->Store(
2023 StoreRepresentation(float_ty.representation(), kNoWriteBarrier));
2024 SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(store_op, stack_slot, Int32Constant(0), input,
2025 effect(), control()));
2026 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
2027 MachineSignature sig(1, 1, sig_types);
2028 Node* function =
2029 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->ExternalConstant(call_ref));
2030 Node* overflow = BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot);
2031 if (IsTrappingConvertOp(opcode)) {
2032 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapFloatUnrepresentable, overflow, position);
2033 return SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(int_ty),
2034 stack_slot, Int32Constant(0), effect(),
2035 control()));
2036 }
2037 Node* test = Binop(wasm::kExprI32Eq, overflow, Int32Constant(0), position);
2038 Diamond tl_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), test, BranchHint::kFalse);
2039 tl_d.Chain(control());
2040 Node* nan_test = Binop(NeOp(float_ty), input, input);
2041 Diamond nan_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), nan_test, BranchHint::kFalse);
2042 nan_d.Nest(tl_d, true);
2043 Node* neg_test = Binop(LtOp(float_ty), input, Zero(this, float_ty));
2044 Diamond sat_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), neg_test, BranchHint::kNone);
2045 sat_d.Nest(nan_d, false);
2046 Node* sat_val =
2047 sat_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), Min(this, int_ty), Max(this, int_ty));
2048 Node* load =
2049 SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(int_ty), stack_slot,
2050 Int32Constant(0), effect(), control()));
2051 Node* nan_val =
2052 nan_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), Zero(this, int_ty), sat_val);
2053 return tl_d.Phi(int_ty.representation(), nan_val, load);
2054}

2056Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MemoryGrow(Node* input) {
2057 needs_stack_check_ = true;
2058
2059 WasmMemoryGrowDescriptor interface_descriptor;
2060 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
2061 mcgraph()->zone(), // zone
2062 interface_descriptor, // descriptor
2063 interface_descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(), // stack parameter count
2064 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, // flags
2065 Operator::kNoProperties, // properties
2066 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub); // stub call mode
2067 // A direct call to a wasm runtime stub defined in this module.
2068 // Just encode the stub index. This will be patched at relocation.
2069 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
2070 wasm::WasmCode::kWasmMemoryGrow, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
2071 return SetEffectControl(
2072 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), call_target,
2073 input, effect(), control()));
2074}
2075
2076Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Throw(uint32_t exception_index,
2077 const wasm::WasmException* exception,
2078 const Vector<Node*> values,
2079 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2080 needs_stack_check_ = true;
2081 uint32_t encoded_size = WasmExceptionPackage::GetEncodedSize(exception);
2082 Node* create_parameters[] = {
2083 LoadExceptionTagFromTable(exception_index),
2084 BuildChangeUint31ToSmi(Uint32Constant(encoded_size))};
2085 Node* except_obj =
2086 BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::kWasmThrowCreate, create_parameters,
2087 arraysize(create_parameters)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(create_parameters))));
2088 SetSourcePosition(except_obj, position);
2089 Node* values_array = CALL_BUILTIN(
2090 WasmGetOwnProperty, except_obj,
2091 LOAD_FULL_POINTER(BuildLoadIsolateRoot(),gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset( RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol
))
2092 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset( RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol
))
2093 RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol))gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset( RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol
)),
2094 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
2095 uint32_t index = 0;
2096 const wasm::WasmExceptionSig* sig = exception->sig;
2097 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2098 for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); ++i) {
2099 Node* value = values[i];
2100 switch (sig->GetParam(i).kind()) {
2101 case wasm::ValueType::kF32:
2102 value = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastFloat32ToInt32(), value);
2103 V8_FALLTHROUGH[[clang::fallthrough]];
2104 case wasm::ValueType::kI32:
2105 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index, value);
2106 break;
2107 case wasm::ValueType::kF64:
2108 value = graph()->NewNode(m->BitcastFloat64ToInt64(), value);
2109 V8_FALLTHROUGH[[clang::fallthrough]];
2110 case wasm::ValueType::kI64: {
2111 Node* upper32 = graph()->NewNode(
2112 m->TruncateInt64ToInt32(),
2113 Binop(wasm::kExprI64ShrU, value, Int64Constant(32)));
2114 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index, upper32);
2115 Node* lower32 = graph()->NewNode(m->TruncateInt64ToInt32(), value);
2116 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index, lower32);
2117 break;
2118 }
2119 case wasm::ValueType::kS128:
2120 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(
2121 values_array, &index,
2122 graph()->NewNode(m->I32x4ExtractLane(0), value));
2123 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(
2124 values_array, &index,
2125 graph()->NewNode(m->I32x4ExtractLane(1), value));
2126 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(
2127 values_array, &index,
2128 graph()->NewNode(m->I32x4ExtractLane(2), value));
2129 BuildEncodeException32BitValue(
2130 values_array, &index,
2131 graph()->NewNode(m->I32x4ExtractLane(3), value));
2132 break;
2133 case wasm::ValueType::kRef:
2134 case wasm::ValueType::kOptRef:
2135 STORE_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(values_array, index, value);
2136 ++index;
2137 break;
2138 case wasm::ValueType::kRtt: // TODO(7748): Implement.
2139 case wasm::ValueType::kI8:
2140 case wasm::ValueType::kI16:
2141 case wasm::ValueType::kStmt:
2142 case wasm::ValueType::kBottom:
2143 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
2144 }
2145 }
2146 DCHECK_EQ(encoded_size, index)((void) 0);
2147 WasmThrowDescriptor interface_descriptor;
2148 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
2149 mcgraph()->zone(), interface_descriptor,
2150 interface_descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(), CallDescriptor::kNoFlags,
2151 Operator::kNoProperties, StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
2152 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
2153 wasm::WasmCode::kWasmThrow, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
2154 Node* call = SetEffectControl(
2155 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), call_target,
2156 except_obj, effect(), control()));
2157 SetSourcePosition(call, position);
2158 return call;
2159}
2160
2161void WasmGraphBuilder::BuildEncodeException32BitValue(Node* values_array,
2162 uint32_t* index,
2163 Node* value) {
2164 MachineOperatorBuilder* machine = mcgraph()->machine();
2165 Node* upper_halfword_as_smi = BuildChangeUint31ToSmi(
2166 graph()->NewNode(machine->Word32Shr(), value, Int32Constant(16)));
2167 STORE_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_SMI(values_array, *index, upper_halfword_as_smi);
2168 ++(*index);
2169 Node* lower_halfword_as_smi = BuildChangeUint31ToSmi(
2170 graph()->NewNode(machine->Word32And(), value, Int32Constant(0xFFFFu)));
2171 STORE_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_SMI(values_array, *index, lower_halfword_as_smi);
2172 ++(*index);
2173}
2174
2175Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildDecodeException32BitValue(Node* values_array,
2176 uint32_t* index) {
2177 MachineOperatorBuilder* machine = mcgraph()->machine();
2178 Node* upper =
2179 BuildChangeSmiToInt32(LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_SMI(values_array, *index));
2180 (*index)++;
2181 upper = graph()->NewNode(machine->Word32Shl(), upper, Int32Constant(16));
2182 Node* lower =
2183 BuildChangeSmiToInt32(LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_SMI(values_array, *index));
2184 (*index)++;
2185 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(machine->Word32Or(), upper, lower);
2186 return value;
2187}
2188
2189Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildDecodeException64BitValue(Node* values_array,
2190 uint32_t* index) {
2191 Node* upper = Binop(wasm::kExprI64Shl,
2192 Unop(wasm::kExprI64UConvertI32,
2193 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, index)),
2194 Int64Constant(32));
2195 Node* lower = Unop(wasm::kExprI64UConvertI32,
2196 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, index));
2197 return Binop(wasm::kExprI64Ior, upper, lower);
2198}

2200Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Rethrow(Node* except_obj) {
2201 // TODO(v8:8091): Currently the message of the original exception is not being
2202 // preserved when rethrown to the console. The pending message will need to be
2203 // saved when caught and restored here while being rethrown.

2206 mcgraph()->zone(), interface_descriptor,

2209 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
2210 wasm::WasmCode::kWasmRethrow, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
2211 return gasm_->Call(call_descriptor, call_target, except_obj);

2227Node* WasmGraphBuilder::GetExceptionTag(Node* except_obj,
2228 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2229 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapBrOnExnNull, gasm_->WordEqual(RefNull(), except_obj),
2230 position);
2231 return CALL_BUILTIN(
2232 WasmGetOwnProperty, except_obj,
2233 LOAD_FULL_POINTER(gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kwasm_exception_tag_symbol
))
2234 BuildLoadIsolateRoot(),gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kwasm_exception_tag_symbol
))
2235 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kwasm_exception_tag_symbol))gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kwasm_exception_tag_symbol
)),
2236 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));

2239Node* WasmGraphBuilder::GetExceptionValues(Node* except_obj,
2240 const wasm::WasmException* exception,
2241 Vector<Node*> values) {
2242 Node* values_array = CALL_BUILTIN(
2243 WasmGetOwnProperty, except_obj,
2244 LOAD_FULL_POINTER(BuildLoadIsolateRoot(),gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset( RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol
))
2245 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset( RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol
))
2246 RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol))gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset( RootIndex::kwasm_exception_values_symbol
)),
2247 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
2248 uint32_t index = 0;
2249 const wasm::WasmExceptionSig* sig = exception->sig;
2250 DCHECK_EQ(sig->parameter_count(), values.size())((void) 0);
2251 for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); ++i) {
2252 Node* value;
2253 switch (sig->GetParam(i).kind()) {
2254 case wasm::ValueType::kI32:
2255 value = BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index);
2256 break;
2257 case wasm::ValueType::kI64:
2258 value = BuildDecodeException64BitValue(values_array, &index);
2259 break;
2260 case wasm::ValueType::kF32: {
2261 value = Unop(wasm::kExprF32ReinterpretI32,
2262 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2263 break;
2264 }
2265 case wasm::ValueType::kF64: {
2266 value = Unop(wasm::kExprF64ReinterpretI64,
2267 BuildDecodeException64BitValue(values_array, &index));
2268 break;
2269 }
2270 case wasm::ValueType::kS128:
2271 value = graph()->NewNode(
2272 mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4Splat(),
2273 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2274 value = graph()->NewNode(
2275 mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ReplaceLane(1), value,
2276 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2277 value = graph()->NewNode(
2278 mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ReplaceLane(2), value,
2279 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2280 value = graph()->NewNode(
2281 mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ReplaceLane(3), value,
2282 BuildDecodeException32BitValue(values_array, &index));
2283 break;
2284 case wasm::ValueType::kRef:
2285 case wasm::ValueType::kOptRef:
2286 value = LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(values_array, index);
2287 ++index;
2288 break;
2289 case wasm::ValueType::kRtt: // TODO(7748): Implement.
2290 case wasm::ValueType::kI8:
2291 case wasm::ValueType::kI16:
2292 case wasm::ValueType::kStmt:
2293 case wasm::ValueType::kBottom:
2294 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
2295 }
2296 values[i] = value;
2297 }
2298 DCHECK_EQ(index, WasmExceptionPackage::GetEncodedSize(exception))((void) 0);
2299 return values_array;
2300}
2301
2302Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32DivS(Node* left, Node* right,
2303 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2304 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2305 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapDivByZero, right, position);
2306 Node* before = control();
2307 Node* denom_is_m1;
2308 Node* denom_is_not_m1;
2309 BranchExpectFalse(
2310 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Equal(), right, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(-1)),
2311 &denom_is_m1, &denom_is_not_m1);
2312 SetControl(denom_is_m1);
2313 TrapIfEq32(wasm::kTrapDivUnrepresentable, left, kMinInt, position);
2314 if (control() != denom_is_m1) {
2315 SetControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Merge(2), denom_is_not_m1,
2316 control()));
2317 } else {
2318 SetControl(before);
2319 }
2320 return graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Div(), left, right, control());
2321}
2322
2323Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32RemS(Node* left, Node* right,
2324 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2325 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2326
2327 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapRemByZero, right, position);
2328
2329 Diamond d(
2330 graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2331 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Equal(), right, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(-1)),
2332 BranchHint::kFalse);
2333 d.Chain(control());
2334
2335 return d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0),
2336 graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Mod(), left, right, d.if_false));
2337}
2338
2339Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32DivU(Node* left, Node* right,
2340 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2341 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2342 return graph()->NewNode(m->Uint32Div(), left, right,
2343 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapDivByZero, right, position));
2344}
2345
2346Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32RemU(Node* left, Node* right,
2347 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2348 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2349 return graph()->NewNode(m->Uint32Mod(), left, right,
2350 ZeroCheck32(wasm::kTrapRemByZero, right, position));
2351}
2352
2353Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32AsmjsDivS(Node* left, Node* right) {
2354 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2355
2356 Int32Matcher mr(right);
2357 if (mr.HasValue()) {
2358 if (mr.Value() == 0) {
2359 return mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
2360 } else if (mr.Value() == -1) {
2361 // The result is the negation of the left input.
2362 return graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Sub(), mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0), left);
2363 }
2364 return graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Div(), left, right, control());
2365 }
2366
2367 // asm.js semantics return 0 on divide or mod by zero.
2368 if (m->Int32DivIsSafe()) {
2369 // The hardware instruction does the right thing (e.g. arm).
2370 return graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Div(), left, right, graph()->start());
2371 }
2372
2373 // Check denominator for zero.
2374 Diamond z(
2375 graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2376 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Equal(), right, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0)),
2377 BranchHint::kFalse);
2378
2379 // Check numerator for -1. (avoid minint / -1 case).
2380 Diamond n(
2381 graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2382 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Equal(), right, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(-1)),
2383 BranchHint::kFalse);
2384
2385 Node* div = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Div(), left, right, z.if_false);
2386 Node* neg =
2387 graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Sub(), mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0), left);
2388
2389 return n.Phi(
2390 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, neg,
2391 z.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0), div));
2392}
2393
2394Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32AsmjsRemS(Node* left, Node* right) {
2395 CommonOperatorBuilder* c = mcgraph()->common();
2396 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2397 Node* const zero = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
2398
2399 Int32Matcher mr(right);
2400 if (mr.HasValue()) {
2401 if (mr.Value() == 0 || mr.Value() == -1) {
2402 return zero;
2403 }
2404 return graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Mod(), left, right, control());
2405 }
2406
2407 // General case for signed integer modulus, with optimization for (unknown)
2408 // power of 2 right hand side.
2409 //
2410 // if 0 < right then
2411 // msk = right - 1
2412 // if right & msk != 0 then
2413 // left % right
2414 // else
2415 // if left < 0 then
2416 // -(-left & msk)
2417 // else
2418 // left & msk
2419 // else
2420 // if right < -1 then
2421 // left % right
2422 // else
2423 // zero
2424 //
2425 // Note: We do not use the Diamond helper class here, because it really hurts
2426 // readability with nested diamonds.
2427 Node* const minus_one = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(-1);
2428
2429 const Operator* const merge_op = c->Merge(2);
2430 const Operator* const phi_op = c->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2);
2431
2432 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32LessThan(), zero, right);
2433 Node* branch0 =
2434 graph()->NewNode(c->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check0, graph()->start());
2435
2436 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfTrue(), branch0);
2437 Node* true0;
2438 {
2439 Node* msk = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Add(), right, minus_one);
2440
2441 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32And(), right, msk);
2442 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(c->Branch(), check1, if_true0);
2443
2444 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfTrue(), branch1);
2445 Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Mod(), left, right, if_true1);
2446
2447 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfFalse(), branch1);
2448 Node* false1;
2449 {
2450 Node* check2 = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32LessThan(), left, zero);
2451 Node* branch2 =
2452 graph()->NewNode(c->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check2, if_false1);
2453
2454 Node* if_true2 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfTrue(), branch2);
2455 Node* true2 = graph()->NewNode(
2456 m->Int32Sub(), zero,
2457 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32And(),
2458 graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Sub(), zero, left), msk));
2459
2460 Node* if_false2 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfFalse(), branch2);
2461 Node* false2 = graph()->NewNode(m->Word32And(), left, msk);
2462
2463 if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true2, if_false2);
2464 false1 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true2, false2, if_false1);
2465 }
2466
2467 if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
2468 true0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_true0);
2469 }
2470
2471 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfFalse(), branch0);
2472 Node* false0;
2473 {
2474 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32LessThan(), right, minus_one);
2475 Node* branch1 =
2476 graph()->NewNode(c->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check1, if_false0);
2477
2478 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfTrue(), branch1);
2479 Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Mod(), left, right, if_true1);
2480
2481 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(c->IfFalse(), branch1);
2482 Node* false1 = zero;
2483
2484 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
2485 false0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_false0);
2486 }
2487
2488 Node* merge0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true0, if_false0);
2489 return graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true0, false0, merge0);
2490}
2491
2492Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32AsmjsDivU(Node* left, Node* right) {
2493 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2494 // asm.js semantics return 0 on divide or mod by zero.
2495 if (m->Uint32DivIsSafe()) {
2496 // The hardware instruction does the right thing (e.g. arm).
2497 return graph()->NewNode(m->Uint32Div(), left, right, graph()->start());
2498 }
2499
2500 // Explicit check for x % 0.
2501 Diamond z(
2502 graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2503 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Equal(), right, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0)),
2504 BranchHint::kFalse);
2505
2506 return z.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0),
2507 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Uint32Div(), left, right,
2508 z.if_false));
2509}
2510
2511Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32AsmjsRemU(Node* left, Node* right) {
2512 MachineOperatorBuilder* m = mcgraph()->machine();
2513 // asm.js semantics return 0 on divide or mod by zero.
2514 // Explicit check for x % 0.
2515 Diamond z(
2516 graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2517 graph()->NewNode(m->Word32Equal(), right, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0)),
2518 BranchHint::kFalse);
2519
2520 Node* rem = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Uint32Mod(), left, right,
2521 z.if_false);
2522 return z.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0),
2523 rem);
2524}
2525
2526Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64DivS(Node* left, Node* right,
2527 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2528 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
2529 return BuildDiv64Call(left, right, ExternalReference::wasm_int64_div(),
2530 MachineType::Int64(), wasm::kTrapDivByZero, position);
2531 }
2532 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapDivByZero, right, position);
2533 Node* before = control();
2534 Node* denom_is_m1;
2535 Node* denom_is_not_m1;
2536 BranchExpectFalse(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word64Equal(), right,
2537 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(-1)),
2538 &denom_is_m1, &denom_is_not_m1);
2539 SetControl(denom_is_m1);
2540 TrapIfEq64(wasm::kTrapDivUnrepresentable, left,
2541 std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min(), position);
2542 if (control() != denom_is_m1) {
2543 SetControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Merge(2), denom_is_not_m1,
2544 control()));
2545 } else {
2546 SetControl(before);
2547 }
2548 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Int64Div(), left, right,
2549 control());
2550}
2551
2552Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64RemS(Node* left, Node* right,
2553 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2554 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
2555 return BuildDiv64Call(left, right, ExternalReference::wasm_int64_mod(),
2556 MachineType::Int64(), wasm::kTrapRemByZero, position);
2557 }
2558 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapRemByZero, right, position);
2559 Diamond d(mcgraph()->graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
2560 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word64Equal(), right,
2561 mcgraph()->Int64Constant(-1)));
2562
2563 d.Chain(control());
2564
2565 Node* rem = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Int64Mod(), left, right,
2566 d.if_false);
2567
2568 return d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord64, mcgraph()->Int64Constant(0),
2569 rem);
2570}
2571
2572Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64DivU(Node* left, Node* right,
2573 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2574 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
2575 return BuildDiv64Call(left, right, ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_div(),
2576 MachineType::Int64(), wasm::kTrapDivByZero, position);
2577 }
2578 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Uint64Div(), left, right,
2579 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapDivByZero, right, position));
2580}
2581Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64RemU(Node* left, Node* right,
2582 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2583 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) {
2584 return BuildDiv64Call(left, right, ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_mod(),
2585 MachineType::Int64(), wasm::kTrapRemByZero, position);
2586 }
2587 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Uint64Mod(), left, right,
2588 ZeroCheck64(wasm::kTrapRemByZero, right, position));
2589}
2590
2591Node* WasmGraphBuilder::GetBuiltinPointerTarget(int builtin_id) {
2592 static_assert(std::is_same<Smi, BuiltinPtr>(), "BuiltinPtr must be Smi");
2593 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(builtin_id));
2594}
2595
2596Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildDiv64Call(Node* left, Node* right,
2597 ExternalReference ref,
2598 MachineType result_type,
2599 wasm::TrapReason trap_zero,
2600 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2601 Node* stack_slot =
2602 StoreArgsInStackSlot({{MachineRepresentation::kWord64, left},
2603 {MachineRepresentation::kWord64, right}});
2604
2605 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
2606 MachineSignature sig(1, 1, sig_types);
2607
2608 Node* function = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->ExternalConstant(ref));
2609 Node* call = BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot);
2610
2611 ZeroCheck32(trap_zero, call, position);
2612 TrapIfEq32(wasm::kTrapDivUnrepresentable, call, -1, position);
2613 return SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(result_type),
2614 stack_slot, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0),
2615 effect(), control()));
2616}
2617
2618template <typename... Args>
2619Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCCall(MachineSignature* sig, Node* function,
2620 Args... args) {
2621 DCHECK_LE(sig->return_count(), 1)((void) 0);
2622 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof...(args), sig->parameter_count())((void) 0);
2623 Node* const call_args[] = {function, args..., effect(), control()};
2624
2625 auto call_descriptor =
2626 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(mcgraph()->zone(), sig);
2627
2628 const Operator* op = mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor);
2629 return SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(op, arraysize(call_args)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(call_args))), call_args));
2630}
2631
2632Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCallNode(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
2633 Vector<Node*> args,
2634 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2635 Node* instance_node, const Operator* op) {
2636 if (instance_node == nullptr) {
2637 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_node_)((void) 0);
2638 instance_node = instance_node_.get();
2639 }
2640 needs_stack_check_ = true;
2641 const size_t params = sig->parameter_count();
2642 const size_t extra = 3; // instance_node, effect, and control.
2643 const size_t count = 1 + params + extra;
2644
2645 // Reallocate the buffer to make space for extra inputs.
2646 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16 + extra> inputs(count);
2647 DCHECK_EQ(1 + params, args.size())((void) 0);
2648
2649 // Make room for the instance_node parameter at index 1, just after code.
2650 inputs[0] = args[0]; // code
2651 inputs[1] = instance_node;
2652 if (params > 0) memcpy(&inputs[2], &args[1], params * sizeof(Node*));
2653
2654 // Add effect and control inputs.
2655 inputs[params + 2] = effect();
2656 inputs[params + 3] = control();
2657
2658 Node* call = graph()->NewNode(op, static_cast<int>(count), inputs.begin());
2659 // Return calls have no effect output. Other calls are the new effect node.
2660 if (op->EffectOutputCount() > 0) SetEffect(call);
2661 DCHECK(position == wasm::kNoCodePosition || position > 0)((void) 0);
2662 if (position > 0) SetSourcePosition(call, position);
2663
2664 return call;
2665}
2666
2667Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildWasmCall(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
2668 Vector<Node*> args, Vector<Node*> rets,
2669 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2670 Node* instance_node,
2671 UseRetpoline use_retpoline) {
2672 auto call_descriptor =
2673 GetWasmCallDescriptor(mcgraph()->zone(), sig, use_retpoline);
2674 const Operator* op = mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor);
2675 Node* call = BuildCallNode(sig, args, position, instance_node, op);
2676
2677 size_t ret_count = sig->return_count();
2678 if (ret_count == 0) return call; // No return value.
2679
2680 DCHECK_EQ(ret_count, rets.size())((void) 0);
2681 if (ret_count == 1) {
2682 // Only a single return value.
2683 rets[0] = call;
2684 } else {
2685 // Create projections for all return values.
2686 for (size_t i = 0; i < ret_count; i++) {
2687 rets[i] = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Projection(i), call,
2688 graph()->start());
2689 }
2690 }
2691 return call;
2692}
2693
2694Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildWasmReturnCall(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
2695 Vector<Node*> args,
2696 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2697 Node* instance_node,
2698 UseRetpoline use_retpoline) {
2699 auto call_descriptor =
2700 GetWasmCallDescriptor(mcgraph()->zone(), sig, use_retpoline);
2701 const Operator* op = mcgraph()->common()->TailCall(call_descriptor);
2702 Node* call = BuildCallNode(sig, args, position, instance_node, op);
2703
2704 MergeControlToEnd(mcgraph(), call);
2705
2706 return call;
2707}
2708
2709Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildImportCall(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
2710 Vector<Node*> args, Vector<Node*> rets,
2711 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2712 int func_index,
2713 IsReturnCall continuation) {
2714 // Load the imported function refs array from the instance.
2715 Node* imported_function_refs =
2716 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(ImportedFunctionRefs, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
2717 Node* ref_node =
2718 LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_PTR(imported_function_refs, func_index);
2719
2720 // Load the target from the imported_targets array at a known offset.
2721 Node* imported_targets =
2722 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(ImportedFunctionTargets, MachineType::Pointer());
2723 Node* target_node = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
2724 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::Pointer()), imported_targets,
2725 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(func_index * kSystemPointerSize), effect(),
2726 control()));
2727 args[0] = target_node;
2728 const UseRetpoline use_retpoline =
2729 untrusted_code_mitigations_ ? kRetpoline : kNoRetpoline;
2730
2731 switch (continuation) {
2732 case kCallContinues:
2733 return BuildWasmCall(sig, args, rets, position, ref_node, use_retpoline);
2734 case kReturnCall:
2735 DCHECK(rets.empty())((void) 0);
2736 return BuildWasmReturnCall(sig, args, position, ref_node, use_retpoline);
2737 }
2738}
2739
2740Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildImportCall(const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
2741 Vector<Node*> args, Vector<Node*> rets,
2742 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2743 Node* func_index,
2744 IsReturnCall continuation) {
2745 // Load the imported function refs array from the instance.
2746 Node* imported_function_refs =
2747 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(ImportedFunctionRefs, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
2748 // Access fixed array at {header_size - tag + func_index * kTaggedSize}.
2749 Node* imported_instances_data = graph()->NewNode(
2750 mcgraph()->machine()->IntAdd(), imported_function_refs,
2751 mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(
2752 wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(0)));
2753 Node* func_index_times_tagged_size = graph()->NewNode(
2754 mcgraph()->machine()->IntMul(), Uint32ToUintptr(func_index),
2755 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(kTaggedSize));
2756 Node* ref_node =
2757 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), imported_instances_data,
2758 func_index_times_tagged_size);
2759
2760 // Load the target from the imported_targets array at the offset of
2761 // {func_index}.
2762 Node* func_index_times_pointersize;
2763 if (kSystemPointerSize == kTaggedSize) {
2764 func_index_times_pointersize = func_index_times_tagged_size;
2765
2766 } else {
2767 DCHECK_EQ(kSystemPointerSize, kTaggedSize + kTaggedSize)((void) 0);
2768 func_index_times_pointersize = graph()->NewNode(
2769 mcgraph()->machine()->Int32Add(), func_index_times_tagged_size,
2770 func_index_times_tagged_size);
2771 }
2772 Node* imported_targets =
2773 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(ImportedFunctionTargets, MachineType::Pointer());
2774 Node* target_node = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
2775 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::Pointer()), imported_targets,
2776 func_index_times_pointersize, effect(), control()));
2777 args[0] = target_node;
2778 const UseRetpoline use_retpoline =
2779 untrusted_code_mitigations_ ? kRetpoline : kNoRetpoline;
2780
2781 switch (continuation) {
2782 case kCallContinues:
2783 return BuildWasmCall(sig, args, rets, position, ref_node, use_retpoline);
2784 case kReturnCall:
2785 DCHECK(rets.empty())((void) 0);
2786 return BuildWasmReturnCall(sig, args, position, ref_node, use_retpoline);
2787 }
2788}
2789
2790Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CallDirect(uint32_t index, Vector<Node*> args,
2791 Vector<Node*> rets,
2792 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2793 DCHECK_NULL(args[0])((void) 0);
2794 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = env_->module->functions[index].sig;
2795
2796 if (env_ && index < env_->module->num_imported_functions) {
2797 // Call to an imported function.
2798 return BuildImportCall(sig, args, rets, position, index, kCallContinues);
2799 }
2800
2801 // A direct call to a wasm function defined in this module.
2802 // Just encode the function index. This will be patched at instantiation.
2803 Address code = static_cast<Address>(index);
2804 args[0] = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(code, RelocInfo::WASM_CALL);
2805
2806 return BuildWasmCall(sig, args, rets, position, nullptr, kNoRetpoline);
2807}
2808
2809Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CallIndirect(uint32_t table_index, uint32_t sig_index,
2810 Vector<Node*> args, Vector<Node*> rets,
2811 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2812 return BuildIndirectCall(table_index, sig_index, args, rets, position,
2813 kCallContinues);
2814}
2815
2816void WasmGraphBuilder::LoadIndirectFunctionTable(uint32_t table_index,
2817 Node** ift_size,
2818 Node** ift_sig_ids,
2819 Node** ift_targets,
2820 Node** ift_instances) {
2821 if (table_index == 0) {
2822 *ift_size =
2823 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(IndirectFunctionTableSize, MachineType::Uint32());
2824 *ift_sig_ids = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(IndirectFunctionTableSigIds,
2825 MachineType::Pointer());
2826 *ift_targets = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(IndirectFunctionTableTargets,
2827 MachineType::Pointer());
2828 *ift_instances = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(IndirectFunctionTableRefs,
2829 MachineType::TaggedPointer());
2830 return;
2831 }
2832
2833 Node* ift_tables =
2834 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(IndirectFunctionTables, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
2835 Node* ift_table = LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(ift_tables, table_index);
2836
2837 *ift_size = gasm_->Load(
2838 MachineType::Int32(), ift_table,
2839 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmIndirectFunctionTable::kSizeOffset));
2840
2841 *ift_sig_ids = gasm_->Load(
2842 MachineType::Pointer(), ift_table,
2843 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmIndirectFunctionTable::kSigIdsOffset));
2844
2845 *ift_targets = gasm_->Load(
2846 MachineType::Pointer(), ift_table,
2847 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmIndirectFunctionTable::kTargetsOffset));
2848
2849 *ift_instances = gasm_->Load(
2850 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), ift_table,
2851 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmIndirectFunctionTable::kRefsOffset));
2852}
2853
2854Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildIndirectCall(uint32_t table_index,
2855 uint32_t sig_index,
2856 Vector<Node*> args,
2857 Vector<Node*> rets,
2858 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
2859 IsReturnCall continuation) {
2860 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(args[0])((void) 0);
2861 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(env_)((void) 0);
2862
2863 // First we have to load the table.
2864 Node* ift_size;
2865 Node* ift_sig_ids;
2866 Node* ift_targets;
2867 Node* ift_instances;
2868 LoadIndirectFunctionTable(table_index, &ift_size, &ift_sig_ids, &ift_targets,
2869 &ift_instances);
2870
2871 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = env_->module->signature(sig_index);
2872
2873 MachineOperatorBuilder* machine = mcgraph()->machine();
2874 Node* key = args[0];
2875
2876 // Bounds check against the table size.
2877 Node* in_bounds = graph()->NewNode(machine->Uint32LessThan(), key, ift_size);
2878 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapFuncInvalid, in_bounds, position);
2879
2880 // Mask the key to prevent SSCA.
2881 if (untrusted_code_mitigations_) {
2882 // mask = ((key - size) & ~key) >> 31
2883 Node* neg_key =
2884 graph()->NewNode(machine->Word32Xor(), key, Int32Constant(-1));
2885 Node* masked_diff = graph()->NewNode(
2886 machine->Word32And(),
2887 graph()->NewNode(machine->Int32Sub(), key, ift_size), neg_key);
2888 Node* mask =
2889 graph()->NewNode(machine->Word32Sar(), masked_diff, Int32Constant(31));
2890 key = graph()->NewNode(machine->Word32And(), key, mask);
2891 }
2892
2893 Node* int32_scaled_key = Uint32ToUintptr(
2894 graph()->NewNode(machine->Word32Shl(), key, Int32Constant(2)));
2895
2896 // Check that the dynamic type of the function is a subtype of its static
2897 // (table) type. Currently, the only subtyping between function types is
2898 // $t <: funcref for all $t: function_type.
2899 // TODO(7748): Expand this with function subtyping.
2900 if (env_->module->tables[table_index].type == wasm::kWasmFuncRef) {
2901 int32_t expected_sig_id = env_->module->signature_ids[sig_index];
2902
2903 Node* loaded_sig = SetEffect(
2904 graph()->NewNode(machine->Load(MachineType::Int32()), ift_sig_ids,
2905 int32_scaled_key, effect(), control()));
2906 Node* sig_match = graph()->NewNode(machine->WordEqual(), loaded_sig,
2907 Int32Constant(expected_sig_id));
2908
2909 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapFuncSigMismatch, sig_match, position);
2910 }
2911
2912 Node* tagged_scaled_key;
2913 if (kTaggedSize == kInt32Size) {
2914 tagged_scaled_key = int32_scaled_key;
2915 } else {
2916 DCHECK_EQ(kTaggedSize, kInt32Size * 2)((void) 0);
2917 tagged_scaled_key = graph()->NewNode(machine->Int32Add(), int32_scaled_key,
2918 int32_scaled_key);
2919 }
2920
2921 Node* target_instance = gasm_->Load(
2922 MachineType::TaggedPointer(),
2923 graph()->NewNode(machine->IntAdd(), ift_instances, tagged_scaled_key),
2924 wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(0));
2925
2926 Node* intptr_scaled_key;
2927 if (kSystemPointerSize == kTaggedSize) {
2928 intptr_scaled_key = tagged_scaled_key;
2929 } else {
2930 DCHECK_EQ(kSystemPointerSize, kTaggedSize + kTaggedSize)((void) 0);
2931 intptr_scaled_key = graph()->NewNode(machine->Int32Add(), tagged_scaled_key,
2932 tagged_scaled_key);
2933 }
2934
2935 Node* target = SetEffect(
2936 graph()->NewNode(machine->Load(MachineType::Pointer()), ift_targets,
2937 intptr_scaled_key, effect(), control()));
2938
2939 args[0] = target;
2940 const UseRetpoline use_retpoline =
2941 untrusted_code_mitigations_ ? kRetpoline : kNoRetpoline;
2942
2943 switch (continuation) {
2944 case kCallContinues:
2945 return BuildWasmCall(sig, args, rets, position, target_instance,
2946 use_retpoline);
2947 case kReturnCall:
2948 return BuildWasmReturnCall(sig, args, position, target_instance,
2949 use_retpoline);
2950 }
2951}

2953Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildLoadFunctionDataFromExportedFunction(
2954 Node* closure) {
2955 Node* shared = gasm_->Load(
2956 MachineType::AnyTagged(), closure,
2957 wasm::ObjectAccess::SharedFunctionInfoOffsetInTaggedJSFunction());
2958 return gasm_->Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), shared,
2959 SharedFunctionInfo::kFunctionDataOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
2960}

2965 MachineType::TaggedSigned(), function_data,
2966 WasmExportedFunctionData::kJumpTableOffsetOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
2967 return BuildChangeSmiToIntPtr(jump_table_offset_smi);

2979Node* HasInstanceType(WasmGraphAssembler* gasm, Node* object,
2980 InstanceType type) {
2981 Node* map = gasm->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), object,
2982 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(HeapObject::kMapOffset));
2983 Node* instance_type =
2984 gasm->Load(MachineType::Uint16(), map,
2985 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
2986 return gasm->Word32Equal(instance_type, gasm->Int32Constant(type));
2987}
2988
2989Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCallRef(uint32_t sig_index, Vector<Node*> args,
2990 Vector<Node*> rets,
2991 CheckForNull null_check,
2992 IsReturnCall continuation,
2993 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
2994 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
2995 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapNullDereference, gasm_->WordEqual(args[0], RefNull()),
2996 position);
2997 }
2998
2999 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = env_->module->signature(sig_index);
3000
3001 Node* function_data = BuildLoadFunctionDataFromExportedFunction(args[0]);
3002
3003 Node* is_js_function =
3004 HasInstanceType(gasm_.get(), function_data, WASM_JS_FUNCTION_DATA_TYPE);
3005
3006 auto js_label = gasm_->MakeLabel();
3007 auto end_label = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer,
3008 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3009
3010 gasm_->GotoIf(is_js_function, &js_label);
3011
3012 {
3013 // Call to a WasmExportedFunction.
3014 // Load instance object corresponding to module where callee is defined.
3015 Node* callee_instance =
3016 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), function_data,
3017 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
3018 WasmExportedFunctionData::kInstanceOffset));
3019
3020 Node* function_index =
3021 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), function_data,
3022 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
3023 WasmExportedFunctionData::kFunctionIndexOffset));
3024
3025 auto imported_label = gasm_->MakeLabel();
3026
3027 // Check if callee is a locally defined or imported function it its module.
3028 Node* imported_function_refs =
3029 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), callee_instance,
3030 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
3031 WasmInstanceObject::kImportedFunctionRefsOffset));
3032 Node* imported_functions_num =
3033 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), imported_function_refs,
3034 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(FixedArray::kLengthOffset));
3035 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->SmiLessThan(function_index, imported_functions_num),
3036 &imported_label);
3037 {
3038 // Function locally defined in module.
3039 Node* jump_table_start =
3040 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), callee_instance,
3041 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
3042 WasmInstanceObject::kJumpTableStartOffset));
3043 Node* jump_table_offset =
3044 BuildLoadJumpTableOffsetFromExportedFunctionData(function_data);
3045 Node* jump_table_slot =
3046 gasm_->IntAdd(jump_table_start, jump_table_offset);
3047
3048 gasm_->Goto(&end_label, jump_table_slot,
3049 callee_instance /* Unused, dummy value */);
3050 }
3051
3052 {
3053 // Function imported to module.
3054 // TODO(9495): Make sure it works with functions imported from other
3055 // modules. Currently, this will never happen: Since functions have to be
3056 // tunneled through JS, and we currently do not have a JS API to pass
3057 // specific function types, we habe to export/import function references
3058 // as funcref. Then, we cannot cast down to the type of the function,
3059 // because we do not have access to the defining module's types. This
3060 // could be fixed either by building a richer JS API, or by implementing
3061 // the type import proposal. That said, this code should work for those
3062 // cases too.
3063 gasm_->Bind(&imported_label);
3064
3065 Node* imported_instance = gasm_->Load(
3066 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), imported_function_refs,
3067 gasm_->Int32Add(
3068 gasm_->Int32Mul(BuildChangeSmiToInt32(function_index),
3069 gasm_->Int32Constant(kTaggedSize)),
3070 gasm_->Int32Constant(FixedArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag)));
3071
3072 Node* imported_function_targets =
3073 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), callee_instance,
3074 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
3075 WasmInstanceObject::kImportedFunctionTargetsOffset));
3076
3077 Node* target_node =
3078 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), imported_function_targets,
3079 gasm_->IntMul(BuildChangeSmiToIntPtr(function_index),
3080 gasm_->IntPtrConstant(kSystemPointerSize)));
3081
3082 gasm_->Goto(&end_label, target_node, imported_instance);
3083 }
3084 }
3085
3086 {
3087 // Call to a WasmJSFunction.
3088 // The call target is the wasm-to-js wrapper code.
3089 gasm_->Bind(&js_label);
3090 // TODO(7748): Implement.
3091 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapUnreachable, gasm_->Int32Constant(1), position);
3092 gasm_->Goto(&end_label, args[0], RefNull() /* Dummy value */);
3093 }
3094
3095 gasm_->Bind(&end_label);
3096
3097 args[0] = end_label.PhiAt(0);
3098 Node* instance_node = end_label.PhiAt(1);
3099
3100 const UseRetpoline use_retpoline =
3101 untrusted_code_mitigations_ ? kRetpoline : kNoRetpoline;
3102
3103 Node* call = continuation == kCallContinues
3104 ? BuildWasmCall(sig, args, rets, position, instance_node,
3105 use_retpoline)
3106 : BuildWasmReturnCall(sig, args, position, instance_node,
3107 use_retpoline);
3108 return call;
3109}

3112 Vector<Node*> rets,
3113 WasmGraphBuilder::CheckForNull null_check,
3114 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3115 return BuildCallRef(sig_index, args, rets, null_check,
3116 IsReturnCall::kCallContinues, position);
3117}

3119Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ReturnCallRef(uint32_t sig_index, Vector<Node*> args,
3120 WasmGraphBuilder::CheckForNull null_check,
3121 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {

3125
3126Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ReturnCall(uint32_t index, Vector<Node*> args,
3127 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3128 DCHECK_NULL(args[0])((void) 0);
3129 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = env_->module->functions[index].sig;
3130
3131 if (env_ && index < env_->module->num_imported_functions) {
3132 // Return Call to an imported function.
3133 return BuildImportCall(sig, args, {}, position, index, kReturnCall);
3134 }
3135
3136 // A direct tail call to a wasm function defined in this module.
3137 // Just encode the function index. This will be patched during code
3138 // generation.
3139 Address code = static_cast<Address>(index);
3140 args[0] = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(code, RelocInfo::WASM_CALL);
3141
3142 return BuildWasmReturnCall(sig, args, position, nullptr, kNoRetpoline);
3143}

3149 return BuildIndirectCall(table_index, sig_index, args, {}, position,
3150 kReturnCall);

3153Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnNull(Node* ref_object, Node** null_node,
3154 Node** non_null_node) {
3155 BranchExpectFalse(gasm_->WordEqual(ref_object, RefNull()), null_node,
3156 non_null_node);
3157 // Return value is not used, but we need it for compatibility
3158 // with graph-builder-interface.
3159 return nullptr;
3160}
3161
3162Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI32Rol(Node* left, Node* right) {
3163 // Implement Rol by Ror since TurboFan does not have Rol opcode.
3164 // TODO(weiliang): support Word32Rol opcode in TurboFan.
3165 Int32Matcher m(right);
3166 if (m.HasValue()) {
3167 return Binop(wasm::kExprI32Ror, left,
3168 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(32 - (m.Value() & 0x1F)));
3169 } else {
3170 return Binop(wasm::kExprI32Ror, left,
3171 Binop(wasm::kExprI32Sub, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(32), right));
3172 }
3173}
3174
3175Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildI64Rol(Node* left, Node* right) {
3176 // Implement Rol by Ror since TurboFan does not have Rol opcode.
3177 // TODO(weiliang): support Word64Rol opcode in TurboFan.
3178 Int64Matcher m(right);
3179 Node* inv_right =
3180 m.HasValue()
3181 ? mcgraph()->Int64Constant(64 - (m.Value() & 0x3F))
3182 : Binop(wasm::kExprI64Sub, mcgraph()->Int64Constant(64), right);
3183 return Binop(wasm::kExprI64Ror, left, inv_right);
3184}
3185
3186Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Invert(Node* node) {
3187 return Unop(wasm::kExprI32Eqz, node);
3188}

3205Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildChangeInt32ToSmi(Node* value) {
3206 // With pointer compression, only the lower 32 bits are used.
3207 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOLfalse) {
3208 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word32Shl(), value,
3209 BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32());
3210 }
3211 value = BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(value);
3212 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->WordShl(), value,
3213 BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant());
3214}
3215
3216Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildChangeUint31ToSmi(Node* value) {
3217 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOLfalse) {
3218 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word32Shl(), value,
3219 BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32());
3220 }
3221 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->WordShl(),
3222 Uint32ToUintptr(value), BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant());
3223}
3224
3225Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant() {
3226 return mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize);
3227}
3228
3229Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32() {
3230 return mcgraph()->Int32Constant(kSmiShiftSize + kSmiTagSize);
3231}
3232
3233Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildChangeSmiToInt32(Node* value) {
3234 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOLfalse) {
3235 value =
3236 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateInt64ToInt32(), value);
3237 value = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word32Sar(), value,
3238 BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32());
3239 } else {
3240 value = BuildChangeSmiToIntPtr(value);
3241 value = BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(value);
3242 }
3243 return value;
3244}
3245
3246Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildChangeSmiToIntPtr(Node* value) {
3247 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOLfalse) {
3248 value = BuildChangeSmiToInt32(value);
3249 return BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(value);
3250 }
3251 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->WordSar(), value,
3252 BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant());
3253}
3254
3255Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildConvertUint32ToSmiWithSaturation(Node* value,
3256 uint32_t maxval) {
3257 DCHECK(Smi::IsValid(maxval))((void) 0);
3258 Node* max = Uint32Constant(maxval);
3259 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Uint32LessThanOrEqual(),
3260 value, max);
3261 Node* valsmi = BuildChangeUint31ToSmi(value);
3262 Node* maxsmi = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(maxval));
3263 Diamond d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), check, BranchHint::kTrue);
3264 d.Chain(control());
3265 return d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, valsmi, maxsmi);
3266}

3268void WasmGraphBuilder::InitInstanceCache(
3269 WasmInstanceCacheNodes* instance_cache) {
3270 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_node_)((void) 0);
3271
3272 // Load the memory start.
3273 instance_cache->mem_start =
3274 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(MemoryStart, MachineType::UintPtr());
3275
3276 // Load the memory size.
3277 instance_cache->mem_size =
3278 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(MemorySize, MachineType::UintPtr());
3279
3280 if (untrusted_code_mitigations_) {
3281 // Load the memory mask.
3282 instance_cache->mem_mask =
3283 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(MemoryMask, MachineType::UintPtr());
3284 } else {
3285 // Explicitly set to nullptr to ensure a SEGV when we try to use it.
3286 instance_cache->mem_mask = nullptr;
3287 }
3288}

3290void WasmGraphBuilder::PrepareInstanceCacheForLoop(
3291 WasmInstanceCacheNodes* instance_cache, Node* control) {
3292#define INTRODUCE_PHI(field, rep) \
3293 instance_cache->field = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Phi(rep, 1), \
3294 instance_cache->field, control);
3295
3296 INTRODUCE_PHI(mem_start, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
3297 INTRODUCE_PHI(mem_size, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
3298 if (untrusted_code_mitigations_) {
3299 INTRODUCE_PHI(mem_mask, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
3300 }
3301
3302#undef INTRODUCE_PHI
3303}

3305void WasmGraphBuilder::NewInstanceCacheMerge(WasmInstanceCacheNodes* to,
3306 WasmInstanceCacheNodes* from,
3307 Node* merge) {
3308#define INTRODUCE_PHI(field, rep) \
3309 if (to->field != from->field) { \
3310 Node* vals[] = {to->field, from->field, merge}; \
3311 to->field = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Phi(rep, 2), 3, vals); \
3312 }
3313
3314 INTRODUCE_PHI(mem_start, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
3315 INTRODUCE_PHI(mem_size, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3316 if (untrusted_code_mitigations_) {
3317 INTRODUCE_PHI(mem_mask, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3318 }
3319
3320#undef INTRODUCE_PHI
3321}

3323void WasmGraphBuilder::MergeInstanceCacheInto(WasmInstanceCacheNodes* to,
3324 WasmInstanceCacheNodes* from,
3325 Node* merge) {
3326 to->mem_size = CreateOrMergeIntoPhi(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
3327 merge, to->mem_size, from->mem_size);
3328 to->mem_start = CreateOrMergeIntoPhi(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
3329 merge, to->mem_start, from->mem_start);
3330 if (untrusted_code_mitigations_) {
3331 to->mem_mask = CreateOrMergeIntoPhi(MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
3332 merge, to->mem_mask, from->mem_mask);
3333 }
3334}
3335
3336Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CreateOrMergeIntoPhi(MachineRepresentation rep,
3337 Node* merge, Node* tnode,
3338 Node* fnode) {
3339 if (IsPhiWithMerge(tnode, merge)) {
3340 AppendToPhi(tnode, fnode);
3341 } else if (tnode != fnode) {
3342 // Note that it is not safe to use {Buffer} here since this method is used
3343 // via {CheckForException} while the {Buffer} is in use by another method.
3344 uint32_t count = merge->InputCount();
3345 // + 1 for the merge node.
3346 base::SmallVector<Node*, 9> inputs(count + 1);
3347 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < count - 1; j++) inputs[j] = tnode;
3348 inputs[count - 1] = fnode;
3349 inputs[count] = merge;
3350 tnode = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Phi(rep, count), count + 1,
3351 inputs.begin());
3352 }
3353 return tnode;
3354}
3355
3356Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CreateOrMergeIntoEffectPhi(Node* merge, Node* tnode,
3357 Node* fnode) {
3358 if (IsPhiWithMerge(tnode, merge)) {
3359 AppendToPhi(tnode, fnode);
3360 } else if (tnode != fnode) {
3361 // Note that it is not safe to use {Buffer} here since this method is used
3362 // via {CheckForException} while the {Buffer} is in use by another method.
3363 uint32_t count = merge->InputCount();
3364 // + 1 for the merge node.
3365 base::SmallVector<Node*, 9> inputs(count + 1);
3366 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < count - 1; j++) {
3367 inputs[j] = tnode;
3368 }
3369 inputs[count - 1] = fnode;
3370 inputs[count] = merge;
3371 tnode = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
3372 inputs.begin());
3373 }
3374 return tnode;
3375}

3395Node* WasmGraphBuilder::GetImportedMutableGlobals() {
3396 if (imported_mutable_globals_ == nullptr) {
3397 // Load imported_mutable_globals_ from the instance object at runtime.
3398 imported_mutable_globals_ = graph()->NewNode(
3399 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::UintPtr()),
3400 instance_node_.get(),
3401 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(
3402 WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_OFFSET(ImportedMutableGlobals)),
3403 graph()->start(), graph()->start());
3404 }
3405 return imported_mutable_globals_.get();
3406}
3407
3408void WasmGraphBuilder::GetGlobalBaseAndOffset(MachineType mem_type,
3409 const wasm::WasmGlobal& global,
3410 Node** base_node,
3411 Node** offset_node) {
3412 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_node_)((void) 0);
3413 if (global.mutability && global.imported) {
3414 *base_node = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
3415 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::UintPtr()),
3416 GetImportedMutableGlobals(),
3417 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(global.index * sizeof(Address)), effect(),
3418 control()));
3419 *offset_node = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
3420 } else {
3421 if (globals_start_ == nullptr) {
3422 // Load globals_start from the instance object at runtime.
3423 // TODO(wasm): we currently generate only one load of the {globals_start}
3424 // start per graph, which means it can be placed anywhere by the
3425 // scheduler. This is legal because the globals_start should never change.
3426 // However, in some cases (e.g. if the instance object is already in a
3427 // register), it is slightly more efficient to reload this value from the
3428 // instance object. Since this depends on register allocation, it is not
3429 // possible to express in the graph, and would essentially constitute a
3430 // "mem2reg" optimization in TurboFan.
3431 globals_start_ = graph()->NewNode(
3432 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::UintPtr()),
3433 instance_node_.get(),
3434 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_OFFSET(GlobalsStart)),
3435 graph()->start(), graph()->start());
3436 }
3437 *base_node = globals_start_.get();
3438 *offset_node = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(global.offset);
3439
3440 if (mem_type == MachineType::Simd128() && global.offset != 0) {
3441 // TODO(titzer,bbudge): code generation for SIMD memory offsets is broken.
3442 *base_node = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->IntAdd(), *base_node,
3443 *offset_node);
3444 *offset_node = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
3445 }
3446 }
3447}
3448
3449void WasmGraphBuilder::GetBaseAndOffsetForImportedMutableExternRefGlobal(
3450 const wasm::WasmGlobal& global, Node** base, Node** offset) {
3451 // Load the base from the ImportedMutableGlobalsBuffer of the instance.
3452 Node* buffers = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(ImportedMutableGlobalsBuffers,
3453 MachineType::TaggedPointer());
3454 *base = LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(buffers, global.index);
3455
3456 // For the offset we need the index of the global in the buffer, and then
3457 // calculate the actual offset from the index. Load the index from the
3458 // ImportedMutableGlobals array of the instance.
3459 Node* index = SetEffect(
3460 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::UintPtr()),
3461 GetImportedMutableGlobals(),
3462 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(global.index * sizeof(Address)),
3463 effect(), control()));
3464
3465 // From the index, calculate the actual offset in the FixeArray. This
3466 // is kHeaderSize + (index * kTaggedSize). kHeaderSize can be acquired with
3467 // wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(0).
3468 Node* index_times_tagged_size =
3469 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->IntMul(), Uint32ToUintptr(index),
3470 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(kTaggedSize));
3471 *offset = graph()->NewNode(
3472 mcgraph()->machine()->IntAdd(), index_times_tagged_size,
3473 mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(
3474 wasm::ObjectAccess::ElementOffsetInTaggedFixedArray(0)));
3475}
3476
3477Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MemBuffer(uint32_t offset) {
3478 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_cache_)((void) 0);
3479 Node* mem_start = instance_cache_->mem_start;
3480 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mem_start)((void) 0);
3481 if (offset == 0) return mem_start;
3482 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->IntAdd(), mem_start,
3483 mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(offset));
3484}
3485
3486Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CurrentMemoryPages() {
3487 // CurrentMemoryPages can not be called from asm.js.
3488 DCHECK_EQ(wasm::kWasmOrigin, env_->module->origin)((void) 0);
3489 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_cache_)((void) 0);
3490 Node* mem_size = instance_cache_->mem_size;
3491 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mem_size)((void) 0);
3492 Node* result =
3493 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->WordShr(), mem_size,
3494 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(wasm::kWasmPageSizeLog2));
3495 result = BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(result);
3496 return result;
3497}
3498
3499// Only call this function for code which is not reused across instantiations,
3500// as we do not patch the embedded js_context.
3501Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::FunctionId f,
3502 Node* js_context,
3503 Node** parameters,
3504 int parameter_count) {
3505 const Runtime::Function* fun = Runtime::FunctionForId(f);
3506 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
3507 mcgraph()->zone(), f, fun->nargs, Operator::kNoProperties,
3508 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
3509 // The CEntryStub is loaded from the IsolateRoot so that generated code is
3510 // Isolate independent. At the moment this is only done for CEntryStub(1).
3511 Node* isolate_root = BuildLoadIsolateRoot();
3512 DCHECK_EQ(1, fun->result_size)((void) 0);
3513 auto centry_id =
3514 Builtins::kCEntry_Return1_DontSaveFPRegs_ArgvOnStack_NoBuiltinExit;
3515 Node* centry_stub = LOAD_FULL_POINTER(gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), isolate_root, IsolateData
::builtin_slot_offset(centry_id))
3516 isolate_root, IsolateData::builtin_slot_offset(centry_id))gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), isolate_root, IsolateData
::builtin_slot_offset(centry_id));
3517 // TODO(titzer): allow arbitrary number of runtime arguments
3518 // At the moment we only allow 5 parameters. If more parameters are needed,
3519 // increase this constant accordingly.
3520 static const int kMaxParams = 5;
3521 DCHECK_GE(kMaxParams, parameter_count)((void) 0);
3522 Node* inputs[kMaxParams + 6];
3523 int count = 0;
3524 inputs[count++] = centry_stub;
3525 for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count; i++) {
3526 inputs[count++] = parameters[i];
3527 }
3528 inputs[count++] =
3529 mcgraph()->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(f)); // ref
3530 inputs[count++] = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(fun->nargs); // arity
3531 inputs[count++] = js_context; // js_context
3532 inputs[count++] = effect();
3533 inputs[count++] = control();
3534
3535 Node* call = mcgraph()->graph()->NewNode(
3536 mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), count, inputs);
3537 SetEffect(call);
3538 return call;
3539}
3540
3541Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId f,
3542 Node** parameters,
3543 int parameter_count) {
3544 return BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(f, NoContextConstant(), parameters,
3545 parameter_count);
3546}

3548Node* WasmGraphBuilder::GlobalGet(uint32_t index) {
3549 const wasm::WasmGlobal& global = env_->module->globals[index];
3550 if (global.type.is_reference_type()) {
3551 if (global.mutability && global.imported) {
3552 Node* base = nullptr;
3553 Node* offset = nullptr;
3554 GetBaseAndOffsetForImportedMutableExternRefGlobal(global, &base, &offset);
3555 return gasm_->Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), base, offset);
3556 }
3557 Node* globals_buffer =
3558 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(TaggedGlobalsBuffer, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
3559 return LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(globals_buffer, global.offset);
3560 }
3561
3562 MachineType mem_type = global.type.machine_type();
3563 if (mem_type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
3564 has_simd_ = true;
3565 }
3566 Node* base = nullptr;
3567 Node* offset = nullptr;
3568 GetGlobalBaseAndOffset(mem_type, global, &base, &offset);
3569 Node* result = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
3570 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(mem_type), base, offset, effect(), control()));
3571#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
3572 result = BuildChangeEndiannessLoad(result, mem_type, global.type);
3573#endif
3574 return result;
3575}

3577Node* WasmGraphBuilder::GlobalSet(uint32_t index, Node* val) {
3578 const wasm::WasmGlobal& global = env_->module->globals[index];
3579 if (global.type.is_reference_type()) {
3580 if (global.mutability && global.imported) {
3581 Node* base = nullptr;
3582 Node* offset = nullptr;
3583 GetBaseAndOffsetForImportedMutableExternRefGlobal(global, &base, &offset);
3584
3585 return STORE_RAW_NODE_OFFSET(
3586 base, offset, val, MachineRepresentation::kTagged, kFullWriteBarrier);
3587 }
3588 Node* globals_buffer =
3589 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(TaggedGlobalsBuffer, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
3590 return STORE_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(globals_buffer, global.offset, val);
3591 }
3592
3593 MachineType mem_type = global.type.machine_type();
3594 if (mem_type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
3595 has_simd_ = true;
3596 }
3597 Node* base = nullptr;
3598 Node* offset = nullptr;
3599 GetGlobalBaseAndOffset(mem_type, global, &base, &offset);
3600 const Operator* op = mcgraph()->machine()->Store(
3601 StoreRepresentation(mem_type.representation(), kNoWriteBarrier));
3602#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
3603 val = BuildChangeEndiannessStore(val, mem_type.representation(), global.type);
3604#endif
3605 return SetEffect(
3606 graph()->NewNode(op, base, offset, val, effect(), control()));
3607}
