3636
3637Node* WasmGraphBuilder::CheckBoundsAndAlignment(
3638 uint8_t access_size, Node* index, uint32_t offset,
3639 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3640 // Atomic operations need bounds checks until the backend can emit protected
3641 // loads.
3642 index =
3643 BoundsCheckMem(access_size, index, offset, position, kNeedsBoundsCheck);
3644
3645 const uintptr_t align_mask = access_size - 1;
3646
3647 // Don't emit an alignment check if the index is a constant.
3648 // TODO(wasm): a constant match is also done above in {BoundsCheckMem}.
3649 UintPtrMatcher match(index);
3650 if (match.HasValue()) {
3651 uintptr_t effective_offset = match.Value() + offset;
3652 if ((effective_offset & align_mask) != 0) {
3653 // statically known to be unaligned; trap.
3654 TrapIfEq32(wasm::kTrapUnalignedAccess, Int32Constant(0), 0, position);
3655 }
3656 return index;
3657 }
3658
3659 // Unlike regular memory accesses, atomic memory accesses should trap if
3660 // the effective offset is misaligned.
3661 // TODO(wasm): this addition is redundant with one inserted by {MemBuffer}.
3662 Node* effective_offset = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->IntAdd(),
3663 MemBuffer(offset), index);
3664
3665 Node* cond = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->WordAnd(),
3666 effective_offset, IntPtrConstant(align_mask));
3667 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapUnalignedAccess,
3668 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word32Equal(), cond,
3669 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0)),
3670 position);
3671 return index;
3672}
3673
3674// Insert code to bounds check a memory access if necessary. Return the
3675// bounds-checked index, which is guaranteed to have (the equivalent of)
3676// {uintptr_t} representation.
3677Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BoundsCheckMem(uint8_t access_size, Node* index,
3678 uint32_t offset,
3679 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
3680 EnforceBoundsCheck enforce_check) {
3681 DCHECK_LE(1, access_size)((void) 0);
3682 index = Uint32ToUintptr(index);
3683 if (!FLAG_wasm_bounds_checks) return index;
3684
3685 if (use_trap_handler() && enforce_check == kCanOmitBoundsCheck) {
3686 return index;
3687 }
3688
3689 if (!base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(offset, access_size, env_->max_memory_size)) {
3690 // The access will be out of bounds, even for the largest memory.
3691 TrapIfEq32(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, Int32Constant(0), 0, position);
3692 return mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(0);
3693 }
3694 uint64_t end_offset = uint64_t{offset} + access_size - 1u;
3695 Node* end_offset_node = IntPtrConstant(end_offset);
3696
3697 // The accessed memory is [index + offset, index + end_offset].
3698 // Check that the last read byte (at {index + end_offset}) is in bounds.
3699 // 1) Check that {end_offset < mem_size}. This also ensures that we can safely
3700 // compute {effective_size} as {mem_size - end_offset)}.
3701 // {effective_size} is >= 1 if condition 1) holds.
3702 // 2) Check that {index + end_offset < mem_size} by
3703 // - computing {effective_size} as {mem_size - end_offset} and
3704 // - checking that {index < effective_size}.
3705
3706 auto m = mcgraph()->machine();
3707 Node* mem_size = instance_cache_->mem_size;
3708 if (end_offset >= env_->min_memory_size) {
3709 // The end offset is larger than the smallest memory.
3710 // Dynamically check the end offset against the dynamic memory size.
3711 Node* cond = graph()->NewNode(m->UintLessThan(), end_offset_node, mem_size);
3712 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, cond, position);
3713 } else {
3714 // The end offset is smaller than the smallest memory, so only one check is
3715 // required. Check to see if the index is also a constant.
3716 UintPtrMatcher match(index);
3717 if (match.HasValue()) {
3718 uintptr_t index_val = match.Value();
3719 if (index_val < env_->min_memory_size - end_offset) {
3720 // The input index is a constant and everything is statically within
3721 // bounds of the smallest possible memory.
3722 return index;
3723 }
3724 }
3725 }
3726
3727 // This produces a positive number, since {end_offset < min_size <= mem_size}.
3728 Node* effective_size =
3729 graph()->NewNode(m->IntSub(), mem_size, end_offset_node);
3730
3731 // Introduce the actual bounds check.
3732 Node* cond = graph()->NewNode(m->UintLessThan(), index, effective_size);
3733 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, cond, position);
3734
3735 if (untrusted_code_mitigations_) {
3736 // In the fallthrough case, condition the index with the memory mask.
3737 Node* mem_mask = instance_cache_->mem_mask;
3738 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mem_mask)((void) 0);
3739 index = graph()->NewNode(m->WordAnd(), index, mem_mask);
3740 }
3741 return index;
3742}
3743
3744Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BoundsCheckRange(Node* start, Node** size, Node* max,
3745 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3746 auto m = mcgraph()->machine();
3747 // The region we are trying to access is [start, start+size). If
3748 // {start} > {max}, none of this region is valid, so we trap. Otherwise,
3749 // there may be a subset of the region that is valid. {max - start} is the
3750 // maximum valid size, so if {max - start < size}, then the region is
3751 // partially out-of-bounds.
3752 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds,
3753 graph()->NewNode(m->Uint32LessThan(), max, start), position);
3754 Node* sub = graph()->NewNode(m->Int32Sub(), max, start);
3755 Node* fail = graph()->NewNode(m->Uint32LessThan(), sub, *size);
3756 Diamond d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), fail, BranchHint::kFalse);
3757 d.Chain(control());
3758 *size = d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, sub, *size);
3759 return fail;
3760}
3761
3762Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BoundsCheckMemRange(Node** start, Node** size,
3763 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3764 // TODO(binji): Support trap handler and no bounds check mode.
3765 Node* fail =
3766 BoundsCheckRange(*start, size, instance_cache_->mem_size, position);
3767 *start = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->IntAdd(), MemBuffer(0),
3768 Uint32ToUintptr(*start));
3769 return fail;
3770}
3771
3772const Operator* WasmGraphBuilder::GetSafeLoadOperator(int offset,
3773 wasm::ValueType type) {
3774 int alignment = offset % type.element_size_bytes();
3775 MachineType mach_type = type.machine_type();
3776 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOLfalse && mach_type.IsTagged()) {
3777 // We are loading tagged value from off-heap location, so we need to load
3778 // it as a full word otherwise we will not be able to decompress it.
3779 mach_type = MachineType::Pointer();
3780 }
3781 if (alignment == 0 || mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedLoadSupported(
3782 type.machine_representation())) {
3783 return mcgraph()->machine()->Load(mach_type);
3784 }
3785 return mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedLoad(mach_type);
3786}
3787
3788const Operator* WasmGraphBuilder::GetSafeStoreOperator(int offset,
3789 wasm::ValueType type) {
3790 int alignment = offset % type.element_size_bytes();
3791 MachineRepresentation rep = type.machine_representation();
3792 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOLfalse && IsAnyTagged(rep)) {
3793 // We are storing tagged value to off-heap location, so we need to store
3794 // it as a full word otherwise we will not be able to decompress it.
3795 rep = MachineType::PointerRepresentation();
3796 }
3797 if (alignment == 0 || mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedStoreSupported(rep)) {
3798 StoreRepresentation store_rep(rep, WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
3799 return mcgraph()->machine()->Store(store_rep);
3800 }
3801 UnalignedStoreRepresentation store_rep(rep);
3802 return mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedStore(store_rep);
3803}
3804
3805Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TraceFunctionEntry(wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3806 Node* call = BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::kWasmTraceEnter, nullptr, 0);
3807 SetSourcePosition(call, position);
3808 return call;
3809}
3810
3811Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TraceFunctionExit(Vector<Node*> vals,
3812 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3813 Node* info = gasm_->IntPtrConstant(0);
3814 size_t num_returns = vals.size();
3815 if (num_returns == 1) {
3816 wasm::ValueType return_type = sig_->GetReturn(0);
3817 MachineRepresentation rep = return_type.machine_representation();
3818 int size = ElementSizeInBytes(rep);
3819 info = gasm_->StackSlot(size, size);
3820
3821 gasm_->Store(StoreRepresentation(rep, kNoWriteBarrier), info,
3822 gasm_->Int32Constant(0), vals[0]);
3823 }
3824
3825 Node* call = BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::kWasmTraceExit, &info, 1);
3826 SetSourcePosition(call, position);
3827 return call;
3828}
3829
3830Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TraceMemoryOperation(bool is_store,
3831 MachineRepresentation rep,
3832 Node* index, uint32_t offset,
3833 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3834 int kAlign = 4; // Ensure that the LSB is 0, such that this looks like a Smi.
3835 TNode<RawPtrT> info =
3836 gasm_->StackSlot(sizeof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo), kAlign);
3837
3838 Node* address = gasm_->Int32Add(Int32Constant(offset), index);
3839 auto store = [&](int offset, MachineRepresentation rep, Node* data) {
3840 gasm_->Store(StoreRepresentation(rep, kNoWriteBarrier), info,
3841 gasm_->Int32Constant(offset), data);
3842 };
3843 // Store address, is_store, and mem_rep.
3844 store(offsetof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo, address)__builtin_offsetof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo, address),
3845 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, address);
3846 store(offsetof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo, is_store)__builtin_offsetof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo, is_store),
3847 MachineRepresentation::kWord8,
3848 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(is_store ? 1 : 0));
3849 store(offsetof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo, mem_rep)__builtin_offsetof(wasm::MemoryTracingInfo, mem_rep),
3850 MachineRepresentation::kWord8,
3851 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(rep)));
3852
3853 Node* args[] = {info};
3854 Node* call =
3855 BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::kWasmTraceMemory, args, arraysize(args)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(args))));
3856 SetSourcePosition(call, position);
3857 return call;
3858}
3859
3860namespace {
3861LoadTransformation GetLoadTransformation(
3862 MachineType memtype, wasm::LoadTransformationKind transform) {
3863 switch (transform) {
3864 case wasm::LoadTransformationKind::kSplat: {
3865 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
3866 return LoadTransformation::kS8x16LoadSplat;
3867 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
3868 return LoadTransformation::kS16x8LoadSplat;
3869 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
3870 return LoadTransformation::kS32x4LoadSplat;
3871 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
3872 return LoadTransformation::kS64x2LoadSplat;
3873 }
3874 break;
3875 }
3876 case wasm::LoadTransformationKind::kExtend: {
3877 if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
3878 return LoadTransformation::kI16x8Load8x8S;
3879 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
3880 return LoadTransformation::kI16x8Load8x8U;
3881 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
3882 return LoadTransformation::kI32x4Load16x4S;
3883 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
3884 return LoadTransformation::kI32x4Load16x4U;
3885 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
3886 return LoadTransformation::kI64x2Load32x2S;
3887 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
3888 return LoadTransformation::kI64x2Load32x2U;
3889 }
3890 break;
3891 }
3892 case wasm::LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend: {
3893 if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
3894 return LoadTransformation::kS128LoadMem32Zero;
3895 } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
3896 return LoadTransformation::kS128LoadMem64Zero;
3897 }
3898 }
3899 }
3900 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
3901}
3902
3903LoadKind GetLoadKind(MachineGraph* mcgraph, MachineType memtype,
3904 bool use_trap_handler) {
3905 if (memtype.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord8 ||
3906 mcgraph->machine()->UnalignedLoadSupported(memtype.representation())) {
3907 if (use_trap_handler) {
3908 return LoadKind::kProtected;
3909 }
3910 return LoadKind::kNormal;
3911 }
3912 // TODO(eholk): Support unaligned loads with trap handlers.
3913 DCHECK(!use_trap_handler)((void) 0);
3914 return LoadKind::kUnaligned;
3915}
3916} // namespace
3917
3918// S390 simulator does not execute BE code, hence needs to also check if we are
3919// running on a LE simulator.
3920// TODO(miladfar): Remove SIM once V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN includes the Sim.
3921#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_S390_LE_SIM)
3922Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadTransformBigEndian(
3923 wasm::ValueType type, MachineType memtype,
3924 wasm::LoadTransformationKind transform, Node* index, uint32_t offset,
3925 uint32_t alignment, wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3926#define LOAD_EXTEND(num_lanes, bytes_per_load, replace_lane) \
3927 result = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->S128Zero()); \
3928 Node* values[num_lanes]; \
3929 for (int i = 0; i < num_lanes; i++) { \
3930 values[i] = LoadMem(type, memtype, index, offset + i * bytes_per_load, \
3931 alignment, position); \
3932 if (memtype.IsSigned()) { \
3933 /* sign extend */ \
3934 values[i] = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeInt32ToInt64(), \
3935 values[i]); \
3936 } else { \
3937 /* zero extend */ \
3938 values[i] = graph()->NewNode( \
3939 mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeUint32ToUint64(), values[i]); \
3940 } \
3941 } \
3942 for (int lane = 0; lane < num_lanes; lane++) { \
3943 result = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->replace_lane(lane), \
3944 result, values[lane]); \
3945 }
3946 Node* result;
3947 LoadTransformation transformation = GetLoadTransformation(memtype, transform);
3948
3949 switch (transformation) {
3950 case LoadTransformation::kS8x16LoadSplat: {
3951 result = LoadMem(type, memtype, index, offset, alignment, position);
3952 result = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I8x16Splat(), result);
3953 break;
3954 }
3955 case LoadTransformation::kI16x8Load8x8S:
3956 case LoadTransformation::kI16x8Load8x8U: {
3957 LOAD_EXTEND(8, 1, I16x8ReplaceLane)
3958 break;
3959 }
3960 case LoadTransformation::kS16x8LoadSplat: {
3961 result = LoadMem(type, memtype, index, offset, alignment, position);
3962 result = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I16x8Splat(), result);
3963 break;
3964 }
3965 case LoadTransformation::kI32x4Load16x4S:
3966 case LoadTransformation::kI32x4Load16x4U: {
3967 LOAD_EXTEND(4, 2, I32x4ReplaceLane)
3968 break;
3969 }
3970 case LoadTransformation::kS32x4LoadSplat: {
3971 result = LoadMem(type, memtype, index, offset, alignment, position);
3972 result = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4Splat(), result);
3973 break;
3974 }
3975 case LoadTransformation::kI64x2Load32x2S:
3976 case LoadTransformation::kI64x2Load32x2U: {
3977 LOAD_EXTEND(2, 4, I64x2ReplaceLane)
3978 break;
3979 }
3980 case LoadTransformation::kS64x2LoadSplat: {
3981 result = LoadMem(type, memtype, index, offset, alignment, position);
3982 result = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I64x2Splat(), result);
3983 break;
3984 }
3985 default:
3986 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
3987 }
3988
3989 return result;
3990#undef LOAD_EXTEND
3991}
3992#endif
3993
3994Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadTransform(wasm::ValueType type, MachineType memtype,
3995 wasm::LoadTransformationKind transform,
3996 Node* index, uint32_t offset,
3997 uint32_t alignment,
3998 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
3999 if (memtype.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4000 has_simd_ = true;
4001 }
4002
4003 Node* load;
4004
4005#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_S390_LE_SIM)
4006 // LoadTransform cannot efficiently be executed on BE machines as a
4007 // single operation since loaded bytes need to be reversed first,
4008 // therefore we divide them into separate "load" and "operation" nodes.
4009 load = LoadTransformBigEndian(type, memtype, transform, index, offset,
4010 alignment, position);
4011 USE(GetLoadKind)do { ::v8::base::Use unused_tmp_array_for_use_macro[]{GetLoadKind
}; (void)unused_tmp_array_for_use_macro; } while (false);
4012#else
4013 // Wasm semantics throw on OOB. Introduce explicit bounds check and
4014 // conditioning when not using the trap handler.
4015
4016 // Load extends always load 8 bytes.
4017 uint8_t access_size = transform == wasm::LoadTransformationKind::kExtend
4018 ? 8
4019 : memtype.MemSize();
4020 index =
4021 BoundsCheckMem(access_size, index, offset, position, kCanOmitBoundsCheck);
4022
4023 LoadTransformation transformation = GetLoadTransformation(memtype, transform);
4024 LoadKind load_kind = GetLoadKind(mcgraph(), memtype, use_trap_handler());
4025
4026 load = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
4027 mcgraph()->machine()->LoadTransform(load_kind, transformation),
4028 MemBuffer(offset), index, effect(), control()));
4029
4030 if (load_kind == LoadKind::kProtected) {
4031 SetSourcePosition(load, position);
4032 }
4033#endif
4034
4035 if (FLAG_trace_wasm_memory) {
4036 TraceMemoryOperation(false, memtype.representation(), index, offset,
4037 position);
4038 }
4039 return load;
4040}
4041
4042Node* WasmGraphBuilder::LoadMem(wasm::ValueType type, MachineType memtype,
4043 Node* index, uint32_t offset,
4044 uint32_t alignment,
4045 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
4046 Node* load;
4047
4048 if (memtype.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4049 has_simd_ = true;
4050 }
4051
4052 // Wasm semantics throw on OOB. Introduce explicit bounds check and
4053 // conditioning when not using the trap handler.
4054 index = BoundsCheckMem(memtype.MemSize(), index, offset, position,
4055 kCanOmitBoundsCheck);
4056
4057 if (memtype.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord8 ||
4058 mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedLoadSupported(memtype.representation())) {
4059 if (use_trap_handler()) {
4060 load = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->ProtectedLoad(memtype),
4061 MemBuffer(offset), index, effect(), control());
4062 SetSourcePosition(load, position);
4063 } else {
4064 load = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(memtype),
4065 MemBuffer(offset), index, effect(), control());
4066 }
4067 } else {
4068 // TODO(eholk): Support unaligned loads with trap handlers.
4069 DCHECK(!use_trap_handler())((void) 0);
4070 load = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedLoad(memtype),
4071 MemBuffer(offset), index, effect(), control());
4072 }
4073
4074 SetEffect(load);
4075
4076#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
4077 load = BuildChangeEndiannessLoad(load, memtype, type);
4078#endif
4079
4080 if (type == wasm::kWasmI64 &&
4081 ElementSizeInBytes(memtype.representation()) < 8) {
4082 // TODO(titzer): TF zeroes the upper bits of 64-bit loads for subword sizes.
4083 if (memtype.IsSigned()) {
4084 // sign extend
4085 load = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeInt32ToInt64(), load);
4086 } else {
4087 // zero extend
4088 load =
4089 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeUint32ToUint64(), load);
4090 }
4091 }
4092
4093 if (FLAG_trace_wasm_memory) {
4094 TraceMemoryOperation(false, memtype.representation(), index, offset,
4095 position);
4096 }
4097
4098 return load;
4099}
4100
4101Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StoreMem(MachineRepresentation mem_rep, Node* index,
4102 uint32_t offset, uint32_t alignment, Node* val,
4103 wasm::WasmCodePosition position,
4104 wasm::ValueType type) {
4105 Node* store;
4106
4107 if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4108 has_simd_ = true;
4109 }
4110
4111 index = BoundsCheckMem(i::ElementSizeInBytes(mem_rep), index, offset,
4112 position, kCanOmitBoundsCheck);
4113
4114#if defined(V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN)
4115 val = BuildChangeEndiannessStore(val, mem_rep, type);
4116#endif
4117
4118 if (mem_rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8 ||
4119 mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedStoreSupported(mem_rep)) {
4120 if (use_trap_handler()) {
4121 store =
4122 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->ProtectedStore(mem_rep),
4123 MemBuffer(offset), index, val, effect(), control());
4124 SetSourcePosition(store, position);
4125 } else {
4126 StoreRepresentation rep(mem_rep, kNoWriteBarrier);
4127 store =
4128 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Store(rep), MemBuffer(offset),
4129 index, val, effect(), control());
4130 }
4131 } else {
4132 // TODO(eholk): Support unaligned stores with trap handlers.
4133 DCHECK(!use_trap_handler())((void) 0);
4134 UnalignedStoreRepresentation rep(mem_rep);
4135 store =
4136 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->UnalignedStore(rep),
4137 MemBuffer(offset), index, val, effect(), control());
4138 }
4139
4140 SetEffect(store);
4141
4142 if (FLAG_trace_wasm_memory) {
4143 TraceMemoryOperation(true, mem_rep, index, offset, position);
4144 }
4145
4146 return store;
4147}
4148
4149namespace {
4150Node* GetAsmJsOOBValue(MachineRepresentation rep, MachineGraph* mcgraph) {
4151 switch (rep) {
4152 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
4153 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
4154 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
4155 return mcgraph->Int32Constant(0);
4156 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
4157 return mcgraph->Int64Constant(0);
4158 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
4159 return mcgraph->Float32Constant(std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN());
4160 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
4161 return mcgraph->Float64Constant(std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN());
4162 default:
4163 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
4164 }
4165}
4166} // namespace
4167
4168Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildAsmjsLoadMem(MachineType type, Node* index) {
4169 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_cache_)((void) 0);
4170 Node* mem_start = instance_cache_->mem_start;
4171 Node* mem_size = instance_cache_->mem_size;
4172 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mem_start)((void) 0);
4173 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mem_size)((void) 0);
4174
4175 // Asm.js semantics are defined in terms of typed arrays, hence OOB
4176 // reads return {undefined} coerced to the result type (0 for integers, NaN
4177 // for float and double).
4178 // Note that we check against the memory size ignoring the size of the
4179 // stored value, which is conservative if misaligned. Technically, asm.js
4180 // should never have misaligned accesses.
4181 index = Uint32ToUintptr(index);
4182 Diamond bounds_check(
4183 graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
4184 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->UintLessThan(), index, mem_size),
4185 BranchHint::kTrue);
4186 bounds_check.Chain(control());
4187
4188 if (untrusted_code_mitigations_) {
4189 // Condition the index with the memory mask.
4190 Node* mem_mask = instance_cache_->mem_mask;
4191 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mem_mask)((void) 0);
4192 index = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->WordAnd(), index, mem_mask);
4193 }
4194
4195 Node* load = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(type), mem_start,
4196 index, effect(), bounds_check.if_true);
4197 SetEffectControl(bounds_check.EffectPhi(load, effect()), bounds_check.merge);
4198 return bounds_check.Phi(type.representation(), load,
4199 GetAsmJsOOBValue(type.representation(), mcgraph()));
4200}
4201
4202Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Uint32ToUintptr(Node* node) {
4203 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32()) return node;
4204 // Fold instances of ChangeUint32ToUint64(IntConstant) directly.
4205 Uint32Matcher matcher(node);
4206 if (matcher.HasValue()) {
4207 uintptr_t value = matcher.Value();
4208 return mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(bit_cast<intptr_t>(value));
4209 }
4210 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->ChangeUint32ToUint64(), node);
4211}
4212
4213Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BuildAsmjsStoreMem(MachineType type, Node* index,
4214 Node* val) {
4215 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(instance_cache_)((void) 0);
4216 Node* mem_start = instance_cache_->mem_start;
4217 Node* mem_size = instance_cache_->mem_size;
4218 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mem_start)((void) 0);
4219 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mem_size)((void) 0);
4220
4221 // Asm.js semantics are to ignore OOB writes.
4222 // Note that we check against the memory size ignoring the size of the
4223 // stored value, which is conservative if misaligned. Technically, asm.js
4224 // should never have misaligned accesses.
4225 Diamond bounds_check(
4226 graph(), mcgraph()->common(),
4227 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Uint32LessThan(), index, mem_size),
4228 BranchHint::kTrue);
4229 bounds_check.Chain(control());
4230
4231 if (untrusted_code_mitigations_) {
4232 // Condition the index with the memory mask.
4233 Node* mem_mask = instance_cache_->mem_mask;
4234 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mem_mask)((void) 0);
4235 index =
4236 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word32And(), index, mem_mask);
4237 }
4238
4239 index = Uint32ToUintptr(index);
4240 const Operator* store_op = mcgraph()->machine()->Store(StoreRepresentation(
4241 type.representation(), WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier));
4242 Node* store = graph()->NewNode(store_op, mem_start, index, val, effect(),
4243 bounds_check.if_true);
4244 SetEffectControl(bounds_check.EffectPhi(store, effect()), bounds_check.merge);
4245 return val;
4246}

4301
4302namespace {
4303Signature<MachineRepresentation>* CreateMachineSignature(
4304 Zone* zone, const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
4305 WasmGraphBuilder::CallOrigin origin) {
4306 Signature<MachineRepresentation>::Builder builder(zone, sig->return_count(),
4307 sig->parameter_count());
4308 for (auto ret : sig->returns()) {
4309 if (origin == WasmGraphBuilder::kCalledFromJS) {
4310 builder.AddReturn(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4311 } else {
4312 builder.AddReturn(ret.machine_representation());
4313 }
4314 }
4315
4316 for (auto param : sig->parameters()) {
4317 if (origin == WasmGraphBuilder::kCalledFromJS) {
4318 // Parameters coming from JavaScript are always tagged values. Especially
4319 // when the signature says that it's an I64 value, then a BigInt object is
4320 // provided by JavaScript, and not two 32-bit parameters.
4321 builder.AddParam(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4322 } else {
4323 builder.AddParam(param.machine_representation());
4324 }
4325 }
4326 return builder.Build();
4327}
4328
4329} // namespace

4331void WasmGraphBuilder::AddInt64LoweringReplacement(
4332 CallDescriptor* original, CallDescriptor* replacement) {
4333 if (!lowering_special_case_) {
4334 lowering_special_case_ = std::make_unique<Int64LoweringSpecialCase>();
4335 }
4336 lowering_special_case_->replacements.insert({original, replacement});
4337}

4339CallDescriptor* WasmGraphBuilder::GetI32AtomicWaitCallDescriptor() {
4340 if (i32_atomic_wait_descriptor_) return i32_atomic_wait_descriptor_;
4341
4342 i32_atomic_wait_descriptor_ =
4343 GetBuiltinCallDescriptor<WasmI32AtomicWait64Descriptor>(
4344 this, StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
4345
4346 AddInt64LoweringReplacement(
4347 i32_atomic_wait_descriptor_,
4348 GetBuiltinCallDescriptor<WasmI32AtomicWait32Descriptor>(
4349 this, StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub));
4350
4351 return i32_atomic_wait_descriptor_;
4352}

4369void WasmGraphBuilder::LowerInt64(CallOrigin origin) {
4370 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()) return;
4371 Int64Lowering r(mcgraph()->graph(), mcgraph()->machine(), mcgraph()->common(),
4372 mcgraph()->zone(),
4373 CreateMachineSignature(mcgraph()->zone(), sig_, origin),
4374 std::move(lowering_special_case_));
4375 r.LowerGraph();
4376}

4397Node* WasmGraphBuilder::SimdOp(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode, Node* const* inputs) {
4398 has_simd_ = true;
4399 switch (opcode) {
4400 case wasm::kExprF64x2Splat:
4401 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Splat(), inputs[0]);
4402 case wasm::kExprF64x2Abs:
4403 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Abs(), inputs[0]);
4404 case wasm::kExprF64x2Neg:
4405 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Neg(), inputs[0]);
4406 case wasm::kExprF64x2Sqrt:
4407 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Sqrt(), inputs[0]);
4408 case wasm::kExprF64x2Add:
4409 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Add(), inputs[0],
4410 inputs[1]);
4411 case wasm::kExprF64x2Sub:
4412 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Sub(), inputs[0],
4413 inputs[1]);
4414 case wasm::kExprF64x2Mul:
4415 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Mul(), inputs[0],
4416 inputs[1]);
4417 case wasm::kExprF64x2Div:
4418 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Div(), inputs[0],
4419 inputs[1]);
4420 case wasm::kExprF64x2Min:
4421 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Min(), inputs[0],
4422 inputs[1]);
4423 case wasm::kExprF64x2Max:
4424 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Max(), inputs[0],
4425 inputs[1]);
4426 case wasm::kExprF64x2Eq:
4427 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Eq(), inputs[0],
4428 inputs[1]);
4429 case wasm::kExprF64x2Ne:
4430 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Ne(), inputs[0],
4431 inputs[1]);
4432 case wasm::kExprF64x2Lt:
4433 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Lt(), inputs[0],
4434 inputs[1]);
4435 case wasm::kExprF64x2Le:
4436 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Le(), inputs[0],
4437 inputs[1]);
4438 case wasm::kExprF64x2Gt:
4439 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Lt(), inputs[1],
4440 inputs[0]);
4441 case wasm::kExprF64x2Ge:
4442 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Le(), inputs[1],
4443 inputs[0]);
4444 case wasm::kExprF64x2Qfma:
4445 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Qfma(), inputs[0],
4446 inputs[1], inputs[2]);
4447 case wasm::kExprF64x2Qfms:
4448 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Qfms(), inputs[0],
4449 inputs[1], inputs[2]);
4450 case wasm::kExprF64x2Pmin:
4451 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Pmin(), inputs[0],
4452 inputs[1]);
4453 case wasm::kExprF64x2Pmax:
4454 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Pmax(), inputs[0],
4455 inputs[1]);
4456 case wasm::kExprF64x2Ceil:
4457 // Architecture support for F64x2Ceil and Float64RoundUp is the same.
4458 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Float64RoundUp().IsSupported())
4459 return BuildF64x2Ceil(inputs[0]);
4460 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Ceil(), inputs[0]);
4461 case wasm::kExprF64x2Floor:
4462 // Architecture support for F64x2Floor and Float64RoundDown is the same.
4463 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Float64RoundDown().IsSupported())
4464 return BuildF64x2Floor(inputs[0]);
4465 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Floor(), inputs[0]);
4466 case wasm::kExprF64x2Trunc:
4467 // Architecture support for F64x2Trunc and Float64RoundTruncate is the
4468 // same.
4469 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Float64RoundTruncate().IsSupported())
4470 return BuildF64x2Trunc(inputs[0]);
4471 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2Trunc(), inputs[0]);
4472 case wasm::kExprF64x2NearestInt:
4473 // Architecture support for F64x2NearestInt and Float64RoundTiesEven is
4474 // the same.
4475 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Float64RoundTiesEven().IsSupported())
4476 return BuildF64x2NearestInt(inputs[0]);
4477 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2NearestInt(),
4478 inputs[0]);
4479 case wasm::kExprF32x4Splat:
4480 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Splat(), inputs[0]);
4481 case wasm::kExprF32x4SConvertI32x4:
4482 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4SConvertI32x4(),
4483 inputs[0]);
4484 case wasm::kExprF32x4UConvertI32x4:
4485 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4UConvertI32x4(),
4486 inputs[0]);
4487 case wasm::kExprF32x4Abs:
4488 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Abs(), inputs[0]);
4489 case wasm::kExprF32x4Neg:
4490 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Neg(), inputs[0]);
4491 case wasm::kExprF32x4Sqrt:
4492 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Sqrt(), inputs[0]);
4493 case wasm::kExprF32x4RecipApprox:
4494 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4RecipApprox(),
4495 inputs[0]);
4496 case wasm::kExprF32x4RecipSqrtApprox:
4497 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4RecipSqrtApprox(),
4498 inputs[0]);
4499 case wasm::kExprF32x4Add:
4500 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Add(), inputs[0],
4501 inputs[1]);
4502 case wasm::kExprF32x4AddHoriz:
4503 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4AddHoriz(), inputs[0],
4504 inputs[1]);
4505 case wasm::kExprF32x4Sub:

4510 inputs[1]);

4513 inputs[1]);
4514 case wasm::kExprF32x4Min:
4515 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Min(), inputs[0],
4516 inputs[1]);
4517 case wasm::kExprF32x4Max:
4518 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Max(), inputs[0],
4519 inputs[1]);
4520 case wasm::kExprF32x4Eq:
4521 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Eq(), inputs[0],
4522 inputs[1]);
4523 case wasm::kExprF32x4Ne:
4524 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Ne(), inputs[0],
4525 inputs[1]);
4526 case wasm::kExprF32x4Lt:

4528 inputs[1]);

4530 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Le(), inputs[0],
4531 inputs[1]);
4532 case wasm::kExprF32x4Gt:
4533 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Lt(), inputs[1],
4534 inputs[0]);
4535 case wasm::kExprF32x4Ge:

4537 inputs[0]);
4538 case wasm::kExprF32x4Qfma:

4540 inputs[1], inputs[2]);
4541 case wasm::kExprF32x4Qfms:

4543 inputs[1], inputs[2]);

4546 inputs[1]);
4547 case wasm::kExprF32x4Pmax:
4548 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Pmax(), inputs[0],
4549 inputs[1]);
4550 case wasm::kExprF32x4Ceil:
4551 // Architecture support for F32x4Ceil and Float32RoundUp is the same.
4552 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Float32RoundUp().IsSupported())

4554 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Ceil(), inputs[0]);
4555 case wasm::kExprF32x4Floor:
4556 // Architecture support for F32x4Floor and Float32RoundDown is the same.
4557 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Float32RoundDown().IsSupported())
4558 return BuildF32x4Floor(inputs[0]);
4559 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Floor(), inputs[0]);
4560 case wasm::kExprF32x4Trunc:
4561 // Architecture support for F32x4Trunc and Float32RoundTruncate is the
4562 // same.
4563 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Float32RoundTruncate().IsSupported())
4564 return BuildF32x4Trunc(inputs[0]);
4565 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4Trunc(), inputs[0]);
4566 case wasm::kExprF32x4NearestInt:
4567 // Architecture support for F32x4NearestInt and Float32RoundTiesEven is
4568 // the same.
4569 if (!mcgraph()->machine()->Float32RoundTiesEven().IsSupported())
4570 return BuildF32x4NearestInt(inputs[0]);
4571 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4NearestInt(),
4572 inputs[0]);
4573 case wasm::kExprI64x2Splat:
4574 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I64x2Splat(), inputs[0]);
4575 case wasm::kExprI64x2Neg:
4576 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I64x2Neg(), inputs[0]);
4577 case wasm::kExprI64x2Shl:
4578 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I64x2Shl(), inputs[0],
4579 inputs[1]);
4580 case wasm::kExprI64x2ShrS:

4582 inputs[1]);
4583 case wasm::kExprI64x2Add:

4585 inputs[1]);

4962
4963Node* WasmGraphBuilder::SimdLaneOp(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode, uint8_t lane,
4964 Node* const* inputs) {
4965 has_simd_ = true;
4966 switch (opcode) {
4967 case wasm::kExprF64x2ExtractLane:
4968 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2ExtractLane(lane),
4969 inputs[0]);
4970 case wasm::kExprF64x2ReplaceLane:
4971 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F64x2ReplaceLane(lane),
4972 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4973 case wasm::kExprF32x4ExtractLane:
4974 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4ExtractLane(lane),
4975 inputs[0]);
4976 case wasm::kExprF32x4ReplaceLane:
4977 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->F32x4ReplaceLane(lane),
4978 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4979 case wasm::kExprI64x2ExtractLane:
4980 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I64x2ExtractLane(lane),
4981 inputs[0]);
4982 case wasm::kExprI64x2ReplaceLane:
4983 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I64x2ReplaceLane(lane),
4984 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4985 case wasm::kExprI32x4ExtractLane:
4986 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ExtractLane(lane),
4987 inputs[0]);
4988 case wasm::kExprI32x4ReplaceLane:
4989 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I32x4ReplaceLane(lane),
4990 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
4991 case wasm::kExprI16x8ExtractLaneS:
4992 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I16x8ExtractLaneS(lane),
4993 inputs[0]);
4994 case wasm::kExprI16x8ExtractLaneU:
4995 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I16x8ExtractLaneU(lane),
4996 inputs[0]);
4997 case wasm::kExprI16x8ReplaceLane:
4998 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I16x8ReplaceLane(lane),
4999 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
5000 case wasm::kExprI8x16ExtractLaneS:
5001 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I8x16ExtractLaneS(lane),
5002 inputs[0]);
5003 case wasm::kExprI8x16ExtractLaneU:
5004 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I8x16ExtractLaneU(lane),
5005 inputs[0]);
5006 case wasm::kExprI8x16ReplaceLane:
5007 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->I8x16ReplaceLane(lane),
5008 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
5009 default:
5010 FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode);
5011 }
5012}
5013
5014Node* WasmGraphBuilder::Simd8x16ShuffleOp(const uint8_t shuffle[16],
5015 Node* const* inputs) {
5016 has_simd_ = true;
5017 return graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->S8x16Shuffle(shuffle),
5018 inputs[0], inputs[1]);
5019}

5046 V(I32AtomicOr16U, Or, Uint16, Word32) \
5047 V(I64AtomicOr8U, Or, Uint8, Word64) \
5048 V(I64AtomicOr16U, Or, Uint16, Word64) \
5049 V(I64AtomicOr32U, Or, Uint32, Word64) \
5050 V(I32AtomicXor, Xor, Uint32, Word32) \
5051 V(I64AtomicXor, Xor, Uint64, Word64) \
5052 V(I32AtomicXor8U, Xor, Uint8, Word32) \
5053 V(I32AtomicXor16U, Xor, Uint16, Word32) \
5054 V(I64AtomicXor8U, Xor, Uint8, Word64) \
5055 V(I64AtomicXor16U, Xor, Uint16, Word64) \
5056 V(I64AtomicXor32U, Xor, Uint32, Word64) \
5057 V(I32AtomicExchange, Exchange, Uint32, Word32) \
5058 V(I64AtomicExchange, Exchange, Uint64, Word64) \
5059 V(I32AtomicExchange8U, Exchange, Uint8, Word32) \
5060 V(I32AtomicExchange16U, Exchange, Uint16, Word32) \
5061 V(I64AtomicExchange8U, Exchange, Uint8, Word64) \
5062 V(I64AtomicExchange16U, Exchange, Uint16, Word64) \
5063 V(I64AtomicExchange32U, Exchange, Uint32, Word64)
5064
5065#define ATOMIC_CMP_EXCHG_LIST(V) \
5066 V(I32AtomicCompareExchange, Uint32, Word32) \
5067 V(I64AtomicCompareExchange, Uint64, Word64) \
5068 V(I32AtomicCompareExchange8U, Uint8, Word32) \
5069 V(I32AtomicCompareExchange16U, Uint16, Word32) \
5070 V(I64AtomicCompareExchange8U, Uint8, Word64) \
5071 V(I64AtomicCompareExchange16U, Uint16, Word64) \
5072 V(I64AtomicCompareExchange32U, Uint32, Word64)
5073
5074#define ATOMIC_LOAD_LIST(V) \
5075 V(I32AtomicLoad, Uint32, Word32) \
5076 V(I64AtomicLoad, Uint64, Word64) \
5077 V(I32AtomicLoad8U, Uint8, Word32) \
5078 V(I32AtomicLoad16U, Uint16, Word32) \
5079 V(I64AtomicLoad8U, Uint8, Word64) \
5080 V(I64AtomicLoad16U, Uint16, Word64) \
5081 V(I64AtomicLoad32U, Uint32, Word64)
5082
5083#define ATOMIC_STORE_LIST(V) \
5084 V(I32AtomicStore, Uint32, kWord32, Word32) \
5085 V(I64AtomicStore, Uint64, kWord64, Word64) \
5086 V(I32AtomicStore8U, Uint8, kWord8, Word32) \
5087 V(I32AtomicStore16U, Uint16, kWord16, Word32) \
5088 V(I64AtomicStore8U, Uint8, kWord8, Word64) \
5089 V(I64AtomicStore16U, Uint16, kWord16, Word64) \
5090 V(I64AtomicStore32U, Uint32, kWord32, Word64)
5091
5092Node* WasmGraphBuilder::AtomicOp(wasm::WasmOpcode opcode, Node* const* inputs,
5093 uint32_t alignment, uint32_t offset,
5094 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5095 Node* node;
5096 switch (opcode) {
5097#define BUILD_ATOMIC_BINOP(Name, Operation, Type, Prefix) \
5098 case wasm::kExpr##Name: { \
5099 Node* index = CheckBoundsAndAlignment(MachineType::Type().MemSize(), \
5100 inputs[0], offset, position); \
5101 node = graph()->NewNode( \
5102 mcgraph()->machine()->Prefix##Atomic##Operation(MachineType::Type()), \
5103 MemBuffer(offset), index, inputs[1], effect(), control()); \
5104 break; \
5105 }
5106 ATOMIC_BINOP_LIST(BUILD_ATOMIC_BINOP)
5107#undef BUILD_ATOMIC_BINOP
5108
5109#define BUILD_ATOMIC_CMP_EXCHG(Name, Type, Prefix) \
5110 case wasm::kExpr##Name: { \
5111 Node* index = CheckBoundsAndAlignment(MachineType::Type().MemSize(), \
5112 inputs[0], offset, position); \
5113 node = graph()->NewNode( \
5114 mcgraph()->machine()->Prefix##AtomicCompareExchange( \
5115 MachineType::Type()), \
5116 MemBuffer(offset), index, inputs[1], inputs[2], effect(), control()); \
5117 break; \
5118 }
5119 ATOMIC_CMP_EXCHG_LIST(BUILD_ATOMIC_CMP_EXCHG)
5120#undef BUILD_ATOMIC_CMP_EXCHG
5121
5122#define BUILD_ATOMIC_LOAD_OP(Name, Type, Prefix) \
5123 case wasm::kExpr##Name: { \
5124 Node* index = CheckBoundsAndAlignment(MachineType::Type().MemSize(), \
5125 inputs[0], offset, position); \
5126 node = graph()->NewNode( \
5127 mcgraph()->machine()->Prefix##AtomicLoad(MachineType::Type()), \
5128 MemBuffer(offset), index, effect(), control()); \
5129 break; \
5130 }
5131 ATOMIC_LOAD_LIST(BUILD_ATOMIC_LOAD_OP)
5132#undef BUILD_ATOMIC_LOAD_OP
5133
5134#define BUILD_ATOMIC_STORE_OP(Name, Type, Rep, Prefix) \
5135 case wasm::kExpr##Name: { \
5136 Node* index = CheckBoundsAndAlignment(MachineType::Type().MemSize(), \
5137 inputs[0], offset, position); \
5138 node = graph()->NewNode( \
5139 mcgraph()->machine()->Prefix##AtomicStore(MachineRepresentation::Rep), \
5140 MemBuffer(offset), index, inputs[1], effect(), control()); \
5141 break; \
5142 }
5143 ATOMIC_STORE_LIST(BUILD_ATOMIC_STORE_OP)
5144#undef BUILD_ATOMIC_STORE_OP
5145 case wasm::kExprAtomicNotify: {
5146 Node* index = CheckBoundsAndAlignment(MachineType::Uint32().MemSize(),
5147 inputs[0], offset, position);
5148 // Now that we've bounds-checked, compute the effective address.
5149 Node* address = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Int32Add(),
5150 Uint32Constant(offset), index);
5151 WasmAtomicNotifyDescriptor interface_descriptor;
5152 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
5153 mcgraph()->zone(), interface_descriptor,
5154 interface_descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(),
5155 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties,
5156 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
5157 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
5158 wasm::WasmCode::kWasmAtomicNotify, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
5159 node = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor),
5160 call_target, address, inputs[1], effect(),
5161 control());
5162 break;
5163 }
5164
5165 case wasm::kExprI32AtomicWait: {
5166 Node* index = CheckBoundsAndAlignment(MachineType::Uint32().MemSize(),
5167 inputs[0], offset, position);
5168 // Now that we've bounds-checked, compute the effective address.
5169 Node* address = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Int32Add(),
5170 Uint32Constant(offset), index);
5171
5172 auto call_descriptor = GetI32AtomicWaitCallDescriptor();
5173
5174 intptr_t target = mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()
5175 ? wasm::WasmCode::kWasmI32AtomicWait64
5176 : wasm::WasmCode::kWasmI32AtomicWait32;
5177 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
5178 target, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
5179
5180 node = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor),
5181 call_target, address, inputs[1], inputs[2],
5182 effect(), control());
5183 break;
5184 }
5185
5186 case wasm::kExprI64AtomicWait: {
5187 Node* index = CheckBoundsAndAlignment(MachineType::Uint64().MemSize(),
5188 inputs[0], offset, position);
5189 // Now that we've bounds-checked, compute the effective address.
5190 Node* address = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Int32Add(),
5191 Uint32Constant(offset), index);
5192
5193 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = GetI64AtomicWaitCallDescriptor();
5194
5195 intptr_t target = mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()
5196 ? wasm::WasmCode::kWasmI64AtomicWait64
5197 : wasm::WasmCode::kWasmI64AtomicWait32;
5198 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
5199 target, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
5200
5201 node = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor),
5202 call_target, address, inputs[1], inputs[2],
5203 effect(), control());
5204 break;
5205 }
5206
5207 default:
5208 FATAL_UNSUPPORTED_OPCODE(opcode);
5209 }
5210 return SetEffect(node);
5211}
5212
5213Node* WasmGraphBuilder::AtomicFence() {
5214 return SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->MemBarrier(),
5215 effect(), control()));
5216}

5218#undef ATOMIC_BINOP_LIST
5219#undef ATOMIC_CMP_EXCHG_LIST
5220#undef ATOMIC_LOAD_LIST
5221#undef ATOMIC_STORE_LIST
5222
5223Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MemoryInit(uint32_t data_segment_index, Node* dst,
5224 Node* src, Node* size,
5225 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5226 // The data segment index must be in bounds since it is required by
5227 // validation.
5228 DCHECK_LT(data_segment_index, env_->module->num_declared_data_segments)((void) 0);
5229
5230 Node* function = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->ExternalConstant(
5231 ExternalReference::wasm_memory_init()));
5232
5233 Node* stack_slot = StoreArgsInStackSlot(
5234 {{MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), instance_node_.get()},
5235 {MachineRepresentation::kWord32, dst},
5236 {MachineRepresentation::kWord32, src},
5237 {MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
5238 gasm_->Uint32Constant(data_segment_index)},
5239 {MachineRepresentation::kWord32, size}});
5240
5241 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
5242 MachineSignature sig(1, 1, sig_types);
5243 Node* call = SetEffect(BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot));
5244 return TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, call, position);
5245}
5246
5247Node* WasmGraphBuilder::DataDrop(uint32_t data_segment_index,
5248 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5249 DCHECK_LT(data_segment_index, env_->module->num_declared_data_segments)((void) 0);
5250
5251 Node* seg_size_array =
5252 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(DataSegmentSizes, MachineType::Pointer());
5253 STATIC_ASSERT(wasm::kV8MaxWasmDataSegments <= kMaxUInt32 >> 2)static_assert(wasm::kV8MaxWasmDataSegments <= kMaxUInt32 >>
2, "wasm::kV8MaxWasmDataSegments <= kMaxUInt32 >> 2"
);
5254 const Operator* store_op = mcgraph()->machine()->Store(
5255 StoreRepresentation(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, kNoWriteBarrier));
5256 return SetEffect(
5257 graph()->NewNode(store_op, seg_size_array,
5258 mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(data_segment_index << 2),
5259 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0), effect(), control()));
5260}
5261
5262Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StoreArgsInStackSlot(
5263 std::initializer_list<std::pair<MachineRepresentation, Node*>> args) {
5264 int slot_size = 0;
5265 for (auto arg : args) {
5266 slot_size += ElementSizeInBytes(arg.first);
5267 }
5268 DCHECK_LT(0, slot_size)((void) 0);
5269 Node* stack_slot =
5270 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->StackSlot(slot_size));
5271
5272 int offset = 0;
5273 for (auto arg : args) {
5274 MachineRepresentation type = arg.first;
5275 Node* value = arg.second;
5276 gasm_->Store(StoreRepresentation(type, kNoWriteBarrier), stack_slot,
5277 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(offset), value);
5278 offset += ElementSizeInBytes(type);
5279 }
5280 return stack_slot;
5281}

5283Node* WasmGraphBuilder::MemoryCopy(Node* dst, Node* src, Node* size,
5284 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5285 Node* function = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->ExternalConstant(
5286 ExternalReference::wasm_memory_copy()));
5287
5288 Node* stack_slot = StoreArgsInStackSlot(
5289 {{MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), instance_node_.get()},
5290 {MachineRepresentation::kWord32, dst},
5291 {MachineRepresentation::kWord32, src},
5292 {MachineRepresentation::kWord32, size}});
5293
5294 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Int32(), MachineType::Pointer()};
5295 MachineSignature sig(1, 1, sig_types);
5296 Node* call = SetEffect(BuildCCall(&sig, function, stack_slot));
5297 return TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapMemOutOfBounds, call, position);
5298}

5317Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TableInit(uint32_t table_index,
5318 uint32_t elem_segment_index, Node* dst,
5319 Node* src, Node* size,
5320 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5321 auto call_descriptor = GetBuiltinCallDescriptor<WasmTableInitDescriptor>(
5322 this, StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
5323
5324 intptr_t target = wasm::WasmCode::kWasmTableInit;
5325 Node* call_target =
5326 mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(target, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
5327
5328 return gasm_->Call(
5329 call_descriptor, call_target, dst, src, size,
5330 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(table_index)),
5331 graph()->NewNode(
5332 mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(elem_segment_index)));
5333}

5335Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ElemDrop(uint32_t elem_segment_index,
5336 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5337 // The elem segment index must be in bounds since it is required by
5338 // validation.
5339 DCHECK_LT(elem_segment_index, env_->module->elem_segments.size())((void) 0);
5340
5341 Node* dropped_elem_segments =
5342 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(DroppedElemSegments, MachineType::Pointer());
5343 const Operator* store_op = mcgraph()->machine()->Store(
5344 StoreRepresentation(MachineRepresentation::kWord8, kNoWriteBarrier));
5345 return SetEffect(
5346 graph()->NewNode(store_op, dropped_elem_segments,
5347 mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(elem_segment_index),
5348 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(1), effect(), control()));
5349}

5368Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TableGrow(uint32_t table_index, Node* value,
5369 Node* delta) {
5370 Node* args[] = {
5371 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(table_index)), value,
5372 BuildConvertUint32ToSmiWithSaturation(delta, FLAG_wasm_max_table_size)};
5373 Node* result =
5374 BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::kWasmTableGrow, args, arraysize(args)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(args))));
5375 return BuildChangeSmiToInt32(result);
5376}
5377
5378Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TableSize(uint32_t table_index) {
5379 Node* tables = LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(Tables, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
5380 Node* table = LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(tables, table_index);
5381
5382 int length_field_size = WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffsetEnd -
5383 WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffset + 1;
5384 Node* length_smi = gasm_->Load(
5385 assert_size(length_field_size, MachineType::TaggedSigned()), table,
5386 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTableObject::kCurrentLengthOffset));
5387
5388 return BuildChangeSmiToInt32(length_smi);
5389}
5390
5391Node* WasmGraphBuilder::TableFill(uint32_t table_index, Node* start,
5392 Node* value, Node* count) {
5393 Node* args[] = {
5394 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(table_index)),
5395 BuildConvertUint32ToSmiWithSaturation(start, FLAG_wasm_max_table_size),
5396 value,
5397 BuildConvertUint32ToSmiWithSaturation(count, FLAG_wasm_max_table_size)};
5398
5399 return BuildCallToRuntime(Runtime::kWasmTableFill, args, arraysize(args)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(args))));
5400}

5402namespace {
5403
5404MachineType FieldType(const wasm::StructType* type, uint32_t field_index,
5405 bool is_signed) {
5406 return MachineType::TypeForRepresentation(
5407 type->field(field_index).machine_representation(), is_signed);
5408}
5409
5410Node* FieldOffset(MachineGraph* graph, const wasm::StructType* type,
5411 uint32_t field_index) {
5412 int offset = WasmStruct::kHeaderSize + type->field_offset(field_index) -
5413 kHeapObjectTag;
5414 return graph->IntPtrConstant(offset);
5415}
5416
5417// It's guaranteed that struct/array fields are aligned to min(field_size,
5418// kTaggedSize), with the latter being 4 or 8 depending on platform and
5419// pointer compression. So on our most common configurations, 8-byte types
5420// must use unaligned loads/stores.
5421Node* LoadWithTaggedAlignment(WasmGraphAssembler* gasm, MachineType type,
5422 Node* base, Node* offset) {
5423 if (ElementSizeInBytes(type.representation()) > kTaggedSize) {
5424 return gasm->LoadUnaligned(type, base, offset);
5425 } else {
5426 return gasm->Load(type, base, offset);
5427 }
5428}
5429
5430// Same alignment considerations as above.
5431Node* StoreWithTaggedAlignment(WasmGraphAssembler* gasm, Node* base,
5432 Node* offset, Node* value,
5433 wasm::ValueType type) {
5434 MachineRepresentation rep = type.machine_representation();
5435 if (ElementSizeInBytes(rep) > kTaggedSize) {
5436 return gasm->StoreUnaligned(rep, base, offset, value);
5437 } else {
5438 WriteBarrierKind write_barrier =
5439 type.is_reference_type() ? kPointerWriteBarrier : kNoWriteBarrier;
5440 StoreRepresentation store_rep(rep, write_barrier);
5441 return gasm->Store(store_rep, base, offset, value);
5442 }
5443}
5444
5445// Set a field of a struct, without checking if the struct is null.
5446// Helper method for StructNewWithRtt and StructSet.
5447Node* StoreStructFieldUnchecked(MachineGraph* graph, WasmGraphAssembler* gasm,
5448 Node* struct_object,
5449 const wasm::StructType* type,
5450 uint32_t field_index, Node* value) {
5451 return StoreWithTaggedAlignment(gasm, struct_object,
5452 FieldOffset(graph, type, field_index), value,
5453 type->field(field_index));
5454}
5455
5456Node* ArrayElementOffset(GraphAssembler* gasm, Node* index,
5457 wasm::ValueType element_type) {
5458 return gasm->Int32Add(
5459 gasm->Int32Constant(WasmArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag),
5460 gasm->Int32Mul(index,
5461 gasm->Int32Constant(element_type.element_size_bytes())));
5462}
5463
5464Node* ArrayLength(GraphAssembler* gasm, Node* array) {
5465 return gasm->Load(
5466 MachineType::Uint32(), array,
5467 gasm->Int32Constant(WasmArray::kLengthOffset - kHeapObjectTag));
5468}

5470} // namespace
5471
5472Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StructNewWithRtt(uint32_t struct_index,
5473 const wasm::StructType* type,
5474 Node* rtt, Vector<Node*> fields) {
5475 Node* s = CALL_BUILTIN(
5476 WasmAllocateStructWithRtt, rtt,
5477 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
5478 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < type->field_count(); i++) {
5479 StoreStructFieldUnchecked(mcgraph(), gasm_.get(), s, type, i, fields[i]);
5480 }
5481 return s;
5482}
5483
5484Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayNewWithRtt(uint32_t array_index,
5485 const wasm::ArrayType* type,
5486 Node* length, Node* initial_value,
5487 Node* rtt) {
5488 wasm::ValueType element_type = type->element_type();
5489 Node* a = CALL_BUILTIN(
5490 WasmAllocateArrayWithRtt, rtt, BuildChangeUint31ToSmi(length),
5491 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(
5492 element_type.element_size_bytes())),
5493 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
5494 auto loop = gasm_->MakeLoopLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
5495 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel();
5496 Node* start_offset =
5497 gasm_->Int32Constant(WasmArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag);
5498 Node* element_size = gasm_->Int32Constant(element_type.element_size_bytes());
5499 Node* end_offset =
5500 gasm_->Int32Add(start_offset, gasm_->Int32Mul(element_size, length));
5501 // "Goto" requires the graph's end to have been set up.
5502 // TODO(jkummerow): Figure out if there's a more elegant solution.
5503 Graph* g = mcgraph()->graph();
5504 if (!g->end()) {
5505 g->SetEnd(g->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->End(0)));
5506 }
5507 gasm_->Goto(&loop, start_offset);
5508 gasm_->Bind(&loop);
5509 {
5510 Node* offset = loop.PhiAt(0);
5511 Node* check = gasm_->Uint32LessThan(offset, end_offset);
5512 gasm_->GotoIfNot(check, &done);
5513 StoreWithTaggedAlignment(gasm_.get(), a, offset, initial_value,
5514 type->element_type());
5515 offset = gasm_->Int32Add(offset, element_size);
5516 gasm_->Goto(&loop, offset);
5517 }
5518 gasm_->Bind(&done);
5519 return a;
5520}

, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmRttEqrefMap));

, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmRttExternrefMap

, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmRttExternrefMap
))

, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmRttExternrefMap
));
5533 case wasm::HeapType::kFunc:

)
5539 BuildLoadIsolateRoot(),gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmRttI31refMap)
)
5540 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmRttI31refMap))gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmRttI31refMap)
);
5541 default:
5542 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
5543 }
5544 }
5545 Node* maps_list =
5546 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(ManagedObjectMaps, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
5547 return LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_PTR(maps_list, type.ref_index());
5548}
5549
5550Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RttSub(wasm::HeapType type, Node* parent_rtt) {
5551 return CALL_BUILTIN(
5552 WasmAllocateRtt,
5553 graph()->NewNode(
5554 mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(type.representation())),
5555 parent_rtt,
5556 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
5557}
5558
5559Node* IsI31(GraphAssembler* gasm, Node* object) {
5560 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOLfalse) {
5561 return gasm->Word32Equal(
5562 gasm->Word32And(object, gasm->Int32Constant(kSmiTagMask)),
5563 gasm->Int32Constant(kSmiTag));
5564 } else {
5565 return gasm->WordEqual(
5566 gasm->WordAnd(object, gasm->IntPtrConstant(kSmiTagMask)),
5567 gasm->IntPtrConstant(kSmiTag));
5568 }
5569}
5570
5571void AssertFalse(GraphAssembler* gasm, Node* condition) {
5572#if DEBUG
5573 if (FLAG_debug_code) {
5574 auto ok = gasm->MakeLabel();
5575 gasm->GotoIfNot(condition, &ok);
5576 gasm->Unreachable();
5577 gasm->Goto(&ok);
5578 gasm->Bind(&ok);
5579 }
5580#endif
5581}
5582
5583Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RefTest(Node* object, Node* rtt,
5584 CheckForNull null_check, CheckForI31 i31_check,
5585 RttIsI31 rtt_is_i31) {
5586 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
5587 bool need_done_label = false;
5588 if (i31_check == kWithI31Check) {
5589 if (rtt_is_i31 == kRttIsI31) {
5590 return IsI31(gasm_.get(), object);
5591 }
5592 gasm_->GotoIf(IsI31(gasm_.get(), object), &done, gasm_->Int32Constant(0));
5593 need_done_label = true;
5594 } else {
5595 AssertFalse(gasm_.get(), IsI31(gasm_.get(), object));
5596 }
5597 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
5598 gasm_->GotoIf(gasm_->WordEqual(object, RefNull()), &done,
5599 gasm_->Int32Constant(0));
5600 need_done_label = true;
5601 }
5602
5603 Node* map = gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), object,
5604 HeapObject::kMapOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
5605 // TODO(7748): Add a fast path for map == rtt.
5606 Node* subtype_check = BuildChangeSmiToInt32(CALL_BUILTIN(
5607 WasmIsRttSubtype, map, rtt,
5608 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer())));
5609
5610 if (need_done_label) {
5611 gasm_->Goto(&done, subtype_check);
5612 gasm_->Bind(&done);
5613 subtype_check = done.PhiAt(0);
5614 }
5615 return subtype_check;
5616}
5617
5618Node* WasmGraphBuilder::RefCast(Node* object, Node* rtt,
5619 CheckForNull null_check, CheckForI31 i31_check,
5620 RttIsI31 rtt_is_i31,
5621 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5622 if (i31_check == kWithI31Check) {
5623 if (rtt_is_i31 == kRttIsI31) {
5624 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapIllegalCast, IsI31(gasm_.get(), object), position);
5625 return object;
5626 } else {
5627 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapIllegalCast, IsI31(gasm_.get(), object), position);
5628 }
5629 } else {
5630 AssertFalse(gasm_.get(), IsI31(gasm_.get(), object));
5631 }
5632 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
5633 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapIllegalCast, gasm_->WordEqual(object, RefNull()),
5634 position);
5635 }
5636 Node* map = gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), object,
5637 HeapObject::kMapOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
5638 // TODO(7748): Add a fast path for map == rtt.
5639 Node* check_result = BuildChangeSmiToInt32(CALL_BUILTIN(
5640 WasmIsRttSubtype, map, rtt,
5641 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer())));
5642 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapIllegalCast, check_result, position);
5643 return object;
5644}
5645
5646Node* WasmGraphBuilder::BrOnCast(Node* object, Node* rtt,
5647 CheckForNull null_check, CheckForI31 i31_check,
5648 RttIsI31 rtt_is_i31, Node** match_control,
5649 Node** match_effect, Node** no_match_control,
5650 Node** no_match_effect) {
5651 // We have up to 3 control nodes to merge; the EffectPhi needs an additional
5652 // input.
5653 base::SmallVector<Node*, 3> merge_controls;
5654 base::SmallVector<Node*, 4> merge_effects;
5655
5656 Node* is_i31 = IsI31(gasm_.get(), object);
5657 if (i31_check == kWithI31Check) {
5658 if (rtt_is_i31 == kRttIsI31) {
5659 BranchExpectFalse(is_i31, match_control, no_match_control);
5660 return nullptr;
5661 } else {
5662 Node* i31_branch = graph()->NewNode(
5663 mcgraph()->common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), is_i31, control());
5664 SetControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfFalse(), i31_branch));
5665 merge_controls.emplace_back(
5666 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfTrue(), i31_branch));
5667 merge_effects.emplace_back(effect());
5668 }
5669 } else {
5670 AssertFalse(gasm_.get(), is_i31);
5671 }
5672
5673 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
5674 Node* null_branch =
5675 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
5676 gasm_->WordEqual(object, RefNull()), control());
5677 SetControl(graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfFalse(), null_branch));
5678 merge_controls.emplace_back(
5679 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfTrue(), null_branch));
5680 merge_effects.emplace_back(effect());
5681 }
5682
5683 // At this point, {object} is neither null nor an i31ref/Smi.
5684 Node* map = gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), object,
5685 HeapObject::kMapOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
5686 // TODO(7748): Add a fast path for map == rtt.
5687 Node* subtype_check = BuildChangeSmiToInt32(CALL_BUILTIN(
5688 WasmIsRttSubtype, map, rtt,
5689 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer())));
5690 Node* cast_branch =
5691 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
5692 subtype_check, control());
5693 *match_control = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfTrue(), cast_branch);
5694 *match_effect = effect();
5695 Node* not_subtype =
5696 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfFalse(), cast_branch);
5697
5698 // Wire up the "cast attempt was unsuccessful" control nodes: merge them if
5699 // there is more than one.
5700 if (merge_controls.size() > 0) {
5701 merge_controls.emplace_back(not_subtype);
5702 merge_effects.emplace_back(effect());
5703 // Range is 1..3, so casting to int is safe.
5704 DCHECK_EQ(merge_controls.size(), merge_effects.size())((void) 0);
5705 unsigned count = static_cast<unsigned>(merge_controls.size());
5706 *no_match_control = Merge(count, merge_controls.data());
5707 // EffectPhis need their control dependency as an additional input.
5708 merge_effects.emplace_back(*no_match_control);
5709 *no_match_effect = EffectPhi(count, merge_effects.data());
5710 } else {
5711 *no_match_control = not_subtype;
5712 *no_match_effect = effect();
5713 }
5714 // Return value is not used, but we need it for compatibility
5715 // with graph-builder-interface.
5716 return nullptr;
5717}
5718
5719Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StructGet(Node* struct_object,
5720 const wasm::StructType* struct_type,
5721 uint32_t field_index, CheckForNull null_check,
5722 bool is_signed,
5723 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5724 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
5725 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapNullDereference,
5726 gasm_->WordEqual(struct_object, RefNull()), position);
5727 }
5728 MachineType machine_type = FieldType(struct_type, field_index, is_signed);
5729 Node* offset = FieldOffset(mcgraph(), struct_type, field_index);
5730 return LoadWithTaggedAlignment(gasm_.get(), machine_type, struct_object,
5731 offset);
5732}
5733
5734Node* WasmGraphBuilder::StructSet(Node* struct_object,
5735 const wasm::StructType* struct_type,
5736 uint32_t field_index, Node* field_value,
5737 CheckForNull null_check,
5738 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5739 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
5740 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapNullDereference,
5741 gasm_->WordEqual(struct_object, RefNull()), position);
5742 }
5743 return StoreStructFieldUnchecked(mcgraph(), gasm_.get(), struct_object,
5744 struct_type, field_index, field_value);
5745}

5747void WasmGraphBuilder::BoundsCheck(Node* array, Node* index,
5748 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5749 Node* length = ArrayLength(gasm_.get(), array);
5750 TrapIfFalse(wasm::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds, gasm_->Uint32LessThan(index, length),
5751 position);
5752}
5753
5754Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayGet(Node* array_object,
5755 const wasm::ArrayType* type, Node* index,
5756 CheckForNull null_check, bool is_signed,
5757 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5758 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
5759 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapNullDereference,
5760 gasm_->WordEqual(array_object, RefNull()), position);
5761 }
5762 BoundsCheck(array_object, index, position);
5763 MachineType machine_type = MachineType::TypeForRepresentation(
5764 type->element_type().machine_representation(), is_signed);
5765 Node* offset = ArrayElementOffset(gasm_.get(), index, type->element_type());
5766 return LoadWithTaggedAlignment(gasm_.get(), machine_type, array_object,
5767 offset);
5768}
5769
5770Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ArraySet(Node* array_object,
5771 const wasm::ArrayType* type, Node* index,
5772 Node* value, CheckForNull null_check,
5773 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5774 if (null_check == kWithNullCheck) {
5775 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapNullDereference,
5776 gasm_->WordEqual(array_object, RefNull()), position);
5777 }
5778 BoundsCheck(array_object, index, position);
5779 Node* offset = ArrayElementOffset(gasm_.get(), index, type->element_type());
5780 return StoreWithTaggedAlignment(gasm_.get(), array_object, offset, value,
5781 type->element_type());
5782}
5783
5784Node* WasmGraphBuilder::ArrayLen(Node* array_object,
5785 wasm::WasmCodePosition position) {
5786 TrapIfTrue(wasm::kTrapNullDereference,
5787 gasm_->WordEqual(array_object, RefNull()), position);
5788 return ArrayLength(gasm_.get(), array_object);
5789}
5790
5791// 1 bit V8 Smi tag, 31 bits V8 Smi shift, 1 bit i31ref high-bit truncation.
5792constexpr int kI31To32BitSmiShift = 33;
5793
5794Node* WasmGraphBuilder::I31New(Node* input) {
5795 if (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
5796 return gasm_->Word32Shl(input, BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32());
5797 }
5798 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits())((void) 0);
5799 input = BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(input);
5800 return gasm_->WordShl(input, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(kI31To32BitSmiShift));
5801}
5802
5803Node* WasmGraphBuilder::I31GetS(Node* input) {
5804 if (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
5805 input = BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(input);
5806 return gasm_->Word32SarShiftOutZeros(input, BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32());
5807 }
5808 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits())((void) 0);
5809 return BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(
5810 gasm_->WordSar(input, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(kI31To32BitSmiShift)));
5811}
5812
5813Node* WasmGraphBuilder::I31GetU(Node* input) {
5814 if (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
5815 input = BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(input);
5816 return gasm_->Word32Shr(input, BuildSmiShiftBitsConstant32());
5817 }
5818 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits())((void) 0);
5819 return BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(
5820 gasm_->WordShr(input, gasm_->IntPtrConstant(kI31To32BitSmiShift)));
5821}

5823class WasmDecorator final : public GraphDecorator {
5824 public:
5825 explicit WasmDecorator(NodeOriginTable* origins, wasm::Decoder* decoder)
5826 : origins_(origins), decoder_(decoder) {}
5827
5828 void Decorate(Node* node) final {
5829 origins_->SetNodeOrigin(
5830 node, NodeOrigin("wasm graph creation", "n/a",
5831 NodeOrigin::kWasmBytecode, decoder_->position()));
5832 }
5833
5834 private:
5835 compiler::NodeOriginTable* origins_;
5836 wasm::Decoder* decoder_;
5837};
5838
5839void WasmGraphBuilder::AddBytecodePositionDecorator(
5840 NodeOriginTable* node_origins, wasm::Decoder* decoder) {
5841 DCHECK_NULL(decorator_)((void) 0);
5842 decorator_ = graph()->zone()->New<WasmDecorator>(node_origins, decoder);
5843 graph()->AddDecorator(decorator_);
5844}
5845
5846void WasmGraphBuilder::RemoveBytecodePositionDecorator() {
5847 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(decorator_)((void) 0);
5848 graph()->RemoveDecorator(decorator_);
5849 decorator_ = nullptr;
5850}

5854class WasmWrapperGraphBuilder : public WasmGraphBuilder {
5855 public:
5856 WasmWrapperGraphBuilder(Zone* zone, MachineGraph* mcgraph,
5857 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
5858 compiler::SourcePositionTable* spt,
5859 StubCallMode stub_mode, wasm::WasmFeatures features)
5860 : WasmGraphBuilder(nullptr, zone, mcgraph, sig, spt),
5861 stub_mode_(stub_mode),
5862 enabled_features_(features) {}
5863
5864 CallDescriptor* GetI64ToBigIntCallDescriptor() {
5865 if (i64_to_bigint_descriptor_) return i64_to_bigint_descriptor_;
5866
5867 i64_to_bigint_descriptor_ =
5868 GetBuiltinCallDescriptor<I64ToBigIntDescriptor>(this, stub_mode_);
5869
5870 AddInt64LoweringReplacement(
5871 i64_to_bigint_descriptor_,
5872 GetBuiltinCallDescriptor<I32PairToBigIntDescriptor>(this, stub_mode_));
5873 return i64_to_bigint_descriptor_;
5874 }
5875
5876 CallDescriptor* GetBigIntToI64CallDescriptor() {
5877 if (bigint_to_i64_descriptor_) return bigint_to_i64_descriptor_;
5878
5879 bigint_to_i64_descriptor_ =
5880 GetBuiltinCallDescriptor<BigIntToI64Descriptor>(this, stub_mode_);
5881
5882 AddInt64LoweringReplacement(
5883 bigint_to_i64_descriptor_,
5884 GetBuiltinCallDescriptor<BigIntToI32PairDescriptor>(this, stub_mode_));
5885 return bigint_to_i64_descriptor_;
5886 }
5887
5888 Node* GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::RuntimeStubId wasm_stub,
5889 Builtins::Name builtin_id) {
5890 return (stub_mode_ == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub)
5891 ? mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(wasm_stub,
5892 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL)
5893 : GetBuiltinPointerTarget(builtin_id);
5894 }
5895
5896 Node* BuildLoadUndefinedValueFromInstance() {
5897 if (undefined_value_node_ == nullptr) {
5898 Node* isolate_root = graph()->NewNode(
5899 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::Pointer()),
5900 instance_node_.get(),
5901 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_OFFSET(IsolateRoot)),
5902 graph()->start(), graph()->start());
5903 undefined_value_node_ = graph()->NewNode(
5904 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::Pointer()), isolate_root,
5905 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(
5906 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue)),
5907 isolate_root, graph()->start());
5908 }
5909 return undefined_value_node_.get();
5910 }
5911
5912 Node* BuildChangeInt32ToNumber(Node* value) {
5913 // We expect most integers at runtime to be Smis, so it is important for
5914 // wrapper performance that Smi conversion be inlined.
5915 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
5916 return BuildChangeInt32ToSmi(value);
5917 }
5918 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits())((void) 0);
5919
5920 auto builtin = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
5921 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
5922
5923 // Double value to test if value can be a Smi, and if so, to convert it.
5924 Node* add = gasm_->Int32AddWithOverflow(value, value);
5925 Node* ovf = gasm_->Projection(1, add);
5926 gasm_->GotoIf(ovf, &builtin);
5927
5928 // If it didn't overflow, the result is {2 * value} as pointer-sized value.
5929 Node* smi_tagged = BuildChangeInt32ToIntPtr(gasm_->Projection(0, add));
5930 gasm_->Goto(&done, smi_tagged);
5931
5932 // Otherwise, call builtin, to convert to a HeapNumber.
5933 gasm_->Bind(&builtin);
5934 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
5935 Node* target =
5936 GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::kWasmInt32ToHeapNumber,
5937 Builtins::kWasmInt32ToHeapNumber);
5938 if (!int32_to_heapnumber_operator_.is_set()) {
5939 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
5940 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmInt32ToHeapNumberDescriptor(), 0,
5941 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties, stub_mode_);
5942 int32_to_heapnumber_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
5943 }
5944 Node* call =
5945 gasm_->Call(int32_to_heapnumber_operator_.get(), target, value);
5946 gasm_->Goto(&done, call);
5947 gasm_->Bind(&done);
5948 return done.PhiAt(0);
5949 }
5950
5951 Node* BuildChangeTaggedToInt32(Node* value, Node* context) {
5952 // We expect most integers at runtime to be Smis, so it is important for
5953 // wrapper performance that Smi conversion be inlined.
5954 auto builtin = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel();
5955 auto done = gasm_->MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
5956
5957 // Test if value is a Smi.
5958 Node* is_smi =
5959 gasm_->Word32Equal(gasm_->Word32And(BuildTruncateIntPtrToInt32(value),
5960 gasm_->Int32Constant(kSmiTagMask)),
5961 gasm_->Int32Constant(0));
5962 gasm_->GotoIfNot(is_smi, &builtin);
5963
5964 // If Smi, convert to int32.
5965 Node* smi = BuildChangeSmiToInt32(value);
5966 gasm_->Goto(&done, smi);
5967
5968 // Otherwise, call builtin which changes non-Smi to Int32.
5969 gasm_->Bind(&builtin);
5970 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
5971 Node* target =
5972 GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::kWasmTaggedNonSmiToInt32,
5973 Builtins::kWasmTaggedNonSmiToInt32);
5974 if (!tagged_non_smi_to_int32_operator_.is_set()) {
5975 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
5976 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmTaggedNonSmiToInt32Descriptor(), 0,
5977 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties, stub_mode_);
5978 tagged_non_smi_to_int32_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
5979 }
5980 Node* call = gasm_->Call(tagged_non_smi_to_int32_operator_.get(), target,
5981 value, context);
5982 SetSourcePosition(call, 1);
5983 gasm_->Goto(&done, call);
5984 gasm_->Bind(&done);
5985 return done.PhiAt(0);
5986 }
5987
5988 Node* BuildChangeFloat32ToNumber(Node* value) {
5989 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
5990 Node* target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFloat32ToNumber,
5991 Builtins::kWasmFloat32ToNumber);
5992 if (!float32_to_number_operator_.is_set()) {
5993 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
5994 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmFloat32ToNumberDescriptor(), 0,
5995 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties, stub_mode_);
5996 float32_to_number_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
5997 }
5998 return gasm_->Call(float32_to_number_operator_.get(), target, value);
5999 }
6000
6001 Node* BuildChangeFloat64ToNumber(Node* value) {
6002 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
6003 Node* target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFloat64ToNumber,
6004 Builtins::kWasmFloat64ToNumber);
6005 if (!float64_to_number_operator_.is_set()) {
6006 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
6007 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmFloat64ToNumberDescriptor(), 0,
6008 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties, stub_mode_);
6009 float64_to_number_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
6010 }
6011 return gasm_->Call(float64_to_number_operator_.get(), target, value);
6012 }
6013
6014 Node* BuildChangeTaggedToFloat64(Node* value, Node* context) {
6015 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = mcgraph()->common();
6016 Node* target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::kWasmTaggedToFloat64,
6017 Builtins::kWasmTaggedToFloat64);
6018 if (!tagged_to_float64_operator_.is_set()) {
6019 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
6020 mcgraph()->zone(), WasmTaggedToFloat64Descriptor(), 0,
6021 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties, stub_mode_);
6022 tagged_to_float64_operator_.set(common->Call(call_descriptor));
6023 }
6024 Node* call =
6025 gasm_->Call(tagged_to_float64_operator_.get(), target, value, context);
6026 SetSourcePosition(call, 1);
6027 return call;
6028 }
6029
6030 int AddArgumentNodes(Vector<Node*> args, int pos, int param_count,
6031 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig) {
6032 // Convert wasm numbers to JS values.
6033 for (int i = 0; i < param_count; ++i) {
6034 Node* param =
6035 Param(i + 1); // Start from index 1 to drop the instance_node.
6036 args[pos++] = ToJS(param, sig->GetParam(i));
6037 }
6038 return pos;
6039 }
6040
6041 Node* ToJS(Node* node, wasm::ValueType type) {
6042 switch (type.kind()) {
6043 case wasm::ValueType::kI32:
6044 return BuildChangeInt32ToNumber(node);
6045 case wasm::ValueType::kS128:
6046 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
6047 case wasm::ValueType::kI64: {
6048 DCHECK(enabled_features_.has_bigint())((void) 0);
6049 return BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(node);
6050 }
6051 case wasm::ValueType::kF32:
6052 return BuildChangeFloat32ToNumber(node);
6053 case wasm::ValueType::kF64:
6054 return BuildChangeFloat64ToNumber(node);
6055 case wasm::ValueType::kRef:
6056 case wasm::ValueType::kOptRef: {
6057 uint32_t representation = type.heap_representation();
6058 if (representation == wasm::HeapType::kExtern ||
6059 representation == wasm::HeapType::kExn ||
6060 representation == wasm::HeapType::kFunc) {
6061 return node;
6062 }
6063 if (representation == wasm::HeapType::kEq) {
6064 return BuildAllocateObjectWrapper(node);
6065 }
6066 // TODO(7748): Figure out a JS interop story for arrays and structs.
6067 // If this is reached, then IsJSCompatibleSignature() is too permissive.
6068 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
6069 }
6070 case wasm::ValueType::kRtt:
6071 // TODO(7748): Figure out what to do for RTTs.
6072 UNIMPLEMENTED()V8_Fatal("unimplemented code");
6073 case wasm::ValueType::kI8:
6074 case wasm::ValueType::kI16:
6075 case wasm::ValueType::kStmt:
6076 case wasm::ValueType::kBottom:
6077 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
6078 }
6079 }
6080
6081 // TODO(7748): Temporary solution to allow round-tripping of Wasm objects
6082 // through JavaScript, where they show up as opaque boxes. This will disappear
6083 // once we have a proper WasmGC <-> JS interaction story.
6084 Node* BuildAllocateObjectWrapper(Node* input) {
6085 return CALL_BUILTIN(
6086 WasmAllocateObjectWrapper, input,
6087 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
6088 }

6090 Node* BuildUnpackObjectWrapper(Node* input) {
6091 Node* obj = CALL_BUILTIN(
6092 WasmGetOwnProperty, input,
6093 LOAD_FULL_POINTER(BuildLoadIsolateRoot(),gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset( RootIndex::kwasm_wrapped_object_symbol
))
6094 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset( RootIndex::kwasm_wrapped_object_symbol
))
6095 RootIndex::kwasm_wrapped_object_symbol))gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset( RootIndex::kwasm_wrapped_object_symbol
)),
6096 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
6097 // Invalid object wrappers (i.e. any other JS object that doesn't have the
6098 // magic hidden property) will return {undefined}. Map that to {null}.
6099 Node* undefined = LOAD_FULL_POINTER(gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue))
6100 BuildLoadIsolateRoot(),gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue))
6101 IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue))gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), BuildLoadIsolateRoot()
, IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
6102 Node* is_undefined = gasm_->WordEqual(obj, undefined);
6103 Diamond check(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), is_undefined,
6104 BranchHint::kFalse);
6105 check.Chain(control());
6106 return check.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, RefNull(), obj);
6107 }

6109 Node* BuildChangeInt64ToBigInt(Node* input) {
6110 const Operator* call =
6111 mcgraph()->common()->Call(GetI64ToBigIntCallDescriptor());
6112
6113 Node* target;
6114 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()) {
6115 target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::kI64ToBigInt,
6116 Builtins::kI64ToBigInt);
6117 } else {
6118 DCHECK(mcgraph()->machine()->Is32())((void) 0);
6119 // On 32-bit platforms we already set the target to the
6120 // I32PairToBigInt builtin here, so that we don't have to replace the
6121 // target in the int64-lowering.
6122 target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::kI32PairToBigInt,
6123 Builtins::kI32PairToBigInt);
6124 }
6125
6126 return SetEffectControl(
6127 graph()->NewNode(call, target, input, effect(), control()));
6128 }
