6130 Node* BuildChangeBigIntToInt64(Node* input, Node* context) {
6131 const Operator* call =
6132 mcgraph()->common()->Call(GetBigIntToI64CallDescriptor());
6133
6134 Node* target;
6135 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is64()) {
6136 target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::kBigIntToI64,
6137 Builtins::kBigIntToI64);
6138 } else {
6139 DCHECK(mcgraph()->machine()->Is32())((void) 0);
6140 // On 32-bit platforms we already set the target to the
6141 // BigIntToI32Pair builtin here, so that we don't have to replace the
6142 // target in the int64-lowering.
6143 target = GetTargetForBuiltinCall(wasm::WasmCode::kBigIntToI32Pair,
6144 Builtins::kBigIntToI32Pair);
6145 }
6146
6147 return SetEffectControl(
6148 graph()->NewNode(call, target, input, context, effect(), control()));

6150
6151 Node* FromJS(Node* input, Node* js_context, wasm::ValueType type) {
6152 switch (type.kind()) {
6153 case wasm::ValueType::kRef:
6154 case wasm::ValueType::kOptRef: {
6155 switch (type.heap_representation()) {
6156 case wasm::HeapType::kExtern:
6157 case wasm::HeapType::kExn:
6158 return input;
6159 case wasm::HeapType::kFunc: {
6160 Node* check =
6161 BuildChangeSmiToInt32(SetEffect(BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(
6162 Runtime::kWasmIsValidFuncRefValue, js_context, &input, 1)));
6163
6164 Diamond type_check(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), check,
6165 BranchHint::kTrue);
6166 type_check.Chain(control());
6167 SetControl(type_check.if_false);
6168
6169 Node* old_effect = effect();
6170 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kWasmThrowTypeError,
6171 js_context, nullptr, 0);
6172
6173 SetEffectControl(type_check.EffectPhi(old_effect, effect()),
6174 type_check.merge);
6175
6176 return input;
6177 }
6178 case wasm::HeapType::kEq:
6179 return BuildUnpackObjectWrapper(input);
6180 default:
6181 // If this is reached, then IsJSCompatibleSignature() is too
6182 // permissive.
6183 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
6184 }
6185 }
6186 case wasm::ValueType::kF32:
6187 return graph()->NewNode(
6188 mcgraph()->machine()->TruncateFloat64ToFloat32(),
6189 BuildChangeTaggedToFloat64(input, js_context));
6190
6191 case wasm::ValueType::kF64:
6192 return BuildChangeTaggedToFloat64(input, js_context);
6193
6194 case wasm::ValueType::kI32:
6195 return BuildChangeTaggedToInt32(input, js_context);
6196
6197 case wasm::ValueType::kI64:
6198 // i64 values can only come from BigInt.
6199 DCHECK(enabled_features_.has_bigint())((void) 0);
6200 return BuildChangeBigIntToInt64(input, js_context);
6201
6202 case wasm::ValueType::kRtt: // TODO(7748): Implement.
6203 case wasm::ValueType::kS128:
6204 case wasm::ValueType::kI8:
6205 case wasm::ValueType::kI16:
6206 case wasm::ValueType::kBottom:
6207 case wasm::ValueType::kStmt:
6208 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
6209 break;
6210 }
6211 }
6212
6213 void BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(bool new_value) {
6214 if (!trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled()) return;
6215 Node* isolate_root = BuildLoadIsolateRoot();
6216
6217 Node* thread_in_wasm_flag_address =
6218 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Pointer(), isolate_root,
6219 Isolate::thread_in_wasm_flag_address_offset());
6220
6221 if (FLAG_debug_code) {
6222 Node* flag_value = SetEffect(
6223 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::Pointer()),
6224 thread_in_wasm_flag_address,
6225 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0), effect(), control()));
6226 Node* check =
6227 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->Word32Equal(), flag_value,
6228 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(new_value ? 0 : 1));
6229
6230 Diamond flag_check(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), check,
6231 BranchHint::kTrue);
6232 flag_check.Chain(control());
6233 SetControl(flag_check.if_false);
6234 Node* message_id = graph()->NewNode(
6235 mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(static_cast<int32_t>(
6236 new_value ? AbortReason::kUnexpectedThreadInWasmSet
6237 : AbortReason::kUnexpectedThreadInWasmUnset)));
6238
6239 Node* old_effect = effect();
6240 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kAbort, NoContextConstant(),
6241 &message_id, 1);
6242
6243 SetEffectControl(flag_check.EffectPhi(old_effect, effect()),
6244 flag_check.merge);
6245 }
6246
6247 SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
6248 mcgraph()->machine()->Store(StoreRepresentation(
6249 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, kNoWriteBarrier)),
6250 thread_in_wasm_flag_address, mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0),
6251 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(new_value ? 1 : 0), effect(), control()));
6252 }

6255 return gasm_->Load(
6256 MachineType::AnyTagged(), function_data,
6257 WasmExportedFunctionData::kInstanceOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
6258 }

6261 Node* iterable, Node* context) {

6265 }

6267 // Extract the FixedArray implementing
6268 // the backing storage of a JavaScript array.
6269 Node* BuildLoadArrayBackingStorage(Node* js_array) {
6270 return gasm_->Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), js_array,
6271 JSObject::kElementsOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
6272 }

6274 // Generate a call to the AllocateJSArray builtin.
6275 Node* BuildCallAllocateJSArray(Node* array_length, Node* context) {
6276 // Since we don't check that args will fit in an array,
6277 // we make sure this is true based on statically known limits.
6278 STATIC_ASSERT(wasm::kV8MaxWasmFunctionMultiReturns <=static_assert(wasm::kV8MaxWasmFunctionMultiReturns <= JSArray
::kInitialMaxFastElementArray, "wasm::kV8MaxWasmFunctionMultiReturns <= JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray"
)
6279 JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray)static_assert(wasm::kV8MaxWasmFunctionMultiReturns <= JSArray
::kInitialMaxFastElementArray, "wasm::kV8MaxWasmFunctionMultiReturns <= JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray"
);
6280 return SetControl(CALL_BUILTIN(WasmAllocateJSArray, array_length, context));
6281 }
6282
6283 void BuildJSToWasmWrapper(bool is_import) {
6284 const int wasm_count = static_cast<int>(sig_->parameter_count());
6285 const int rets_count = static_cast<int>(sig_->return_count());
6286
6287 // Build the start and the JS parameter nodes.
6288 SetEffectControl(Start(wasm_count + 5));
6289
6290 // Create the js_closure and js_context parameters.
6291 Node* js_closure =
6292 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Parameter(
6293 Linkage::kJSCallClosureParamIndex, "%closure"),
6294 graph()->start());
6295 Node* js_context = graph()->NewNode(
6296 mcgraph()->common()->Parameter(
6297 Linkage::GetJSCallContextParamIndex(wasm_count + 1), "%context"),
6298 graph()->start());
6299
6300 // Create the instance_node node to pass as parameter. It is loaded from
6301 // an actual reference to an instance or a placeholder reference,
6302 // called {WasmExportedFunction} via the {WasmExportedFunctionData}
6303 // structure.
6304 Node* function_data = BuildLoadFunctionDataFromExportedFunction(js_closure);
6305 instance_node_.set(
6306 BuildLoadInstanceFromExportedFunctionData(function_data));
6307
6308 if (!wasm::IsJSCompatibleSignature(sig_, enabled_features_)) {
6309 // Throw a TypeError. Use the js_context of the calling javascript
6310 // function (passed as a parameter), such that the generated code is
6311 // js_context independent.
6312 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kWasmThrowTypeError, js_context,
6313 nullptr, 0);
6314 TerminateThrow(effect(), control());
6315 return;
6316 }
6317
6318 const int args_count = wasm_count + 1; // +1 for wasm_code.
6319 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(args_count);
6320 base::SmallVector<Node*, 1> rets(rets_count);
6321
6322 // Convert JS parameters to wasm numbers.
6323 for (int i = 0; i < wasm_count; ++i) {
6324 Node* param = Param(i + 1);
6325 Node* wasm_param = FromJS(param, js_context, sig_->GetParam(i));
6326 args[i + 1] = wasm_param;
6327 }
6328
6329 // Set the ThreadInWasm flag before we do the actual call.
6330 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
6331
6332 if (is_import) {
6333 // Call to an imported function.
6334 // Load function index from {WasmExportedFunctionData}.
6335 Node* function_index =
6336 BuildLoadFunctionIndexFromExportedFunctionData(function_data);
6337 BuildImportCall(sig_, VectorOf(args), VectorOf(rets),
6338 wasm::kNoCodePosition, function_index, kCallContinues);
6339 } else {
6340 // Call to a wasm function defined in this module.
6341 // The call target is the jump table slot for that function.
6342 Node* jump_table_start =
6343 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(JumpTableStart, MachineType::Pointer());
6344 Node* jump_table_offset =
6345 BuildLoadJumpTableOffsetFromExportedFunctionData(function_data);
6346 Node* jump_table_slot = graph()->NewNode(
6347 mcgraph()->machine()->IntAdd(), jump_table_start, jump_table_offset);
6348 args[0] = jump_table_slot;
6349
6350 BuildWasmCall(sig_, VectorOf(args), VectorOf(rets), wasm::kNoCodePosition,
6351 nullptr, kNoRetpoline);
6352 }
6353
6354 // Clear the ThreadInWasm flag.
6355 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
6356
6357 Node* jsval;
6358 if (sig_->return_count() == 0) {
6359 jsval = BuildLoadUndefinedValueFromInstance();
6360 } else if (sig_->return_count() == 1) {
6361 jsval = ToJS(rets[0], sig_->GetReturn());
6362 } else {
6363 int32_t return_count = static_cast<int32_t>(sig_->return_count());
6364 Node* size =
6365 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(return_count));
6366
6367 jsval = BuildCallAllocateJSArray(size, js_context);
6368
6369 Node* fixed_array = BuildLoadArrayBackingStorage(jsval);
6370
6371 for (int i = 0; i < return_count; ++i) {
6372 Node* value = ToJS(rets[i], sig_->GetReturn(i));
6373 STORE_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(fixed_array, i, value);
6374 }
6375 }
6376 Return(jsval);
6377 if (ContainsInt64(sig_)) LowerInt64(kCalledFromJS);
6378 }
6379
6380 Node* BuildReceiverNode(Node* callable_node, Node* native_context,
6381 Node* undefined_node) {
6382 // Check function strict bit.
6383 Node* shared_function_info = gasm_->Load(
6384 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), callable_node,
6385 wasm::ObjectAccess::SharedFunctionInfoOffsetInTaggedJSFunction());
6386 Node* flags =
6387 gasm_->Load(MachineType::Int32(), shared_function_info,
6388 wasm::ObjectAccess::FlagsOffsetInSharedFunctionInfo());
6389 Node* strict_check =
6390 Binop(wasm::kExprI32And, flags,
6391 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(SharedFunctionInfo::IsNativeBit::kMask |
6392 SharedFunctionInfo::IsStrictBit::kMask));
6393
6394 // Load global receiver if sloppy else use undefined.
6395 Diamond strict_d(graph(), mcgraph()->common(), strict_check,
6396 BranchHint::kNone);
6397 Node* old_effect = effect();
6398 SetControl(strict_d.if_false);
6399 Node* global_proxy =
6400 LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_PTR(native_context, Context::GLOBAL_PROXY_INDEX);
6401 SetEffectControl(strict_d.EffectPhi(old_effect, global_proxy),
6402 strict_d.merge);
6403 return strict_d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, undefined_node,
6404 global_proxy);
6405 }
6406
6407 bool BuildWasmImportCallWrapper(WasmImportCallKind kind, int expected_arity) {
6408 int wasm_count = static_cast<int>(sig_->parameter_count());
6409
6410 // Build the start and the parameter nodes.
6411 SetEffectControl(Start(wasm_count + 4));
6412
6413 instance_node_.set(Param(wasm::kWasmInstanceParameterIndex));
6414
6415 Node* native_context =
6416 LOAD_INSTANCE_FIELD(NativeContext, MachineType::TaggedPointer());
6417
6418 if (kind == WasmImportCallKind::kRuntimeTypeError) {
6419 // =======================================================================
6420 // === Runtime TypeError =================================================
6421 // =======================================================================
6422 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kWasmThrowTypeError,
6423 native_context, nullptr, 0);
6424 TerminateThrow(effect(), control());
6425 return false;
6426 }
6427
6428 // The callable is passed as the last parameter, after Wasm arguments.
6429 Node* callable_node = Param(wasm_count + 1);
6430
6431 Node* undefined_node = BuildLoadUndefinedValueFromInstance();
6432
6433 Node* call = nullptr;
6434
6435 // Clear the ThreadInWasm flag.
6436 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
6437
6438 switch (kind) {
6439 // =======================================================================
6440 // === JS Functions with matching arity ==================================
6441 // =======================================================================
6442 case WasmImportCallKind::kJSFunctionArityMatch: {
6443 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(wasm_count + 7);
6444 int pos = 0;
6445 Node* function_context =
6446 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), callable_node,
6447 wasm::ObjectAccess::ContextOffsetInTaggedJSFunction());
6448 args[pos++] = callable_node; // target callable.
6449
6450 // Determine receiver at runtime.
6451 args[pos++] =
6452 BuildReceiverNode(callable_node, native_context, undefined_node);
6453
6454 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
6455 graph()->zone(), false, wasm_count + 1, CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
6456
6457 // Convert wasm numbers to JS values.
6458 pos = AddArgumentNodes(VectorOf(args), pos, wasm_count, sig_);
6459
6460 args[pos++] = undefined_node; // new target
6461 args[pos++] = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(wasm_count); // argument count
6462 args[pos++] = function_context;
6463 args[pos++] = effect();
6464 args[pos++] = control();
6465
6466 DCHECK_EQ(pos, args.size())((void) 0);
6467 call = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), pos,
6468 args.begin());
6469 break;
6470 }
6471 // =======================================================================
6472 // === JS Functions with arguments adapter ===============================
6473 // =======================================================================
6474 case WasmImportCallKind::kJSFunctionArityMismatch: {
6475 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(wasm_count + 9);
6476 int pos = 0;
6477 Node* function_context =
6478 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), callable_node,
6479 wasm::ObjectAccess::ContextOffsetInTaggedJSFunction());
6480 args[pos++] = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
6481 wasm::WasmCode::kArgumentsAdaptorTrampoline,
6482 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
6483 args[pos++] = callable_node; // target callable
6484 args[pos++] = undefined_node; // new target
6485 args[pos++] = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(wasm_count); // argument count
6486
6487 // Load shared function info, and then the formal parameter count.
6488 Node* shared_function_info = gasm_->Load(
6489 MachineType::TaggedPointer(), callable_node,
6490 wasm::ObjectAccess::SharedFunctionInfoOffsetInTaggedJSFunction());
6491 Node* formal_param_count = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
6492 mcgraph()->machine()->Load(MachineType::Uint16()),
6493 shared_function_info,
6494 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(
6495 wasm::ObjectAccess::
6496 FormalParameterCountOffsetInSharedFunctionInfo()),
6497 effect(), control()));
6498 args[pos++] = formal_param_count;
6499
6500 // Determine receiver at runtime.
6501 args[pos++] =
6502 BuildReceiverNode(callable_node, native_context, undefined_node);
6503
6504 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
6505 mcgraph()->zone(), ArgumentsAdaptorDescriptor{}, 1 + wasm_count,
6506 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties,
6507 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
6508
6509 // Convert wasm numbers to JS values.
6510 pos = AddArgumentNodes(VectorOf(args), pos, wasm_count, sig_);
6511 args[pos++] = function_context;
6512 args[pos++] = effect();
6513 args[pos++] = control();
6514
6515 DCHECK_EQ(pos, args.size())((void) 0);
6516 call = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), pos,
6517 args.begin());
6518 break;
6519 }
6520 // =======================================================================
6521 // === JS Functions without arguments adapter ============================
6522 // =======================================================================
6523 case WasmImportCallKind::kJSFunctionArityMismatchSkipAdaptor: {
6524 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(expected_arity + 7);
6525 int pos = 0;
6526 Node* function_context =
6527 gasm_->Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), callable_node,
6528 wasm::ObjectAccess::ContextOffsetInTaggedJSFunction());
6529 args[pos++] = callable_node; // target callable.
6530
6531 // Determine receiver at runtime.
6532 args[pos++] =
6533 BuildReceiverNode(callable_node, native_context, undefined_node);
6534
6535 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
6536 graph()->zone(), false, expected_arity + 1,
6537 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
6538
6539 // Convert wasm numbers to JS values.
6540 if (expected_arity <= wasm_count) {
6541 pos = AddArgumentNodes(VectorOf(args), pos, expected_arity, sig_);
6542 } else {
6543 pos = AddArgumentNodes(VectorOf(args), pos, wasm_count, sig_);
6544 for (int i = wasm_count; i < expected_arity; ++i) {
6545 args[pos++] = undefined_node;
6546 }
6547 }
6548
6549 args[pos++] = undefined_node; // new target
6550 args[pos++] =
6551 mcgraph()->Int32Constant(expected_arity); // argument count
6552 args[pos++] = function_context;
6553 args[pos++] = effect();
6554 args[pos++] = control();
6555
6556 DCHECK_EQ(pos, args.size())((void) 0);
6557 call = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), pos,
6558 args.begin());
6559 break;
6560 }
6561 // =======================================================================
6562 // === General case of unknown callable ==================================
6563 // =======================================================================
6564 case WasmImportCallKind::kUseCallBuiltin: {
6565 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(wasm_count + 7);
6566 int pos = 0;
6567 args[pos++] = GetBuiltinPointerTarget(Builtins::kCall_ReceiverIsAny);
6568 args[pos++] = callable_node;
6569 args[pos++] = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(wasm_count); // argument count
6570 args[pos++] = undefined_node; // receiver
6571
6572 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
6573 graph()->zone(), CallTrampolineDescriptor{}, wasm_count + 1,
6574 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties,
6575 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
6576
6577 // Convert wasm numbers to JS values.
6578 pos = AddArgumentNodes(VectorOf(args), pos, wasm_count, sig_);
6579
6580 // The native_context is sufficient here, because all kind of callables
6581 // which depend on the context provide their own context. The context
6582 // here is only needed if the target is a constructor to throw a
6583 // TypeError, if the target is a native function, or if the target is a
6584 // callable JSObject, which can only be constructed by the runtime.
6585 args[pos++] = native_context;
6586 args[pos++] = effect();
6587 args[pos++] = control();
6588
6589 DCHECK_EQ(pos, args.size())((void) 0);
6590 call = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), pos,
6591 args.begin());
6592 break;
6593 }
6594 default:
6595 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
6596 }
6597 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(call)((void) 0);
6598
6599 SetEffect(call);
6600 SetSourcePosition(call, 0);
6601
6602 // Convert the return value(s) back.
6603 if (sig_->return_count() <= 1) {
6604 Node* val = sig_->return_count() == 0
6605 ? mcgraph()->Int32Constant(0)
6606 : FromJS(call, native_context, sig_->GetReturn());
6607 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
6608 Return(val);
6609 } else {
6610 Node* fixed_array =
6611 BuildMultiReturnFixedArrayFromIterable(sig_, call, native_context);
6612 base::SmallVector<Node*, 8> wasm_values(sig_->return_count());
6613 for (unsigned i = 0; i < sig_->return_count(); ++i) {
6614 wasm_values[i] = FromJS(LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(fixed_array, i),
6615 native_context, sig_->GetReturn(i));
6616 }
6617 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
6618 Return(VectorOf(wasm_values));
6619 }
6620
6621 if (ContainsInt64(sig_)) LowerInt64(kCalledFromWasm);
6622 return true;
6623 }
6624
6625 void BuildCapiCallWrapper(Address address) {
6626 // Store arguments on our stack, then align the stack for calling to C.
6627 int param_bytes = 0;
6628 for (wasm::ValueType type : sig_->parameters()) {
6629 param_bytes += type.element_size_bytes();
6630 }
6631 int return_bytes = 0;
6632 for (wasm::ValueType type : sig_->returns()) {
6633 return_bytes += type.element_size_bytes();
6634 }
6635
6636 int stack_slot_bytes = std::max(param_bytes, return_bytes);
6637 Node* values = stack_slot_bytes == 0
6638 ? mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(0)
6639 : graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->StackSlot(
6640 stack_slot_bytes, kDoubleAlignment));
6641
6642 int offset = 0;
6643 int param_count = static_cast<int>(sig_->parameter_count());
6644 for (int i = 0; i < param_count; ++i) {
6645 wasm::ValueType type = sig_->GetParam(i);
6646 // Start from the parameter with index 1 to drop the instance_node.
6647 // TODO(jkummerow): When a values is a reference type, we should pass it
6648 // in a GC-safe way, not just as a raw pointer.
6649 SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(GetSafeStoreOperator(offset, type), values,
6650 Int32Constant(offset), Param(i + 1), effect(),
6651 control()));
6652 offset += type.element_size_bytes();
6653 }
6654 // The function is passed as the last parameter, after Wasm arguments.
6655 Node* function_node = Param(param_count + 1);
6656 Node* shared = gasm_->Load(
6657 MachineType::AnyTagged(), function_node,
6658 wasm::ObjectAccess::SharedFunctionInfoOffsetInTaggedJSFunction());
6659 Node* sfi_data =
6660 gasm_->Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), shared,
6661 SharedFunctionInfo::kFunctionDataOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
6662 Node* host_data_foreign =
6663 gasm_->Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), sfi_data,
6664 WasmCapiFunctionData::kEmbedderDataOffset - kHeapObjectTag);
6665
6666 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(false);
6667 Node* isolate_root = BuildLoadIsolateRoot();
6668 Node* fp_value = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->LoadFramePointer());
6669 STORE_RAW(isolate_root, Isolate::c_entry_fp_offset(), fp_value,
6670 MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), kNoWriteBarrier);
6671
6672 // TODO(jkummerow): Load the address from the {host_data}, and cache
6673 // wrappers per signature.
6674 const ExternalReference ref = ExternalReference::Create(address);
6675 Node* function =
6676 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->ExternalConstant(ref));
6677
6678 // Parameters: Address host_data_foreign, Address arguments.
6679 MachineType host_sig_types[] = {
6680 MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Pointer(), MachineType::Pointer()};
6681 MachineSignature host_sig(1, 2, host_sig_types);
6682 Node* return_value =
6683 BuildCCall(&host_sig, function, host_data_foreign, values);
6684
6685 BuildModifyThreadInWasmFlag(true);
6686
6687 Node* exception_branch =
6688 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue),
6689 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->WordEqual(),
6690 return_value, IntPtrConstant(0)),
6691 control());
6692 SetControl(
6693 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfFalse(), exception_branch));
6694 WasmThrowDescriptor interface_descriptor;
6695 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
6696 mcgraph()->zone(), interface_descriptor,
6697 interface_descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(), CallDescriptor::kNoFlags,
6698 Operator::kNoProperties, StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
6699 Node* call_target = mcgraph()->RelocatableIntPtrConstant(
6700 wasm::WasmCode::kWasmRethrow, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
6701 Node* throw_effect =
6702 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor),
6703 call_target, return_value, effect(), control());
6704 TerminateThrow(throw_effect, control());
6705
6706 SetControl(
6707 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfTrue(), exception_branch));
6708 DCHECK_LT(sig_->return_count(), wasm::kV8MaxWasmFunctionMultiReturns)((void) 0);
6709 size_t return_count = sig_->return_count();
6710 if (return_count == 0) {
6711 Return(Int32Constant(0));
6712 } else {
6713 base::SmallVector<Node*, 8> returns(return_count);
6714 offset = 0;
6715 for (size_t i = 0; i < return_count; ++i) {
6716 wasm::ValueType type = sig_->GetReturn(i);
6717 Node* val = SetEffect(
6718 graph()->NewNode(GetSafeLoadOperator(offset, type), values,
6719 Int32Constant(offset), effect(), control()));
6720 returns[i] = val;
6721 offset += type.element_size_bytes();
6722 }
6723 Return(VectorOf(returns));
6724 }
6725
6726 if (ContainsInt64(sig_)) LowerInt64(kCalledFromWasm);
6727 }
6728
6729 void BuildJSToJSWrapper(Isolate* isolate) {
6730 int wasm_count = static_cast<int>(sig_->parameter_count());
6731
6732 // Build the start and the parameter nodes.
6733 int param_count = 1 /* closure */ + 1 /* receiver */ + wasm_count +
6734 1 /* new.target */ + 1 /* #arg */ + 1 /* context */;
6735 SetEffectControl(Start(param_count));
6736 Node* closure = Param(Linkage::kJSCallClosureParamIndex);
6737 Node* context = Param(Linkage::GetJSCallContextParamIndex(wasm_count + 1));
6738
6739 // Since JS-to-JS wrappers are specific to one Isolate, it is OK to embed
6740 // values (for undefined and root) directly into the instruction stream.
6741 isolate_root_node_ = mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(isolate->isolate_root());
6742 undefined_value_node_ = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->HeapConstant(
6743 isolate->factory()->undefined_value()));
6744
6745 // Throw a TypeError if the signature is incompatible with JavaScript.
6746 if (!wasm::IsJSCompatibleSignature(sig_, enabled_features_)) {
6747 BuildCallToRuntimeWithContext(Runtime::kWasmThrowTypeError, context,
6748 nullptr, 0);
6749 TerminateThrow(effect(), control());
6750 return;
6751 }
6752
6753 // Load the original callable from the closure.
6754 Node* shared = LOAD_TAGGED_ANY(
6755 closure,
6756 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
6757 Node* func_data = LOAD_TAGGED_ANY(
6758 shared,
6759 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(SharedFunctionInfo::kFunctionDataOffset));
6760 Node* callable = LOAD_TAGGED_ANY(
6761 func_data,
6762 wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmJSFunctionData::kCallableOffset));
6763
6764 // Call the underlying closure.
6765 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(wasm_count + 7);
6766 int pos = 0;
6767 args[pos++] = GetBuiltinPointerTarget(Builtins::kCall_ReceiverIsAny);
6768 args[pos++] = callable;
6769 args[pos++] = mcgraph()->Int32Constant(wasm_count); // argument count
6770 args[pos++] = BuildLoadUndefinedValueFromInstance(); // receiver
6771
6772 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
6773 graph()->zone(), CallTrampolineDescriptor{}, wasm_count + 1,
6774 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kNoProperties,
6775 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
6776
6777 // Convert parameter JS values to wasm numbers and back to JS values.
6778 for (int i = 0; i < wasm_count; ++i) {
6779 Node* param = Param(i + 1); // Start from index 1 to skip receiver.
6780 args[pos++] =
6781 ToJS(FromJS(param, context, sig_->GetParam(i)), sig_->GetParam(i));
6782 }
6783
6784 args[pos++] = context;
6785 args[pos++] = effect();
6786 args[pos++] = control();
6787
6788 DCHECK_EQ(pos, args.size())((void) 0);
6789 Node* call = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
6790 mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), pos, args.begin()));
6791
6792 // Convert return JS values to wasm numbers and back to JS values.
6793 Node* jsval;
6794 if (sig_->return_count() == 0) {
6795 jsval = BuildLoadUndefinedValueFromInstance();
6796 } else if (sig_->return_count() == 1) {
6797 jsval = ToJS(FromJS(call, context, sig_->GetReturn()), sig_->GetReturn());
6798 } else {
6799 Node* fixed_array =
6800 BuildMultiReturnFixedArrayFromIterable(sig_, call, context);
6801 int32_t return_count = static_cast<int32_t>(sig_->return_count());
6802 Node* size =
6803 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->NumberConstant(return_count));
6804 jsval = BuildCallAllocateJSArray(size, context);
6805 Node* result_fixed_array = BuildLoadArrayBackingStorage(jsval);
6806 for (unsigned i = 0; i < sig_->return_count(); ++i) {
6807 const auto& type = sig_->GetReturn(i);
6808 Node* elem = LOAD_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(fixed_array, i);
6809 Node* cast = ToJS(FromJS(elem, context, type), type);
6810 STORE_FIXED_ARRAY_SLOT_ANY(result_fixed_array, i, cast);
6811 }
6812 }
6813 Return(jsval);
6814 }
6815
6816 void BuildCWasmEntry() {
6817 // +1 offset for first parameter index being -1.
6818 SetEffectControl(Start(CWasmEntryParameters::kNumParameters + 1));
6819
6820 Node* code_entry = Param(CWasmEntryParameters::kCodeEntry);
6821 Node* object_ref = Param(CWasmEntryParameters::kObjectRef);
6822 Node* arg_buffer = Param(CWasmEntryParameters::kArgumentsBuffer);
6823 Node* c_entry_fp = Param(CWasmEntryParameters::kCEntryFp);
6824
6825 Node* fp_value = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->machine()->LoadFramePointer());
6826 STORE_RAW(fp_value, TypedFrameConstants::kFirstPushedFrameValueOffset,
6827 c_entry_fp, MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
6828 kNoWriteBarrier);
6829
6830 int wasm_arg_count = static_cast<int>(sig_->parameter_count());
6831 base::SmallVector<Node*, 16> args(wasm_arg_count + 4);
6832
6833 int pos = 0;
6834 args[pos++] = code_entry;
6835 args[pos++] = object_ref;
6836
6837 int offset = 0;
6838 for (wasm::ValueType type : sig_->parameters()) {
6839 Node* arg_load = SetEffect(
6840 graph()->NewNode(GetSafeLoadOperator(offset, type), arg_buffer,
6841 Int32Constant(offset), effect(), control()));
6842 args[pos++] = arg_load;
6843 offset += type.element_size_bytes();
6844 }
6845
6846 args[pos++] = effect();
6847 args[pos++] = control();
6848
6849 // Call the wasm code.
6850 auto call_descriptor = GetWasmCallDescriptor(mcgraph()->zone(), sig_);
6851
6852 DCHECK_EQ(pos, args.size())((void) 0);
6853 Node* call = SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(
6854 mcgraph()->common()->Call(call_descriptor), pos, args.begin()));
6855
6856 Node* if_success = graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfSuccess(), call);
6857 Node* if_exception =
6858 graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->IfException(), call, call);
6859
6860 // Handle exception: return it.
6861 SetControl(if_exception);
6862 Return(if_exception);
6863
6864 // Handle success: store the return value(s).
6865 SetControl(if_success);
6866 pos = 0;
6867 offset = 0;
6868 for (wasm::ValueType type : sig_->returns()) {
6869 Node* value = sig_->return_count() == 1
6870 ? call
6871 : graph()->NewNode(mcgraph()->common()->Projection(pos),
6872 call, control());
6873 SetEffect(graph()->NewNode(GetSafeStoreOperator(offset, type), arg_buffer,
6874 Int32Constant(offset), value, effect(),
6875 control()));
6876 offset += type.element_size_bytes();
6877 pos++;
6878 }
6879
6880 Return(mcgraph()->IntPtrConstant(0));
6881
6882 if (mcgraph()->machine()->Is32() && ContainsInt64(sig_)) {
6883 // No special lowering should be requested in the C entry.
6884 DCHECK_NULL(lowering_special_case_)((void) 0);
6885
6886 MachineRepresentation sig_reps[] = {
6887 MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), // return value
6888 MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), // target
6889 MachineRepresentation::kTagged, // object_ref
6890 MachineType::PointerRepresentation(), // argv
6891 MachineType::PointerRepresentation() // c_entry_fp
6892 };
6893 Signature<MachineRepresentation> c_entry_sig(1, 4, sig_reps);
6894 Int64Lowering r(mcgraph()->graph(), mcgraph()->machine(),
6895 mcgraph()->common(), mcgraph()->zone(), &c_entry_sig);
6896 r.LowerGraph();
6897 }
6898 }
6899
6900 private:
6901 StubCallMode stub_mode_;
6902 SetOncePointer<Node> undefined_value_node_;
6903 SetOncePointer<const Operator> int32_to_heapnumber_operator_;
6904 SetOncePointer<const Operator> tagged_non_smi_to_int32_operator_;
6905 SetOncePointer<const Operator> float32_to_number_operator_;
6906 SetOncePointer<const Operator> float64_to_number_operator_;
6907 SetOncePointer<const Operator> tagged_to_float64_operator_;
6908 wasm::WasmFeatures enabled_features_;
6909 CallDescriptor* bigint_to_i64_descriptor_ = nullptr;
6910 CallDescriptor* i64_to_bigint_descriptor_ = nullptr;
6911};
6912
6913} // namespace
6914
6915std::unique_ptr<OptimizedCompilationJob> NewJSToWasmCompilationJob(
6916 Isolate* isolate, wasm::WasmEngine* wasm_engine,
6917 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig, bool is_import,
6918 const wasm::WasmFeatures& enabled_features) {
6919 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6920 // Create the Graph.
6921 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6922 std::unique_ptr<Zone> zone = std::make_unique<Zone>(
6923 wasm_engine->allocator(), ZONE_NAME__func__, kCompressGraphZone);
6924 Graph* graph = zone->New<Graph>(zone.get());
6925 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = zone->New<CommonOperatorBuilder>(zone.get());
6926 MachineOperatorBuilder* machine = zone->New<MachineOperatorBuilder>(
6927 zone.get(), MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
6928 InstructionSelector::SupportedMachineOperatorFlags(),
6929 InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements());
6930 MachineGraph* mcgraph = zone->New<MachineGraph>(graph, common, machine);
6931
6932 WasmWrapperGraphBuilder builder(zone.get(), mcgraph, sig, nullptr,
6933 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer,
6934 enabled_features);
6935 builder.BuildJSToWasmWrapper(is_import);
6936
6937 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6938 // Create the compilation job.
6939 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6940 constexpr size_t kMaxNameLen = 128;
6941 constexpr size_t kNamePrefixLen = 11;
6942 auto name_buffer = std::unique_ptr<char[]>(new char[kMaxNameLen]);
6943 memcpy(name_buffer.get(), "js-to-wasm:", kNamePrefixLen);
6944 PrintSignature(VectorOf(name_buffer.get(), kMaxNameLen) + kNamePrefixLen,
6945 sig);
6946
6947 int params = static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count());
6948 CallDescriptor* incoming = Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
6949 zone.get(), false, params + 1, CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
6950
6951 return Pipeline::NewWasmHeapStubCompilationJob(
6952 isolate, wasm_engine, incoming, std::move(zone), graph,
6953 CodeKind::JS_TO_WASM_FUNCTION, std::move(name_buffer),
6954 WasmAssemblerOptions());
6955}
6956
6957std::pair<WasmImportCallKind, Handle<JSReceiver>> ResolveWasmImportCall(
6958 Handle<JSReceiver> callable, const wasm::FunctionSig* expected_sig,
6959 const wasm::WasmFeatures& enabled_features) {
6960 if (WasmExportedFunction::IsWasmExportedFunction(*callable)) {
6961 auto imported_function = Handle<WasmExportedFunction>::cast(callable);
6962 auto func_index = imported_function->function_index();
6963 auto module = imported_function->instance().module();
6964 const wasm::FunctionSig* imported_sig = module->functions[func_index].sig;
6965 if (*imported_sig != *expected_sig) {
6966 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kLinkError, callable);
6967 }
6968 if (static_cast<uint32_t>(func_index) >= module->num_imported_functions) {
6969 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kWasmToWasm, callable);
6970 }
6971 Isolate* isolate = callable->GetIsolate();
6972 // Resolve the short-cut to the underlying callable and continue.
6973 Handle<WasmInstanceObject> instance(imported_function->instance(), isolate);
6974 ImportedFunctionEntry entry(instance, func_index);
6975 callable = handle(entry.callable(), isolate);
6976 }
6977 if (WasmJSFunction::IsWasmJSFunction(*callable)) {
6978 auto js_function = Handle<WasmJSFunction>::cast(callable);
6979 if (!js_function->MatchesSignature(expected_sig)) {
6980 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kLinkError, callable);
6981 }
6982 Isolate* isolate = callable->GetIsolate();
6983 // Resolve the short-cut to the underlying callable and continue.
6984 callable = handle(js_function->GetCallable(), isolate);
6985 }
6986 if (WasmCapiFunction::IsWasmCapiFunction(*callable)) {
6987 auto capi_function = Handle<WasmCapiFunction>::cast(callable);
6988 if (!capi_function->IsSignatureEqual(expected_sig)) {
6989 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kLinkError, callable);
6990 }
6991 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kWasmToCapi, callable);
6992 }
6993 // Assuming we are calling to JS, check whether this would be a runtime error.
6994 if (!wasm::IsJSCompatibleSignature(expected_sig, enabled_features)) {
6995 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kRuntimeTypeError, callable);
6996 }
6997 // For JavaScript calls, determine whether the target has an arity match.
6998 if (callable->IsJSFunction()) {
6999 Handle<JSFunction> function = Handle<JSFunction>::cast(callable);
7000 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(),
7001 function->GetIsolate());
7002
7003// Check for math intrinsics.
7004#define COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN(name) \
7005 { \
7006 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig = \
7007 wasm::WasmOpcodes::Signature(wasm::kExpr##name); \
7008 if (!sig) sig = wasm::WasmOpcodes::AsmjsSignature(wasm::kExpr##name); \
7009 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(sig)((void) 0); \
7010 if (*expected_sig == *sig) { \
7011 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::k##name, callable); \
7012 } \
7013 }
7014#define COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(name) \
7015 case Builtins::kMath##name: \
7016 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN(F64##name); \
7017 break;
7018#define COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F32_F64(name) \
7019 case Builtins::kMath##name: \
7020 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN(F64##name); \
7021 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN(F32##name); \
7022 break;
7023
7024 if (FLAG_wasm_math_intrinsics && shared->HasBuiltinId()) {
7025 switch (shared->builtin_id()) {
7026 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Acos);
7027 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Asin);
7028 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Atan);
7029 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Cos);
7030 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Sin);
7031 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Tan);
7032 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Exp);
7033 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Log);
7034 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Atan2);
7035 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64(Pow);
7036 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F32_F64(Min);
7037 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F32_F64(Max);
7038 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F32_F64(Abs);
7039 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F32_F64(Ceil);
7040 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F32_F64(Floor);
7041 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F32_F64(Sqrt);
7042 case Builtins::kMathFround:
7043 COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN(F32ConvertF64);
7044 break;
7045 default:
7046 break;
7047 }
7048 }
7049
7050#undef COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN
7051#undef COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F64
7052#undef COMPARE_SIG_FOR_BUILTIN_F32_F64
7053
7054 if (IsClassConstructor(shared->kind())) {
7055 // Class constructor will throw anyway.
7056 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kUseCallBuiltin, callable);
7057 }
7058
7059 if (shared->internal_formal_parameter_count() ==
7060 expected_sig->parameter_count()) {
7061 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kJSFunctionArityMatch,
7062 callable);
7063 }
7064
7065 // If function isn't compiled, compile it now.
7066 IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(
7067 shared->is_compiled_scope(callable->GetIsolate()));
7068 if (!is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) {
7069 Compiler::Compile(function, Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION,
7070 &is_compiled_scope);
7071 }
7072 if (shared->is_safe_to_skip_arguments_adaptor()) {
7073 return std::make_pair(
7074 WasmImportCallKind::kJSFunctionArityMismatchSkipAdaptor, callable);
7075 }
7076
7077 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kJSFunctionArityMismatch,
7078 callable);
7079 }
7080 // Unknown case. Use the call builtin.
7081 return std::make_pair(WasmImportCallKind::kUseCallBuiltin, callable);
7082}
7083
7084namespace {
7085
7086wasm::WasmOpcode GetMathIntrinsicOpcode(WasmImportCallKind kind,
7087 const char** name_ptr) {
7088#define CASE(name) \
7089 case WasmImportCallKind::k##name: \
7090 *name_ptr = "WasmMathIntrinsic:" #name; \
7091 return wasm::kExpr##name
7092 switch (kind) {
7093 CASE(F64Acos);
7094 CASE(F64Asin);
7095 CASE(F64Atan);
7096 CASE(F64Cos);
7097 CASE(F64Sin);
7098 CASE(F64Tan);
7099 CASE(F64Exp);
7100 CASE(F64Log);
7101 CASE(F64Atan2);
7102 CASE(F64Pow);
7103 CASE(F64Ceil);
7104 CASE(F64Floor);
7105 CASE(F64Sqrt);
7106 CASE(F64Min);
7107 CASE(F64Max);
7108 CASE(F64Abs);
7109 CASE(F32Min);
7110 CASE(F32Max);
7111 CASE(F32Abs);
7112 CASE(F32Ceil);
7113 CASE(F32Floor);
7114 CASE(F32Sqrt);
7115 CASE(F32ConvertF64);
7116 default:
7117 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
7118 return wasm::kExprUnreachable;
7119 }
7120#undef CASE
7121}

7130
7131 Zone zone(wasm_engine->allocator(), ZONE_NAME__func__, kCompressGraphZone);
7132
7133 // Compile a Wasm function with a single bytecode and let TurboFan
7134 // generate either inlined machine code or a call to a helper.
7135 SourcePositionTable* source_positions = nullptr;
7136 MachineGraph* mcgraph = zone.New<MachineGraph>(
7137 zone.New<Graph>(&zone), zone.New<CommonOperatorBuilder>(&zone),
7138 zone.New<MachineOperatorBuilder>(
7139 &zone, MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
7140 InstructionSelector::SupportedMachineOperatorFlags(),
7141 InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements()));
7142
7143 wasm::CompilationEnv env(
7144 nullptr, wasm::UseTrapHandler::kNoTrapHandler,
7145 wasm::RuntimeExceptionSupport::kNoRuntimeExceptionSupport,
7146 wasm::WasmFeatures::All(), wasm::LowerSimd::kNoLowerSimd);
7147
7148 WasmGraphBuilder builder(&env, mcgraph->zone(), mcgraph, sig,
7149 source_positions);
7150
7151 // Set up the graph start.
7152 Node* start = builder.Start(static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count() + 1 + 1));
7153 builder.SetEffectControl(start);
7154 builder.set_instance_node(builder.Param(wasm::kWasmInstanceParameterIndex));
7155
7156 // Generate either a unop or a binop.
7157 Node* node = nullptr;
7158 const char* debug_name = "WasmMathIntrinsic";
7159 auto opcode = GetMathIntrinsicOpcode(kind, &debug_name);
7160 switch (sig->parameter_count()) {
7161 case 1:
7162 node = builder.Unop(opcode, builder.Param(1));
7163 break;
7164 case 2:
7165 node = builder.Binop(opcode, builder.Param(1), builder.Param(2));
7166 break;
7167 default:
7168 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
7169 }
7170
7171 builder.Return(node);
7172
7173 // Run the compiler pipeline to generate machine code.
7174 auto call_descriptor = GetWasmCallDescriptor(&zone, sig);
7175 if (mcgraph->machine()->Is32()) {
7176 call_descriptor = GetI32WasmCallDescriptor(&zone, call_descriptor);
7177 }
7178
7179 wasm::WasmCompilationResult result = Pipeline::GenerateCodeForWasmNativeStub(
7180 wasm_engine, call_descriptor, mcgraph, CodeKind::WASM_FUNCTION,
7181 wasm::WasmCode::kFunction, debug_name, WasmStubAssemblerOptions(),
7182 source_positions);
7183 return result;
7184}
7185
7186} // namespace

7188wasm::WasmCompilationResult CompileWasmImportCallWrapper(
7189 wasm::WasmEngine* wasm_engine, wasm::CompilationEnv* env,
7190 WasmImportCallKind kind, const wasm::FunctionSig* sig,
7191 bool source_positions, int expected_arity) {
7192 DCHECK_NE(WasmImportCallKind::kLinkError, kind)((void) 0);
7193 DCHECK_NE(WasmImportCallKind::kWasmToWasm, kind)((void) 0);
7194
7195 // Check for math intrinsics first.
7196 if (FLAG_wasm_math_intrinsics &&
7197 kind >= WasmImportCallKind::kFirstMathIntrinsic &&
7198 kind <= WasmImportCallKind::kLastMathIntrinsic) {
7199 return CompileWasmMathIntrinsic(wasm_engine, kind, sig);
7200 }

7228 "wasm-to-js-%d-", static_cast<int>(kind));
7229 PrintSignature(VectorOf(func_name, kMaxNameLen) + name_prefix_len, sig, '-');

7234 WasmCallKind::kWasmImportWrapper);

7236 incoming = GetI32WasmCallDescriptor(&zone, incoming);
7237 }
7238 wasm::WasmCompilationResult result = Pipeline::GenerateCodeForWasmNativeStub(
7239 wasm_engine, incoming, mcgraph, CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION,
7240 wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToJsWrapper, func_name, WasmStubAssemblerOptions(),
7241 source_position_table);
7242 result.kind = wasm::WasmCompilationResult::kWasmToJsWrapper;
7243 return result;
7244}

7298
7299MaybeHandle<Code> CompileJSToJSWrapper(Isolate* isolate,
7300 const wasm::FunctionSig* sig) {
7301 std::unique_ptr<Zone> zone = std::make_unique<Zone>(
7302 isolate->allocator(), ZONE_NAME__func__, kCompressGraphZone);
7303 Graph* graph = zone->New<Graph>(zone.get());
7304 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = zone->New<CommonOperatorBuilder>(zone.get());
7305 MachineOperatorBuilder* machine = zone->New<MachineOperatorBuilder>(
7306 zone.get(), MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
7307 InstructionSelector::SupportedMachineOperatorFlags(),
7308 InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements());
7309 MachineGraph* mcgraph = zone->New<MachineGraph>(graph, common, machine);
7310
7311 WasmWrapperGraphBuilder builder(zone.get(), mcgraph, sig, nullptr,
7312 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer,
7313 wasm::WasmFeatures::FromIsolate(isolate));
7314 builder.BuildJSToJSWrapper(isolate);
7315
7316 int wasm_count = static_cast<int>(sig->parameter_count());
7317 CallDescriptor* incoming = Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
7318 zone.get(), false, wasm_count + 1, CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
7319
7320 // Build a name in the form "js-to-js:<params>:<returns>".
7321 constexpr size_t kMaxNameLen = 128;
7322 constexpr size_t kNamePrefixLen = 9;
7323 auto name_buffer = std::unique_ptr<char[]>(new char[kMaxNameLen]);
7324 memcpy(name_buffer.get(), "js-to-js:", kNamePrefixLen);
7325 PrintSignature(VectorOf(name_buffer.get(), kMaxNameLen) + kNamePrefixLen,
7326 sig);
7327
7328 // Run the compilation job synchronously.
7329 std::unique_ptr<OptimizedCompilationJob> job(
7330 Pipeline::NewWasmHeapStubCompilationJob(
7331 isolate, isolate->wasm_engine(), incoming, std::move(zone), graph,
7332 CodeKind::JS_TO_JS_FUNCTION, std::move(name_buffer),
7333 AssemblerOptions::Default(isolate)));
7334
7335 if (job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats()) ==
7336 CompilationJob::FAILED ||
7337 job->FinalizeJob(isolate) == CompilationJob::FAILED) {
7338 return {};
7339 }
7340 Handle<Code> code = job->compilation_info()->code();
7341
7342 return code;
7343}
7344
7345Handle<Code> CompileCWasmEntry(Isolate* isolate, const wasm::FunctionSig* sig) {
7346 std::unique_ptr<Zone> zone = std::make_unique<Zone>(
7347 isolate->allocator(), ZONE_NAME__func__, kCompressGraphZone);
7348 Graph* graph = zone->New<Graph>(zone.get());
7349 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = zone->New<CommonOperatorBuilder>(zone.get());
7350 MachineOperatorBuilder* machine = zone->New<MachineOperatorBuilder>(
7351 zone.get(), MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
7352 InstructionSelector::SupportedMachineOperatorFlags(),
7353 InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements());
7354 MachineGraph* mcgraph = zone->New<MachineGraph>(graph, common, machine);
7355
7356 WasmWrapperGraphBuilder builder(zone.get(), mcgraph, sig, nullptr,
7357 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer,
7358 wasm::WasmFeatures::FromIsolate(isolate));
7359 builder.BuildCWasmEntry();
7360
7361 // Schedule and compile to machine code.
7362 MachineType sig_types[] = {MachineType::Pointer(), // return
7363 MachineType::Pointer(), // target
7364 MachineType::AnyTagged(), // object_ref
7365 MachineType::Pointer(), // argv
7366 MachineType::Pointer()}; // c_entry_fp
7367 MachineSignature incoming_sig(1, 4, sig_types);
7368 // Traps need the root register, for TailCallRuntime to call
7369 // Runtime::kThrowWasmError.
7370 CallDescriptor::Flags flags = CallDescriptor::kInitializeRootRegister;
7371 CallDescriptor* incoming =
7372 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(zone.get(), &incoming_sig, flags);
7373
7374 // Build a name in the form "c-wasm-entry:<params>:<returns>".
7375 constexpr size_t kMaxNameLen = 128;
7376 constexpr size_t kNamePrefixLen = 13;
7377 auto name_buffer = std::unique_ptr<char[]>(new char[kMaxNameLen]);
7378 memcpy(name_buffer.get(), "c-wasm-entry:", kNamePrefixLen);
7379 PrintSignature(VectorOf(name_buffer.get(), kMaxNameLen) + kNamePrefixLen,
7380 sig);
7381
7382 // Run the compilation job synchronously.
7383 std::unique_ptr<OptimizedCompilationJob> job(
7384 Pipeline::NewWasmHeapStubCompilationJob(
7385 isolate, isolate->wasm_engine(), incoming, std::move(zone), graph,
7386 CodeKind::C_WASM_ENTRY, std::move(name_buffer),
7387 AssemblerOptions::Default(isolate)));
7388
7389 CHECK_NE(job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats()),do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpNEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(job->ExecuteJob(isolate->
counters()->runtime_call_stats()))>::type, typename ::v8
::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(CompilationJob::FAILED)
>::type>((job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->
runtime_call_stats())), (CompilationJob::FAILED)); do { if ((
__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s."
, "job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats())"
" " "!=" " " "CompilationJob::FAILED"); } } while (false); }
while (false)
7390 CompilationJob::FAILED)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpNEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(job->ExecuteJob(isolate->
counters()->runtime_call_stats()))>::type, typename ::v8
::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(CompilationJob::FAILED)
>::type>((job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->
runtime_call_stats())), (CompilationJob::FAILED)); do { if ((
__builtin_expect(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s."
, "job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats())"
" " "!=" " " "CompilationJob::FAILED"); } } while (false); }
while (false);
7391 CHECK_NE(job->FinalizeJob(isolate), CompilationJob::FAILED)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpNEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(job->FinalizeJob(isolate))
>::type, typename ::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype
(CompilationJob::FAILED)>::type>((job->FinalizeJob(isolate
)), (CompilationJob::FAILED)); do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(
!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "job->FinalizeJob(isolate)"
" " "!=" " " "CompilationJob::FAILED"); } } while (false); }
while (false);
7392
7393 return job->compilation_info()->code();
7394}
7395
7396namespace {
7397
7398bool BuildGraphForWasmFunction(AccountingAllocator* allocator,
7399 wasm::CompilationEnv* env,
7400 const wasm::FunctionBody& func_body,
7401 int func_index, wasm::WasmFeatures* detected,
7402 MachineGraph* mcgraph,
7403 NodeOriginTable* node_origins,
7404 SourcePositionTable* source_positions) {
7405 // Create a TF graph during decoding.
7406 WasmGraphBuilder builder(env, mcgraph->zone(), mcgraph, func_body.sig,
7407 source_positions);
7408 wasm::VoidResult graph_construction_result =
7409 wasm::BuildTFGraph(allocator, env->enabled_features, env->module,
7410 &builder, detected, func_body, node_origins);
7411 if (graph_construction_result.failed()) {
7412 if (FLAG_trace_wasm_compiler) {
7413 StdoutStream{} << "Compilation failed: "
7414 << graph_construction_result.error().message()
7415 << std::endl;
7416 }
7417 return false;
7418 }
7419
7420 builder.LowerInt64(WasmWrapperGraphBuilder::kCalledFromWasm);
7421
7422 if (builder.has_simd() &&
7423 (!CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128() || env->lower_simd)) {
7424 SimdScalarLowering(
7425 mcgraph, CreateMachineSignature(mcgraph->zone(), func_body.sig,
7426 WasmGraphBuilder::kCalledFromWasm))
7427 .LowerGraph();
7428 }
7429
7430 if (func_index >= FLAG_trace_wasm_ast_start &&
7431 func_index < FLAG_trace_wasm_ast_end) {
7432 PrintRawWasmCode(allocator, func_body, env->module, wasm::kPrintLocals);
7433 }
7434 return true;
7435}
7436
7437Vector<const char> GetDebugName(Zone* zone, int index) {
7438 // TODO(herhut): Use name from module if available.
7439 constexpr int kBufferLength = 24;
7440
7441 EmbeddedVector<char, kBufferLength> name_vector;
7442 int name_len = SNPrintF(name_vector, "wasm-function#%d", index);
7443 DCHECK(name_len > 0 && name_len < name_vector.length())((void) 0);
7444
7445 char* index_name = zone->NewArray<char>(name_len);
7446 memcpy(index_name, name_vector.begin(), name_len);
7447 return Vector<const char>(index_name, name_len);
7448}

)) & (kEnabledForRecording_CategoryGroupEnabledFlags | kEnabledForEventCallback_CategoryGroupEnabledFlags
)) { uint64_t h = v8::internal::tracing::AddTraceEvent( ('X')
, trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458, "wasm.CompileTopTier"
, v8::internal::tracing::kGlobalScope, v8::internal::tracing::
kNoId, v8::internal::tracing::kNoId, (static_cast<unsigned
int>(0)), "func_index", func_index, "body_size", func_body
.end - func_body.start); trace_event_unique_tracer7458 .Initialize
(trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458, "wasm.CompileTopTier"
, h); }
7458 func_body.end - func_body.start)static v8::base::AtomicWord trace_event_unique_atomic7458 = 0
; const uint8_t* trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458
; trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458 = reinterpret_cast
<const uint8_t*>(v8::base::Relaxed_Load(&(trace_event_unique_atomic7458
))); if (!trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458) { trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458
= v8::internal::tracing::TraceEventHelper::GetTracingController
() ->GetCategoryGroupEnabled("disabled-by-default-" "v8.wasm.detailed"
); v8::base::Relaxed_Store(&(trace_event_unique_atomic7458
), (reinterpret_cast<v8::base::AtomicWord>( trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458
))); };; v8::internal::tracing::ScopedTracer trace_event_unique_tracer7458
; if (v8::base::Relaxed_Load(reinterpret_cast<const v8::base
::Atomic8*>( trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458
)) & (kEnabledForRecording_CategoryGroupEnabledFlags | kEnabledForEventCallback_CategoryGroupEnabledFlags
)) { uint64_t h = v8::internal::tracing::AddTraceEvent( ('X')
, trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458, "wasm.CompileTopTier"
, v8::internal::tracing::kGlobalScope, v8::internal::tracing::
kNoId, v8::internal::tracing::kNoId, (static_cast<unsigned
int>(0)), "func_index", func_index, "body_size", func_body
.end - func_body.start); trace_event_unique_tracer7458 .Initialize
(trace_event_unique_category_group_enabled7458, "wasm.CompileTopTier"
, h); };
7459 Zone zone(wasm_engine->allocator(), ZONE_NAME__func__, kCompressGraphZone);
7460 MachineGraph* mcgraph = zone.New<MachineGraph>(
7461 zone.New<Graph>(&zone), zone.New<CommonOperatorBuilder>(&zone),
7462 zone.New<MachineOperatorBuilder>(
7463 &zone, MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
7464 InstructionSelector::SupportedMachineOperatorFlags(),
7465 InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements()));
7466
7467 OptimizedCompilationInfo info(GetDebugName(&zone, func_index), &zone,
7468 CodeKind::WASM_FUNCTION);
7469 if (env->runtime_exception_support) {
7470 info.set_wasm_runtime_exception_support();
7471 }
7472
7473 if (info.trace_turbo_json()) {
7474 TurboCfgFile tcf;
7475 tcf << AsC1VCompilation(&info);
7476 }
7477
7478 NodeOriginTable* node_origins =
7479 info.trace_turbo_json() ? zone.New<NodeOriginTable>(mcgraph->graph())
7480 : nullptr;
7481 SourcePositionTable* source_positions =
7482 mcgraph->zone()->New<SourcePositionTable>(mcgraph->graph());
7483 if (!BuildGraphForWasmFunction(wasm_engine->allocator(), env, func_body,
7484 func_index, detected, mcgraph, node_origins,
7485 source_positions)) {
7486 return wasm::WasmCompilationResult{};
7487 }
7488
7489 if (node_origins) {
7490 node_origins->AddDecorator();
7491 }
7492
7493 // Run the compiler pipeline to generate machine code.
7494 auto call_descriptor = GetWasmCallDescriptor(&zone, func_body.sig);
7495 if (mcgraph->machine()->Is32()) {
7496 call_descriptor = GetI32WasmCallDescriptor(&zone, call_descriptor);
7497 }
7498
7499 if (ContainsSimd(func_body.sig) &&
7500 (!CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128() || env->lower_simd)) {
7501 call_descriptor = GetI32WasmCallDescriptorForSimd(&zone, call_descriptor);
7502 }
7503
7504 Pipeline::GenerateCodeForWasmFunction(
7505 &info, wasm_engine, mcgraph, call_descriptor, source_positions,
7506 node_origins, func_body, env->module, func_index);
7507
7508 if (counters) {
7509 counters->wasm_compile_function_peak_memory_bytes()->AddSample(
7510 static_cast<int>(mcgraph->graph()->zone()->allocation_size()));
7511 }
7512 auto result = info.ReleaseWasmCompilationResult();
7513 CHECK_NOT_NULL(result)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((result) != nullptr)), 0))) {
V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "(result) != nullptr"); } } while
(false); // Compilation expected to succeed.
7514 DCHECK_EQ(wasm::ExecutionTier::kTurbofan, result->result_tier)((void) 0);
7515 return std::move(*result);
7516}
7517
7518namespace {
7519// Helper for allocating either an GP or FP reg, or the next stack slot.
7520class LinkageLocationAllocator {
7521 public:
7522 template <size_t kNumGpRegs, size_t kNumFpRegs>
7523 constexpr LinkageLocationAllocator(const Register (&gp)[kNumGpRegs],
7524 const DoubleRegister (&fp)[kNumFpRegs])
7525 : allocator_(wasm::LinkageAllocator(gp, fp)) {}
7526
7527 LinkageLocation Next(MachineRepresentation rep) {
7528 MachineType type = MachineType::TypeForRepresentation(rep);
7529 if (IsFloatingPoint(rep)) {
7530 if (allocator_.CanAllocateFP(rep)) {
7531 int reg_code = allocator_.NextFpReg(rep);
7532 return LinkageLocation::ForRegister(reg_code, type);
7533 }
7534 } else if (allocator_.CanAllocateGP()) {
7535 int reg_code = allocator_.NextGpReg();
7536 return LinkageLocation::ForRegister(reg_code, type);
7537 }
7538 // Cannot use register; use stack slot.
7539 int index = -1 - allocator_.NextStackSlot(rep);
7540 return LinkageLocation::ForCallerFrameSlot(index, type);
7541 }
7542
7543 void SetStackOffset(int offset) { allocator_.SetStackOffset(offset); }
7544 int NumStackSlots() const { return allocator_.NumStackSlots(); }
7545
7546 private:
7547 wasm::LinkageAllocator allocator_;
7548};
7549} // namespace
7550
7551// General code uses the above configuration data.
7552CallDescriptor* GetWasmCallDescriptor(
7553 Zone* zone, const wasm::FunctionSig* fsig,
7554 WasmGraphBuilder::UseRetpoline use_retpoline, WasmCallKind call_kind) {
7555 // The extra here is to accomodate the instance object as first parameter
7556 // and, when specified, the additional callable.
7557 bool extra_callable_param =
7558 call_kind == kWasmImportWrapper || call_kind == kWasmCapiFunction;
7559 int extra_params = extra_callable_param ? 2 : 1;
7560 LocationSignature::Builder locations(zone, fsig->return_count(),
7561 fsig->parameter_count() + extra_params);
7562
7563 // Add register and/or stack parameter(s).
7564 LinkageLocationAllocator params(wasm::kGpParamRegisters,
7565 wasm::kFpParamRegisters);
7566
7567 // The instance object.
7568 locations.AddParam(params.Next(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer));
7569 const size_t param_offset = 1; // Actual params start here.
7570
7571 // Parameters are separated into two groups (first all untagged, then all
7572 // tagged parameters). This allows for easy iteration of tagged parameters
7573 // during frame iteration.
7574 const size_t parameter_count = fsig->parameter_count();
7575 for (size_t i = 0; i < parameter_count; i++) {
7576 MachineRepresentation param = fsig->GetParam(i).machine_representation();
7577 // Skip tagged parameters (e.g. any-ref).
7578 if (IsAnyTagged(param)) continue;
7579 auto l = params.Next(param);
7580 locations.AddParamAt(i + param_offset, l);
7581 }
7582 for (size_t i = 0; i < parameter_count; i++) {
7583 MachineRepresentation param = fsig->GetParam(i).machine_representation();
7584 // Skip untagged parameters.
7585 if (!IsAnyTagged(param)) continue;
7586 auto l = params.Next(param);
7587 locations.AddParamAt(i + param_offset, l);
7588 }
7589
7590 // Import call wrappers have an additional (implicit) parameter, the callable.
7591 // For consistency with JS, we use the JSFunction register.
7592 if (extra_callable_param) {
7593 locations.AddParam(LinkageLocation::ForRegister(
7594 kJSFunctionRegister.code(), MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
7595 }
7596
7597 // Add return location(s).
7598 LinkageLocationAllocator rets(wasm::kGpReturnRegisters,
7599 wasm::kFpReturnRegisters);
7600
7601 int parameter_slots = params.NumStackSlots();
7602 if (ShouldPadArguments(parameter_slots)) parameter_slots++;
7603
7604 rets.SetStackOffset(parameter_slots);
7605
7606 const int return_count = static_cast<int>(locations.return_count_);
7607 for (int i = 0; i < return_count; i++) {
7608 MachineRepresentation ret = fsig->GetReturn(i).machine_representation();
7609 auto l = rets.Next(ret);
7610 locations.AddReturn(l);
7611 }
7612
7613 const RegList kCalleeSaveRegisters = 0;
7614 const RegList kCalleeSaveFPRegisters = 0;
7615
7616 // The target for wasm calls is always a code object.
7617 MachineType target_type = MachineType::Pointer();
7618 LinkageLocation target_loc = LinkageLocation::ForAnyRegister(target_type);
7619
7620 CallDescriptor::Kind descriptor_kind;
7621 if (call_kind == kWasmFunction) {
7622 descriptor_kind = CallDescriptor::kCallWasmFunction;
7623 } else if (call_kind == kWasmImportWrapper) {
7624 descriptor_kind = CallDescriptor::kCallWasmImportWrapper;
7625 } else {
7626 DCHECK_EQ(call_kind, kWasmCapiFunction)((void) 0);
7627 descriptor_kind = CallDescriptor::kCallWasmCapiFunction;
7628 }
7629
7630 CallDescriptor::Flags flags =
7631 use_retpoline ? CallDescriptor::kRetpoline : CallDescriptor::kNoFlags;
7632 return zone->New<CallDescriptor>( // --
7633 descriptor_kind, // kind
7634 target_type, // target MachineType
7635 target_loc, // target location
7636 locations.Build(), // location_sig
7637 parameter_slots, // stack_parameter_count
7638 compiler::Operator::kNoProperties, // properties
7639 kCalleeSaveRegisters, // callee-saved registers
7640 kCalleeSaveFPRegisters, // callee-saved fp regs
7641 flags, // flags
7642 "wasm-call", // debug name
7643 StackArgumentOrder::kDefault, // order of the arguments in the stack
7644 0, // allocatable registers
7645 rets.NumStackSlots() - parameter_slots); // stack_return_count
7646}
7647
7648namespace {
7649CallDescriptor* ReplaceTypeInCallDescriptorWith(
7650 Zone* zone, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, size_t num_replacements,
7651 MachineType input_type, MachineRepresentation output_type) {
7652 size_t parameter_count = call_descriptor->ParameterCount();
7653 size_t return_count = call_descriptor->ReturnCount();
7654 for (size_t i = 0; i < call_descriptor->ParameterCount(); i++) {
7655 if (call_descriptor->GetParameterType(i) == input_type) {
7656 parameter_count += num_replacements - 1;
7657 }
7658 }
7659 for (size_t i = 0; i < call_descriptor->ReturnCount(); i++) {
7660 if (call_descriptor->GetReturnType(i) == input_type) {
7661 return_count += num_replacements - 1;
7662 }
7663 }
7664 if (parameter_count == call_descriptor->ParameterCount() &&
7665 return_count == call_descriptor->ReturnCount()) {
7666 return const_cast<CallDescriptor*>(call_descriptor);
7667 }
7668
7669 LocationSignature::Builder locations(zone, return_count, parameter_count);
7670
7671 // The last parameter may be the special callable parameter. In that case we
7672 // have to preserve it as the last parameter, i.e. we allocate it in the new
7673 // location signature again in the same register.
7674 bool has_callable_param =
7675 (call_descriptor->GetInputLocation(call_descriptor->InputCount() - 1) ==
7676 LinkageLocation::ForRegister(kJSFunctionRegister.code(),
7677 MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
7678 LinkageLocationAllocator params(wasm::kGpParamRegisters,
7679 wasm::kFpParamRegisters);
7680 for (size_t i = 0, e = call_descriptor->ParameterCount() -
7681 (has_callable_param ? 1 : 0);
7682 i < e; i++) {
7683 if (call_descriptor->GetParameterType(i) == input_type) {
7684 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_replacements; j++) {
7685 locations.AddParam(params.Next(output_type));
7686 }
7687 } else {
7688 locations.AddParam(
7689 params.Next(call_descriptor->GetParameterType(i).representation()));
7690 }
7691 }
7692 if (has_callable_param) {
7693 locations.AddParam(LinkageLocation::ForRegister(
7694 kJSFunctionRegister.code(), MachineType::TaggedPointer()));
7695 }
7696
7697 LinkageLocationAllocator rets(wasm::kGpReturnRegisters,
7698 wasm::kFpReturnRegisters);
7699 rets.SetStackOffset(params.NumStackSlots());
7700 for (size_t i = 0; i < call_descriptor->ReturnCount(); i++) {
7701 if (call_descriptor->GetReturnType(i) == input_type) {
7702 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_replacements; j++) {
7703 locations.AddReturn(rets.Next(output_type));
7704 }
7705 } else {
7706 locations.AddReturn(
7707 rets.Next(call_descriptor->GetReturnType(i).representation()));
7708 }
7709 }
7710
7711 return zone->New<CallDescriptor>( // --
7712 call_descriptor->kind(), // kind
7713 call_descriptor->GetInputType(0), // target MachineType
7714 call_descriptor->GetInputLocation(0), // target location
7715 locations.Build(), // location_sig
7716 params.NumStackSlots(), // stack_parameter_count
7717 call_descriptor->properties(), // properties
7718 call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters(), // callee-saved registers
7719 call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters(), // callee-saved fp regs
7720 call_descriptor->flags(), // flags
7721 call_descriptor->debug_name(), // debug name
7722 call_descriptor->GetStackArgumentOrder(), // stack order
7723 call_descriptor->AllocatableRegisters(), // allocatable registers
7724 rets.NumStackSlots() - params.NumStackSlots()); // stack_return_count
7725}
7726} // namespace
7727
7728CallDescriptor* GetI32WasmCallDescriptor(
7729 Zone* zone, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor) {
7730 return ReplaceTypeInCallDescriptorWith(zone, call_descriptor, 2,
7731 MachineType::Int64(),
7732 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
7733}
7734
7735CallDescriptor* GetI32WasmCallDescriptorForSimd(
7736 Zone* zone, CallDescriptor* call_descriptor) {
7737 return ReplaceTypeInCallDescriptorWith(zone, call_descriptor, 4,
7738 MachineType::Simd128(),
7739 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
7740}
7741
7742AssemblerOptions WasmAssemblerOptions() {
7743 AssemblerOptions options;
7744 // Relocation info required to serialize {WasmCode} for proper functions.
7745 options.record_reloc_info_for_serialization = true;
7746 options.enable_root_array_delta_access = false;
7747 return options;
7748}
7749
7750AssemblerOptions WasmStubAssemblerOptions() {
7751 AssemblerOptions options;
7752 // Relocation info not necessary because stubs are not serialized.
7753 options.record_reloc_info_for_serialization = false;
7754 options.enable_root_array_delta_access = false;
7755 return options;
7756}
